b/vendor/plugins/redmine_dmsf/README.txt
1 
Redmine DMSF is Document Management System Features plugin for Redmine issue tracking system.
2 

  		





  
  3
  
    
It is aimed to replace current Redmine's Documents module.


  		





  
  4
  
    

  		





  
  5
  
    
Initial development was for Kontron AG R&D department and it is released as open source thanks to their generosity.


  		





  
  6
  
    

  		





  
  7
  
    
Project home: http://code.google.com/p/redmine-dmsf/


  		





  
  8
  
    

  		





  
  9
  
    
1. License


  		





  
  10
  
    

  		





  
  11
  
    
Redmine Document Management System "Features" plugin is distributed under GNU GPL version 2.


  		





  
  12
  
    

  		





  
  13
  
    
License itself is here: http://www.gnu.org/licenses/old-licenses/gpl-2.0.html#SEC1


  		





  
  14
  
    

  		





  
  15
  
    
2. Installation


  		





  
  16
  
    

  		





  
  17
  
    
2.1. Prerequisities


  		





  
  18
  
    

  		





  
  19
  
    
* Redmine 1.1.x


  		





  
  20
  
    
* Ruby Zip library - rubyzip gem


  		





  
  21
  
    

  		





  
  22
  
    
2.1.1. Fulltext search (optional) 


  		





  
  23
  
    

  		





  
  24
  
    
If you want to use fulltext search abilities:


  		





  
  25
  
    
* Xapian (http://xapian.org) search engine


  		





  
  26
  
    
* Xapian Omega indexing tool


  		





  
  27
  
    
* Xapian ruby bindings - xapian or xapian-full gem


  		





  
  28
  
    
 


  		





  
  29
  
    
To index some files with omega you may have to install some other packages like xpdf, antiword, ...


  		





  
  30
  
    

  		





  
  31
  
    
From Omega documentation:


  		





  
  32
  
    

  		





  
  33
  
    
    * PDF (.pdf) if pdftotext is available (comes with xpdf)


  		





  
  34
  
    
    * PostScript (.ps, .eps, .ai) if ps2pdf (from ghostscript) and pdftotext (comes with xpdf) are available


  		





  
  35
  
    
    * OpenOffice/StarOffice documents (.sxc, .stc, .sxd, .std, .sxi, .sti, .sxm, .sxw, .sxg, .stw) if unzip is available


  		





  
  36
  
    
    * OpenDocument format documents (.odt, .ods, .odp, .odg, .odc, .odf, .odb, .odi, .odm, .ott, .ots, .otp, .otg, .otc, .otf, .oti, .oth) if unzip is available


  		





  
  37
  
    
    * MS Word documents (.doc, .dot) if antiword is available


  		





  
  38
  
    
    * MS Excel documents (.xls, .xlb, .xlt) if xls2csv is available (comes with catdoc)


  		





  
  39
  
    
    * MS Powerpoint documents (.ppt, .pps) if catppt is available (comes with catdoc)


  		





  
  40
  
    
    * MS Office 2007 documents (.docx, .dotx, .xlsx, .xlst, .pptx, .potx, .ppsx) if unzip is available


  		





  
  41
  
    
    * Wordperfect documents (.wpd) if wpd2text is available (comes with libwpd)


  		





  
  42
  
    
    * MS Works documents (.wps, .wpt) if wps2text is available (comes with libwps)


  		





  
  43
  
    
    * AbiWord documents (.abw)


  		





  
  44
  
    
    * Compressed AbiWord documents (.zabw) if gzip is available


  		





  
  45
  
    
    * Rich Text Format documents (.rtf) if unrtf is available


  		





  
  46
  
    
    * Perl POD documentation (.pl, .pm, .pod) if pod2text is available


  		





  
  47
  
    
    * TeX DVI files (.dvi) if catdvi is available


  		





  
  48
  
    
    * DjVu files (.djv, .djvu) if djvutxt is available


  		





  
  49
  
    
    * XPS files (.xps) if unzip is available


  		





  
  50
  
    

  		





  
  51
  
    
On Debinan (Squeeze) use:


  		





  
  52
  
    
apt-get install libxapian-ruby1.8 xapian-omega libxapian-dev xpdf antiword unzip\


  		





  
  53
  
    
  catdoc libwpd8c2a libwps-0.1-1 gzip unrtf catdvi djview djview3


  		





  
  54
  
    

  		





  
  55
  
    
On Ubuntu use:


  		





  
  56
  
    
sudo apt-get install libxapian-ruby1.8 xapian-omega libxapian-dev xpdf antiword unzip\


  		





  
  57
  
    
  catdoc libwpd-0.9-9 libwps-0.2-2 gzip unrtf catdvi djview djview3


  		





  
  58
  
    

  		





  
  59
  
    
2.2. Setup/Upgrade


  		





  
  60
  
    

  		





  
  61
  
    
* In case of upgrade BACKUP YOUR DATABASE first


  		





  
  62
  
    
* Put redmine_dmsf plugin directory into vendor/plugins


  		





  
  63
  
    
* Initialize/Update database:


  		





  
  64
  
    
    rake db:migrate:plugins RAILS_ENV="production"


  		





  
  65
  
    
* The access rights must be set for web server, example: 


  		





  
  66
  
    
    chown -R www-data:www-data /opt/redmine/vendor/plugins/redmine_dmsf


  		





  
  67
  
    
* Restart web server


  		





  
  68
  
    
* You should configure plugin via Redmine interface: Administration -> Plugins -> DMSF -> Configure


  		





  
  69
  
    
* Assign DMSF permissions to appropriate roles


  		





  
  70
  
    

  		





  
  71
  
    
2.2.1. Fulltext search (optional)


  		





  
  72
  
    

  		





  
  73
  
    
If you want to use fulltext search features, you must setup file content indexing.


  		





  
  74
  
    

  		





  
  75
  
    
It is necessary to index DMSF files with omega before searching attemts to recieve some output:


  		





  
  76
  
    
    omindex -s english -l 1 -U / --db {path to index database from configuration} {path to storage from configuration}


  		





  
  77
  
    

  		





  
  78
  
    
This command must be run on regular basis (e.g. from cron)


  		





  
  79
  
    

  		





  
  80
  
    
Example of cron job (once per hour at 8th minute):


  		





  
  81
  
    
    8 * * * * root /usr/bin/omindex -s english -l 1 -U / --db /opt/redmine/files/dmsf_index /opt/redmine/files/dmsf


  		





  
  82
  
    

  		





  
  83
  
    
Use omindex -h for help.


  		





  
  84
  
    

  		





  
  85
  
    
2.3. Usage


  		





  
  86
  
    

  		





  
  87
  
    
DMSF act as project module so you must check DMSF in project settings.


  		





  
  88
  
    

  		





  
  89
  
    
Search options will now contain "Dmsf files" check, that allows you to search DMSF content.


  		





  
  90
  
    

  		





  
  91
  
    
There is possibility to link DMSF files from Wiki entries:


  		





  
  92
  
    
    {{dmsf(17)}} link to file with id 17


  		





  
  93
  
    
    {{dmsf(17,File)}} link to file with id 17 with link text "File"


  		





  
  94
  
    
    {{dmsf(17,File,10)}} link to file with id 17 with link text "File" and link pointing to revision 10


  		





  
  95
  
    
DMSF file/revision id can be found in link for file/revision download.


  		





  
  96
  
    

  		





  
  97
  
    
There is possibility to link DMSF folders from Wiki entries:


  		





  
  98
  
    
    {{dmsff(5)}} link to folder with id 5


  		





  
  99
  
    
    {{dmsff(5,Folder)}} link to folder with id 5 with link text "Folder"


  		





  
  100
  
    
DMSF folder id can be found in link for folder opening.


  		





  
  101
  
    

  		





  
  102
  
    
You can also publish Wiki help description. 


  		





  
  103
  
    
In file <redmine_root>/public/help/wiki_syntax_detailed.html include after document link description:


  		





  
  104
  
    
<ul>


  		





  
  105
  
    
    <li>


  		





  
  106
  
    
    	DMSF:


  		





  
  107
  
    
        <ul>


  		





  
  108
  
    
            <li><strong>{{dmsf(17)}}</strong> (link to file with id 17)</li>


  		





  
  109
  
    
            <li><strong>{{dmsf(17,File)}}</strong> (link to file with id 17 with link text "File")</li>


  		





  
  110
  
    
            <li><strong>{{dmsf(17,File,10)}}</strong> (link to file with id 17 with link text "File" and link pointing to revision 10)</li>


  		





  
  111
  
    
            <li><strong>{{dmsff(5)}}</strong> (link to folder with id 5)</li>


  		





  
  112
  
    
            <li><strong>{{dmsff(5,Folder)}}</strong> (link to folder with id 5 with link text "Folder")</li>


  		





  
  113
  
    
        </ul>


  		





  
  114
  
    
        DMSF file/revision id can be found in link for file/revision download.<br />


  		





  
  115
  
    
        DMSF folder id can be found in link for folder opening.


  		





  
  116
  
    
    </li>


  		





  
  117
  
    
</ul>

class DmsfController < ApplicationController


  		





  
  20
  
    
  unloadable


  		





  
  21
  
    
  


  		





  
  22
  
    
  before_filter :find_project


  		





  
  23
  
    
  before_filter :authorize, :except => [:delete_entries]


  		





  
  24
  
    
  before_filter :find_folder, :except => [:new, :create, :edit_root, :save_root]


  		





  
  25
  
    
  before_filter :find_parent, :only => [:new, :create]


  		





  
  26
  
    
  


  		





  
  27
  
    
  verify :method => :post, :only => [:delete_entries, :create, :save, :delete, :save_root, :notify_activate, :notify_deactivate], 


  		





  
  28
  
    
    :render => { :nothing => true, :status => :method_not_allowed }


  		





  
  29
  
    
  


  		





  
  30
  
    
  def show


  		





  
  31
  
    
    if @folder.nil?


  		





  
  32
  
    
      @subfolders = DmsfFolder.project_root_folders(@project)


  		





  
  33
  
    
      @files = DmsfFile.project_root_files(@project)


  		





  
  34
  
    
    else 


  		





  
  35
  
    
      @subfolders = @folder.subfolders


  		





  
  36
  
    
      @files = @folder.files


  		





  
  37
  
    
    end


  		





  
  38
  
    
    


  		





  
  39
  
    
    @files.sort! do |a,b|


  		





  
  40
  
    
      a.last_revision.title <=> b.last_revision.title


  		





  
  41
  
    
    end


  		





  
  42
  
    
  end


  		





  
  43
  
    

  		





  
  44
  
    
  def entries_operation


  		





  
  45
  
    
    selected_folders = params[:subfolders]


  		





  
  46
  
    
    selected_files = params[:files]


  		





  
  47
  
    
    


  		





  
  48
  
    
    if selected_folders.nil? && selected_files.nil?


  		





  
  49
  
    
      flash[:warning] = l(:warning_no_entries_selected)


  		





  
  50
  
    
      redirect_to :action => "show", :id => @project, :folder_id => @folder


  		





  
  51
  
    
      return


  		





  
  52
  
    
    end


  		





  
  53
  
    
    


  		





  
  54
  
    
    if !params[:email_entries].blank?


  		





  
  55
  
    
      email_entries(selected_folders, selected_files)


  		





  
  56
  
    
    else


  		





  
  57
  
    
      download_entries(selected_folders, selected_files)


  		





  
  58
  
    
    end


  		





  
  59
  
    
  rescue ZipMaxFilesError


  		





  
  60
  
    
    flash[:error] = l(:error_max_files_exceeded, :number => Setting.plugin_redmine_dmsf["dmsf_max_file_download"].to_i.to_s)


  		





  
  61
  
    
    redirect_to({:controller => "dmsf", :action => "show", :id => @project, :folder_id => @folder})


  		





  
  62
  
    
  rescue EmailMaxFileSize


  		





  
  63
  
    
    flash[:error] = l(:error_max_email_filesize_exceeded, :number => Setting.plugin_redmine_dmsf["dmsf_max_email_filesize"].to_s)


  		





  
  64
  
    
    redirect_to({:controller => "dmsf", :action => "show", :id => @project, :folder_id => @folder})


  		





  
  65
  
    
  rescue DmsfAccessError


  		





  
  66
  
    
    render_403


  		





  
  67
  
    
  end


  		





  
  68
  
    

  		





  
  69
  
    
  def entries_email


  		





  
  70
  
    
    @email_params = params[:email]


  		





  
  71
  
    
    if @email_params["to"].strip.blank?


  		





  
  72
  
    
      flash.now[:error] = l(:error_email_to_must_be_entered)


  		





  
  73
  
    
      render :action => "email_entries"


  		





  
  74
  
    
      return


  		





  
  75
  
    
    end


  		





  
  76
  
    
    DmsfMailer.deliver_send_documents(User.current, @email_params["to"], @email_params["cc"],


  		





  
  77
  
    
      @email_params["subject"], @email_params["zipped_content"], @email_params["body"])


  		





  
  78
  
    
    File.delete(@email_params["zipped_content"])


  		





  
  79
  
    
    flash[:notice] = l(:notice_email_sent)


  		





  
  80
  
    
    redirect_to({:controller => "dmsf", :action => "show", :id => @project, :folder_id => @folder})


  		





  
  81
  
    
  end


  		





  
  82
  
    

  		





  
  83
  
    
  class ZipMaxFilesError < StandardError


  		





  
  84
  
    
  end


  		





  
  85
  
    

  		





  
  86
  
    
  class EmailMaxFileSize < StandardError


  		





  
  87
  
    
  end


  		





  
  88
  
    

  		





  
  89
  
    
  def delete_entries


  		





  
  90
  
    
    selected_folders = params[:subfolders]


  		





  
  91
  
    
    selected_files = params[:files]


  		





  
  92
  
    
    if selected_folders.nil? && selected_files.nil?


  		





  
  93
  
    
      flash[:warning] = l(:warning_no_entries_selected)


  		





  
  94
  
    
    else


  		





  
  95
  
    
      failed_entries = []


  		





  
  96
  
    
      deleted_files = []


  		





  
  97
  
    
      deleted_folders = []


  		





  
  98
  
    
      unless selected_folders.nil?


  		





  
  99
  
    
        if User.current.allowed_to?(:folder_manipulation, @project)


  		





  
  100
  
    
          selected_folders.each do |subfolderid|


  		





  
  101
  
    
            subfolder = DmsfFolder.find(subfolderid)


  		





  
  102
  
    
            next if subfolder.nil?


  		





  
  103
  
    
            if subfolder.project != @project || !subfolder.delete


  		





  
  104
  
    
              failed_entries.push(subfolder) 


  		





  
  105
  
    
            else


  		





  
  106
  
    
              deleted_folders.push(subfolder)


  		





  
  107
  
    
            end


  		





  
  108
  
    
          end


  		





  
  109
  
    
        else


  		





  
  110
  
    
          flash[:error] = l(:error_user_has_not_right_delete_folder)


  		





  
  111
  
    
        end


  		





  
  112
  
    
      end


  		





  
  113
  
    
      unless selected_files.nil?


  		





  
  114
  
    
        if User.current.allowed_to?(:file_manipulation, @project)


  		





  
  115
  
    
          selected_files.each do |fileid|


  		





  
  116
  
    
            file = DmsfFile.find(fileid)


  		





  
  117
  
    
            next if file.nil?


  		





  
  118
  
    
            if file.project != @project || !file.delete


  		





  
  119
  
    
              failed_entries.push(file)


  		





  
  120
  
    
            else


  		





  
  121
  
    
              deleted_files.push(file)


  		





  
  122
  
    
            end


  		





  
  123
  
    
          end


  		





  
  124
  
    
        else


  		





  
  125
  
    
          flash[:error] = l(:error_user_has_not_right_delete_file)


  		





  
  126
  
    
        end


  		





  
  127
  
    
      end


  		





  
  128
  
    
      unless deleted_files.empty?


  		





  
  129
  
    
        deleted_files.each {|f| log_activity(f, "deleted")}


  		





  
  130
  
    
        DmsfMailer.deliver_files_deleted(User.current, deleted_files)


  		





  
  131
  
    
      end


  		





  
  132
  
    
      if failed_entries.empty?


  		





  
  133
  
    
        flash[:notice] = l(:notice_entries_deleted)


  		





  
  134
  
    
      else


  		





  
  135
  
    
        flash[:warning] = l(:warning_some_entries_were_not_deleted, :entries => failed_entries.map{|e| e.title}.join(", "))


  		





  
  136
  
    
      end


  		





  
  137
  
    
    end


  		





  
  138
  
    
    


  		





  
  139
  
    
    redirect_to :controller => "dmsf", :action => "show", :id => @project, :folder_id => @folder


  		





  
  140
  
    
  end


  		





  
  141
  
    

  		





  
  142
  
    
  # Folder manipulation


  		





  
  143
  
    

  		





  
  144
  
    
  def new


  		





  
  145
  
    
    @pathfolder = @parent


  		





  
  146
  
    
    render :action => "edit"


  		





  
  147
  
    
  end


  		





  
  148
  
    

  		





  
  149
  
    
  def create


  		





  
  150
  
    
    @folder = DmsfFolder.new(params[:dmsf_folder])


  		





  
  151
  
    
    @folder.project = @project


  		





  
  152
  
    
    @folder.user = User.current


  		





  
  153
  
    
    if @folder.save


  		





  
  154
  
    
      flash[:notice] = l(:notice_folder_created)


  		





  
  155
  
    
      redirect_to({:controller => "dmsf", :action => "show", :id => @project, :folder_id => @folder})


  		





  
  156
  
    
    else


  		





  
  157
  
    
      @pathfolder = @parent


  		





  
  158
  
    
      render :action => "edit"


  		





  
  159
  
    
    end


  		





  
  160
  
    
  end


  		





  
  161
  
    

  		





  
  162
  
    
  def edit


  		





  
  163
  
    
    @parent = @folder.folder


  		





  
  164
  
    
    @pathfolder = copy_folder(@folder)


  		





  
  165
  
    
  end


  		





  
  166
  
    

  		





  
  167
  
    
  def save


  		





  
  168
  
    
    unless params[:dmsf_folder]


  		





  
  169
  
    
      redirect_to :controller => "dmsf", :action => "show", :id => @project, :folder_id => @folder


  		





  
  170
  
    
      return


  		





  
  171
  
    
    end


  		





  
  172
  
    
    @pathfolder = copy_folder(@folder)


  		





  
  173
  
    
    @folder.attributes = params[:dmsf_folder]


  		





  
  174
  
    
    if @folder.save


  		





  
  175
  
    
      flash[:notice] = l(:notice_folder_details_were_saved)


  		





  
  176
  
    
      redirect_to :controller => "dmsf", :action => "show", :id => @project, :folder_id => @folder


  		





  
  177
  
    
    else


  		





  
  178
  
    
      render :action => "edit"


  		





  
  179
  
    
    end


  		





  
  180
  
    
  end


  		





  
  181
  
    

  		





  
  182
  
    
  def delete


  		





  
  183
  
    
    check_project(@delete_folder = DmsfFolder.find(params[:delete_folder_id]))


  		





  
  184
  
    
    if !@delete_folder.nil?


  		





  
  185
  
    
      if @delete_folder.delete


  		





  
  186
  
    
        flash[:notice] = l(:notice_folder_deleted)


  		





  
  187
  
    
      else


  		





  
  188
  
    
        flash[:error] = l(:error_folder_is_not_empty)


  		





  
  189
  
    
      end


  		





  
  190
  
    
    end


  		





  
  191
  
    
    redirect_to :controller => "dmsf", :action => "show", :id => @project, :folder_id => @folder


  		





  
  192
  
    
  rescue DmsfAccessError


  		





  
  193
  
    
    render_403  


  		





  
  194
  
    
  end


  		





  
  195
  
    

  		





  
  196
  
    
  def edit_root


  		





  
  197
  
    
  end


  		





  
  198
  
    

  		





  
  199
  
    
  def save_root


  		





  
  200
  
    
    @project.dmsf_description = params[:project][:dmsf_description]


  		





  
  201
  
    
    @project.save!


  		





  
  202
  
    
    flash[:notice] = l(:notice_folder_details_were_saved)


  		





  
  203
  
    
    redirect_to :controller => "dmsf", :action => "show", :id => @project


  		





  
  204
  
    
  end


  		





  
  205
  
    

  		





  
  206
  
    
  def notify_activate


  		





  
  207
  
    
    if @folder.notification


  		





  
  208
  
    
      flash[:warning] = l(:warning_folder_notifications_already_activated)


  		





  
  209
  
    
    else


  		





  
  210
  
    
      @folder.notify_activate


  		





  
  211
  
    
      flash[:notice] = l(:notice_folder_notifications_activated)


  		





  
  212
  
    
    end


  		





  
  213
  
    
    redirect_to params[:current] ? params[:current] : 


  		





  
  214
  
    
      {:controller => "dmsf", :action => "show", :id => @project, :folder_id => @folder.folder}


  		





  
  215
  
    
  end


  		





  
  216
  
    
  


  		





  
  217
  
    
  def notify_deactivate


  		





  
  218
  
    
    if !@folder.notification


  		





  
  219
  
    
      flash[:warning] = l(:warning_folder_notifications_already_deactivated)


  		





  
  220
  
    
    else


  		





  
  221
  
    
      @folder.notify_deactivate


  		





  
  222
  
    
      flash[:notice] = l(:notice_folder_notifications_deactivated)


  		





  
  223
  
    
    end


  		





  
  224
  
    
    redirect_to params[:current] ? params[:current] : 


  		





  
  225
  
    
      {:controller => "dmsf", :action => "show", :id => @project, :folder_id => @folder.folder}


  		





  
  226
  
    
  end

  230
  
    
  def log_activity(file, action)


  		





  
  231
  
    
    Rails.logger.info "#{Time.now.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')} #{User.current.login}@#{request.remote_ip}/#{request.env['HTTP_X_FORWARDED_FOR']}: #{action} dmsf://#{file.project.identifier}/#{file.id}"


  		





  
  232
  
    
  end


  		





  
  233
  
    

  		





  
  234
  
    
  def email_entries(selected_folders, selected_files)


  		





  
  235
  
    
    zip = DmsfZip.new


  		





  
  236
  
    
    zip_entries(zip, selected_folders, selected_files)


  		





  
  237
  
    
    


  		





  
  238
  
    
    ziped_content = "#{DmsfHelper.temp_dir}/#{DmsfHelper.temp_filename("dmsf_email_sent_documents.zip")}";


  		





  
  239
  
    
    


  		





  
  240
  
    
    File.open(ziped_content, "wb") do |f|


  		





  
  241
  
    
      zip_file = File.open(zip.finish, "rb")


  		





  
  242
  
    
      while (buffer = zip_file.read(8192))


  		





  
  243
  
    
        f.write(buffer)


  		





  
  244
  
    
      end


  		





  
  245
  
    
    end


  		





  
  246
  
    

  		





  
  247
  
    
    max_filesize = Setting.plugin_redmine_dmsf["dmsf_max_email_filesize"].to_f


  		





  
  248
  
    
    if max_filesize > 0 && File.size(ziped_content) > max_filesize * 1048576


  		





  
  249
  
    
      raise EmailMaxFileSize


  		





  
  250
  
    
    end


  		





  
  251
  
    
    


  		





  
  252
  
    
    zip.files.each do |f| 


  		





  
  253
  
    
      log_activity(f,"emailing zip")


  		





  
  254
  
    
      audit = DmsfFileRevisionAccess.new(:user_id => User.current.id, :dmsf_file_revision_id => f.last_revision.id, 


  		





  
  255
  
    
        :action => DmsfFileRevisionAccess::EmailAction)


  		





  
  256
  
    
      audit.save!


  		





  
  257
  
    
    end


  		





  
  258
  
    
    


  		





  
  259
  
    
    @email_params = {"zipped_content" => ziped_content}


  		





  
  260
  
    
    render :action => "email_entries"


  		





  
  261
  
    
  ensure


  		





  
  262
  
    
    zip.close unless zip.nil? 


  		





  
  263
  
    
  end


  		





  
  264
  
    

  		





  
  265
  
    
  def download_entries(selected_folders, selected_files)


  		





  
  266
  
    
    zip = DmsfZip.new


  		





  
  267
  
    
    zip_entries(zip, selected_folders, selected_files)


  		





  
  268
  
    
    


  		





  
  269
  
    
    zip.files.each do |f| 


  		





  
  270
  
    
      log_activity(f,"download zip")


  		





  
  271
  
    
      audit = DmsfFileRevisionAccess.new(:user_id => User.current.id, :dmsf_file_revision_id => f.last_revision.id, 


  		





  
  272
  
    
        :action => DmsfFileRevisionAccess::DownloadAction)


  		





  
  273
  
    
      audit.save!


  		





  
  274
  
    
    end


  		





  
  275
  
    
    


  		





  
  276
  
    
    send_file(zip.finish, 


  		





  
  277
  
    
      :filename => filename_for_content_disposition(@project.name + "-" + DateTime.now.strftime("%y%m%d%H%M%S") + ".zip"),


  		





  
  278
  
    
      :type => "application/zip", 


  		





  
  279
  
    
      :disposition => "attachment")


  		





  
  280
  
    
  ensure


  		





  
  281
  
    
    zip.close unless zip.nil? 


  		





  
  282
  
    
  end


  		





  
  283
  
    
  


  		





  
  284
  
    
  def zip_entries(zip, selected_folders, selected_files)


  		





  
  285
  
    
    if selected_folders && selected_folders.is_a?(Array)


  		





  
  286
  
    
      selected_folders.each do |selected_folder_id|


  		





  
  287
  
    
        check_project(folder = DmsfFolder.find(selected_folder_id))


  		





  
  288
  
    
        zip.add_folder(folder, (@folder.dmsf_path_str unless @folder.nil?)) unless folder.nil?


  		





  
  289
  
    
      end


  		





  
  290
  
    
    end


  		





  
  291
  
    
    if selected_files && selected_files.is_a?(Array)


  		





  
  292
  
    
      selected_files.each do |selected_file_id|


  		





  
  293
  
    
        check_project(file = DmsfFile.find(selected_file_id))


  		





  
  294
  
    
        zip.add_file(file, (@folder.dmsf_path_str unless @folder.nil?)) unless file.nil?


  		





  
  295
  
    
      end


  		





  
  296
  
    
    end


  		





  
  297
  
    
    


  		





  
  298
  
    
    max_files = 0


  		





  
  299
  
    
    max_files = Setting.plugin_redmine_dmsf["dmsf_max_file_download"].to_i


  		





  
  300
  
    
    if max_files > 0 && zip.files.length > max_files


  		





  
  301
  
    
      raise ZipMaxFilesError, zip.files.length


  		





  
  302
  
    
    end


  		





  
  303
  
    
    


  		





  
  304
  
    
    zip


  		





  
  305
  
    
  end


  		





  
  306
  
    
  


  		





  
  307
  
    
  def find_project


  		





  
  308
  
    
    @project = Project.find(params[:id])


  		





  
  309
  
    
  end


  		





  
  310
  
    
  


  		





  
  311
  
    
  def find_folder


  		





  
  312
  
    
    @folder = DmsfFolder.find(params[:folder_id]) if params.keys.include?("folder_id")


  		





  
  313
  
    
    check_project(@folder)


  		





  
  314
  
    
  rescue DmsfAccessError


  		





  
  315
  
    
    render_403


  		





  
  316
  
    
  end


  		





  
  317
  
    

  		





  
  318
  
    
  def find_parent


  		





  
  319
  
    
    @parent = DmsfFolder.find(params[:parent_id]) if params.keys.include?("parent_id")


  		





  
  320
  
    
    check_project(@parent)


  		





  
  321
  
    
  rescue DmsfAccessError


  		





  
  322
  
    
    render_403


  		





  
  323
  
    
  end


  		





  
  324
  
    

  		





  
  325
  
    
  def check_project(entry)


  		





  
  326
  
    
    if !entry.nil? && entry.project != @project


  		





  
  327
  
    
      raise DmsfAccessError, l(:error_entry_project_does_not_match_current_project) 


  		





  
  328
  
    
    end


  		





  
  329
  
    
  end


  		





  
  330
  
    

  		





  
  331
  
    
  def copy_folder(folder)


  		





  
  332
  
    
    copy = folder.clone


  		





  
  333
  
    
    copy.id = folder.id


  		





  
  334
  
    
    copy


  		





  
  335
  
    
  end

  337
  
    
end

class DmsfFilesController < ApplicationController


  		





  
  20
  
    
  unloadable


  		





  
  21
  
    
  


  		





  
  22
  
    
  menu_item :dmsf


  		





  
  23
  
    
  


  		





  
  24
  
    
  before_filter :find_file, :except => [:delete_revision]


  		





  
  25
  
    
  before_filter :find_revision, :only => [:delete_revision]


  		





  
  26
  
    
  before_filter :authorize


  		





  
  27
  
    

  		





  
  28
  
    
  verify :method => :post, :only => [:create_revision, :delete_revision, :delete, :lock, :unlock, :notify_activate, :notify_deactivate], 


  		





  
  29
  
    
    :render => { :nothing => true, :status => :method_not_allowed }


  		





  
  30
  
    

  		





  
  31
  
    
  def show


  		





  
  32
  
    
    # download is put here to provide more clear and usable links


  		





  
  33
  
    
    if params.has_key?(:download)


  		





  
  34
  
    
      if @file.deleted


  		





  
  35
  
    
        render_404


  		





  
  36
  
    
        return


  		





  
  37
  
    
      end


  		





  
  38
  
    
      if params[:download].blank?


  		





  
  39
  
    
        @revision = @file.last_revision


  		





  
  40
  
    
      else


  		





  
  41
  
    
        @revision = DmsfFileRevision.find(params[:download].to_i)


  		





  
  42
  
    
        if @revision.file != @file


  		





  
  43
  
    
          render_403


  		





  
  44
  
    
          return


  		





  
  45
  
    
        end


  		





  
  46
  
    
        if @revision.deleted


  		





  
  47
  
    
          render_404


  		





  
  48
  
    
          return


  		





  
  49
  
    
        end


  		





  
  50
  
    
      end


  		





  
  51
  
    
      check_project(@revision.file)


  		





  
  52
  
    
      send_revision


  		





  
  53
  
    
      return


  		





  
  54
  
    
    end


  		





  
  55
  
    
    


  		





  
  56
  
    
    @revision = @file.last_revision


  		





  
  57
  
    
    # TODO: line bellow is to handle old instalations with errors in data handling


  		





  
  58
  
    
    @revision.name = @file.name


  		





  
  59
  
    
    


  		





  
  60
  
    
    @revision_pages = Paginator.new self, @file.revisions.count, params["per_page"] ? params["per_page"].to_i : 25, params["page"]


  		





  
  61
  
    
    


  		





  
  62
  
    
    render :layout => !request.xhr?


  		





  
  63
  
    
  end


  		





  
  64
  
    

  		





  
  65
  
    
  #TODO: don't create revision if nothing change


  		





  
  66
  
    
  def create_revision


  		





  
  67
  
    
    unless params[:dmsf_file_revision]


  		





  
  68
  
    
      redirect_to :action => "show", :id => @file


  		





  
  69
  
    
      return


  		





  
  70
  
    
    end


  		





  
  71
  
    
    if @file.locked_for_user?


  		





  
  72
  
    
      flash[:error] = l(:error_file_is_locked)


  		





  
  73
  
    
      redirect_to :action => "show", :id => @file


  		





  
  74
  
    
    else


  		





  
  75
  
    
      #TODO: validate folder_id


  		





  
  76
  
    
      @revision = DmsfFileRevision.new(params[:dmsf_file_revision])


  		





  
  77
  
    
      


  		





  
  78
  
    
      @revision.file = @file


  		





  
  79
  
    
      @revision.project = @file.project


  		





  
  80
  
    
      last_revision = @file.last_revision


  		





  
  81
  
    
      @revision.source_revision = last_revision


  		





  
  82
  
    
      @revision.user = User.current


  		





  
  83
  
    
      


  		





  
  84
  
    
      @revision.major_version = last_revision.major_version


  		





  
  85
  
    
      @revision.minor_version = last_revision.minor_version


  		





  
  86
  
    
      @revision.workflow = last_revision.workflow


  		





  
  87
  
    
      version = params[:version].to_i


  		





  
  88
  
    
      file_upload = params[:file_upload]


  		





  
  89
  
    
      if file_upload.nil?


  		





  
  90
  
    
        @revision.disk_filename = last_revision.disk_filename


  		





  
  91
  
    
        @revision.increase_version(version, false)


  		





  
  92
  
    
        @revision.mime_type = last_revision.mime_type


  		





  
  93
  
    
        @revision.size = last_revision.size


  		





  
  94
  
    
      else


  		





  
  95
  
    
        @revision.increase_version(version, true)


  		





  
  96
  
    
        @revision.size = file_upload.size


  		





  
  97
  
    
        @revision.disk_filename = @revision.new_storage_filename


  		





  
  98
  
    
        @revision.mime_type = Redmine::MimeType.of(file_upload.original_filename)


  		





  
  99
  
    
      end


  		





  
  100
  
    
      @revision.set_workflow(params[:workflow])


  		





  
  101
  
    
      


  		





  
  102
  
    
      @file.name = @revision.name


  		





  
  103
  
    
      @file.folder = @revision.folder


  		





  
  104
  
    
      


  		





  
  105
  
    
      if @revision.valid? && @file.valid?


  		





  
  106
  
    
        @revision.save!


  		





  
  107
  
    
        unless file_upload.nil?


  		





  
  108
  
    
          @revision.copy_file_content(file_upload)


  		





  
  109
  
    
        end


  		





  
  110
  
    
        


  		





  
  111
  
    
        if @file.locked?


  		





  
  112
  
    
          DmsfFileLock.file_lock_state(@file, false)


  		





  
  113
  
    
          flash[:notice] = l(:notice_file_unlocked) + ", "


  		





  
  114
  
    
        end


  		





  
  115
  
    
        @file.save!


  		





  
  116
  
    
        @file.reload


  		





  
  117
  
    
        


  		





  
  118
  
    
        flash[:notice] = (flash[:notice].nil? ? "" : flash[:notice]) + l(:notice_file_revision_created)


  		





  
  119
  
    
        log_activity("new revision")


  		





  
  120
  
    
        begin


  		





  
  121
  
    
          DmsfMailer.deliver_files_updated(User.current, [@file])


  		





  
  122
  
    
        rescue ActionView::MissingTemplate => e


  		





  
  123
  
    
          Rails.logger.error "Could not send email notifications: " + e


  		





  
  124
  
    
        end


  		





  
  125
  
    
        redirect_to :action => "show", :id => @file


  		





  
  126
  
    
      else


  		





  
  127
  
    
        render :action => "show"


  		





  
  128
  
    
      end


  		





  
  129
  
    
    end


  		





  
  130
  
    
  end


  		





  
  131
  
    

  		





  
  132
  
    
  def delete


  		





  
  133
  
    
    if !@file.nil?


  		





  
  134
  
    
      if @file.delete


  		





  
  135
  
    
        flash[:notice] = l(:notice_file_deleted)


  		





  
  136
  
    
        log_activity("deleted")


  		





  
  137
  
    
        DmsfMailer.deliver_files_deleted(User.current, [@file])


  		





  
  138
  
    
      else


  		





  
  139
  
    
        flash[:error] = l(:error_file_is_locked)


  		





  
  140
  
    
      end


  		





  
  141
  
    
    end


  		





  
  142
  
    
    redirect_to :controller => "dmsf", :action => "show", :id => @project, :folder_id => @file.folder


  		





  
  143
  
    
  end


  		





  
  144
  
    

  		





  
  145
  
    
  def delete_revision


  		





  
  146
  
    
    if !@revision.nil? && !@revision.deleted


  		





  
  147
  
    
      if @revision.delete


  		





  
  148
  
    
        flash[:notice] = l(:notice_revision_deleted)


  		





  
  149
  
    
        log_activity("deleted")


  		





  
  150
  
    
      else


  		





  
  151
  
    
        # TODO: check this error handling


  		





  
  152
  
    
        @revision.errors.each {|e| flash[:error] = e[1]}


  		





  
  153
  
    
      end


  		





  
  154
  
    
    end


  		





  
  155
  
    
    redirect_to :action => "show", :id => @file


  		





  
  156
  
    
  end


  		





  
  157
  
    

  		





  
  158
  
    
  def lock


  		





  
  159
  
    
    if @file.locked?


  		





  
  160
  
    
      flash[:warning] = l(:warning_file_already_locked)


  		





  
  161
  
    
    else


  		





  
  162
  
    
      @file.lock


  		





  
  163
  
    
      flash[:notice] = l(:notice_file_locked)


  		





  
  164
  
    
    end


  		





  
  165
  
    
      redirect_to params[:current] ? params[:current] : 


  		





  
  166
  
    
        {:controller => "dmsf", :action => "show", :id => @project, :folder_id => @file.folder}


  		





  
  167
  
    
  end


  		





  
  168
  
    
  


  		





  
  169
  
    
  def unlock


  		





  
  170
  
    
    if !@file.locked?


  		





  
  171
  
    
      flash[:warning] = l(:warning_file_not_locked)


  		





  
  172
  
    
    else


  		





  
  173
  
    
      if @file.locks[0].user == User.current || User.current.allowed_to?(:force_file_unlock, @file.project)


  		





  
  174
  
    
        @file.unlock


  		





  
  175
  
    
        flash[:notice] = l(:notice_file_unlocked)


  		





  
  176
  
    
      else


  		





  
  177
  
    
        flash[:error] = l(:error_only_user_that_locked_file_can_unlock_it)


  		





  
  178
  
    
      end


  		





  
  179
  
    
    end


  		





  
  180
  
    
    redirect_to params[:current] ? params[:current] : 


  		





  
  181
  
    
        {:controller => "dmsf", :action => "show", :id => @project, :folder_id => @file.folder}


  		





  
  182
  
    
  end


  		





  
  183
  
    

  		





  
  184
  
    
  def notify_activate


  		





  
  185
  
    
    if @file.notification


  		





  
  186
  
    
      flash[:warning] = l(:warning_file_notifications_already_activated)


  		





  
  187
  
    
    else


  		





  
  188
  
    
      @file.notify_activate


  		





  
  189
  
    
      flash[:notice] = l(:notice_file_notifications_activated)


  		





  
  190
  
    
    end


  		





  
  191
  
    
    redirect_to params[:current] ? params[:current] :


  		





  
  192
  
    
      {:controller => "dmsf", :action => "show", :id => @project, :folder_id => @file.folder}


  		





  
  193
  
    
  end


  		





  
  194
  
    
  


  		





  
  195
  
    
  def notify_deactivate


  		





  
  196
  
    
    if !@file.notification


  		





  
  197
  
    
      flash[:warning] = l(:warning_file_notifications_already_deactivated)


  		





  
  198
  
    
    else


  		





  
  199
  
    
      @file.notify_deactivate


  		





  
  200
  
    
      flash[:notice] = l(:notice_file_notifications_deactivated)


  		





  
  201
  
    
    end


  		





  
  202
  
    
    redirect_to params[:current] ? params[:current] :


  		





  
  203
  
    
      {:controller => "dmsf", :action => "show", :id => @project, :folder_id => @file.folder}


  		





  
  204
  
    
  end

  208
  
    
  def log_activity(action)


  		





  
  209
  
    
    Rails.logger.info "#{Time.now.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')} #{User.current.login}@#{request.remote_ip}/#{request.env['HTTP_X_FORWARDED_FOR']}: #{action} dmsf://#{@file.project.identifier}/#{@file.id}/#{@revision.id if @revision}"


  		





  
  210
  
    
  end


  		





  
  211
  
    

  		





  
  212
  
    
  def send_revision


  		





  
  213
  
    
    log_activity("downloaded")


  		





  
  214
  
    
    access = DmsfFileRevisionAccess.new(:user_id => User.current.id, :dmsf_file_revision_id => @revision.id, 


  		





  
  215
  
    
      :action => DmsfFileRevisionAccess::DownloadAction)


  		





  
  216
  
    
    access.save!


  		





  
  217
  
    
    send_file(@revision.disk_file, 


  		





  
  218
  
    
      :filename => filename_for_content_disposition(@revision.name),


  		





  
  219
  
    
      :type => @revision.detect_content_type, 


  		





  
  220
  
    
      :disposition => "attachment")


  		





  
  221
  
    
  end


  		





  
  222
  
    
  


  		





  
  223
  
    
  def find_file


  		





  
  224
  
    
    @file = DmsfFile.find(params[:id])


  		





  
  225
  
    
    @project = @file.project


  		





  
  226
  
    
  rescue


  		





  
  227
  
    
  end


  		





  
  228
  
    

  		





  
  229
  
    
  def find_revision


  		





  
  230
  
    
    @revision = DmsfFileRevision.find(params[:id])


  		





  
  231
  
    
    @file = @revision.file 


  		





  
  232
  
    
    @project = @file.project


  		





  
  233
  
    
  end


  		





  
  234
  
    

  		





  
  235
  
    
  def check_project(entry)


  		





  
  236
  
    
    if !entry.nil? && entry.project != @project


  		





  
  237
  
    
      raise DmsfAccessError, l(:error_entry_project_does_not_match_current_project) 


  		





  
  238
  
    
    end


  		





  
  239
  
    
  end

end

class DmsfFilesCopyController < ApplicationController


  		





  
  20
  
    
  unloadable


  		





  
  21
  
    
  


  		





  
  22
  
    
  menu_item :dmsf


  		





  
  23
  
    
  


  		





  
  24
  
    
  before_filter :find_file


  		





  
  25
  
    
  before_filter :authorize


  		





  
  26
  
    

  		





  
  27
  
    
  verify :method => :post, :only => [:create, :move], :render => { :nothing => true, :status => :method_not_allowed }


  		





  
  28
  
    

  		





  
  29
  
    
  def new


  		





  
  30
  
    
    @target_project = DmsfFile.allowed_target_projects_on_copy.detect {|p| p.id.to_s == params[:target_project_id]} if params[:target_project_id]


  		





  
  31
  
    
    @target_project ||= @project if User.current.allowed_to?(:file_manipulation, @project)


  		





  
  32
  
    
    if DmsfFile.allowed_target_projects_on_copy.blank?


  		





  
  33
  
    
      flash.now[:warning] = l(:warning_no_project_to_copy_file_to)


  		





  
  34
  
    
    else


  		





  
  35
  
    
      @target_project ||= DmsfFile.allowed_target_projects_on_copy[0]


  		





  
  36
  
    
    end


  		





  
  37
  
    
    


  		





  
  38
  
    
    @target_folder = DmsfFolder.find(params[:target_folder_id]) unless params[:target_folder_id].blank?


  		





  
  39
  
    
    @target_folder ||= @file.folder if @target_project == @project


  		





  
  40
  
    
    


  		





  
  41
  
    
    render :layout => !request.xhr?


  		





  
  42
  
    
  end


  		





  
  43
  
    

  		





  
  44
  
    
  def create


  		





  
  45
  
    
    @target_project = DmsfFile.allowed_target_projects_on_copy.detect {|p| p.id.to_s == params[:target_project_id]} if params[:target_project_id]


  		





  
  46
  
    
    unless @target_project


  		





  
  47
  
    
      render_403


  		





  
  48
  
    
      return


  		





  
  49
  
    
    end


  		





  
  50
  
    
    @target_folder = DmsfFolder.find(params[:target_folder_id]) unless params[:target_folder_id].blank?


  		





  
  51
  
    
    if !@target_folder.nil? && @target_folder.project != @target_project


  		





  
  52
  
    
      raise DmsfAccessError, l(:error_entry_project_does_not_match_current_project) 


  		





  
  53
  
    
    end


  		





  
  54
  
    

  		





  
  55
  
    
    if (!@target_folder.nil? && @target_folder == @file.folder) || 


  		





  
  56
  
    
        (@target_folder.nil? && @file.folder.nil? && @target_project == @file.project)


  		





  
  57
  
    
      flash[:error] = l(:error_target_folder_same)


  		





  
  58
  
    
      redirect_to :action => "new", :id => @file, :target_project_id => @target_project, :target_folder_id => @target_folder


  		





  
  59
  
    
      return


  		





  
  60
  
    
    end


  		





  
  61
  
    

  		





  
  62
  
    
    new_file = @file.copy_to(@target_project, @target_folder)


  		





  
  63
  
    
    


  		





  
  64
  
    
    unless new_file.errors.empty?


  		





  
  65
  
    
      flash[:error] = "#{l(:error_file_cannot_be_copied)}: #{new_file.errors.full_messages.join(", ")}"


  		





  
  66
  
    
      redirect_to :action => "new", :id => @file, :target_project_id => @target_project, :target_folder_id => @target_folder


  		





  
  67
  
    
      return


  		





  
  68
  
    
    end


  		





  
  69
  
    

  		





  
  70
  
    
    flash[:notice] = l(:notice_file_copied)


  		





  
  71
  
    
    log_activity(new_file, "was copied (is copy)")


  		





  
  72
  
    
    begin 


  		





  
  73
  
    
      DmsfMailer.deliver_files_updated(User.current, [new_file])


  		





  
  74
  
    
    rescue ActionView::MissingTemplate => e


  		





  
  75
  
    
      Rails.logger.error "Could not send email notifications: " + e


  		





  
  76
  
    
    end


  		





  
  77
  
    
    


  		





  
  78
  
    
    redirect_to :controller => "dmsf_files", :action => "show", :id => new_file


  		





  
  79
  
    
  end


  		





  
  80
  
    

  		





  
  81
  
    
  def move


  		





  
  82
  
    
    @target_project = DmsfFile.allowed_target_projects_on_copy.detect {|p| p.id.to_s == params[:target_project_id]} if params[:target_project_id]


  		





  
  83
  
    
    unless @target_project && User.current.allowed_to?(:file_manipulation, @target_project) && User.current.allowed_to?(:file_manipulation, @project)


  		





  
  84
  
    
      render_403


  		





  
  85
  
    
      return


  		





  
  86
  
    
    end


  		





  
  87
  
    
    @target_folder = DmsfFolder.find(params[:target_folder_id]) unless params[:target_folder_id].blank?


  		





  
  88
  
    
    if !@target_folder.nil? && @target_folder.project != @target_project


  		





  
  89
  
    
      raise DmsfAccessError, l(:error_entry_project_does_not_match_current_project) 


  		





  
  90
  
    
    end


  		





  
  91
  
    

  		





  
  92
  
    
    if (!@target_folder.nil? && @target_folder == @file.folder) || 


  		





  
  93
  
    
        (@target_folder.nil? && @file.folder.nil? && @target_project == @file.project)


  		





  
  94
  
    
      flash[:error] = l(:error_target_folder_same)


  		





  
  95
  
    
      redirect_to :action => "new", :id => @file, :target_project_id => @target_project, :target_folder_id => @target_folder


  		





  
  96
  
    
      return


  		





  
  97
  
    
    end


  		





  
  98
  
    

  		





  
  99
  
    
    unless @file.move_to(@target_project, @target_folder)


  		





  
  100
  
    
      flash[:error] = "#{l(:error_file_cannot_be_moved)}: #{@file.errors.full_messages.join(", ")}"


  		





  
  101
  
    
      redirect_to :action => "new", :id => @file, :target_project_id => @target_project, :target_folder_id => @target_folder


  		





  
  102
  
    
      return


  		





  
  103
  
    
    end


  		





  
  104
  
    

  		





  
  105
  
    
    @file.reload


  		





  
  106
  
    
    


  		





  
  107
  
    
    flash[:notice] = l(:notice_file_moved)


  		





  
  108
  
    
    log_activity(@file, "was moved (is copy)")


  		





  
  109
  
    
    begin


  		





  
  110
  
    
      # TODO: implement proper mail notification


  		





  
  111
  
    
      DmsfMailer.deliver_files_updated(User.current, [@file])


  		





  
  112
  
    
    rescue ActionView::MissingTemplate => e


  		





  
  113
  
    
      Rails.logger.error "Could not send email notifications: " + e


  		





  
  114
  
    
    end


  		





  
  115
  
    
    


  		





  
  116
  
    
    redirect_to :controller => "dmsf_files", :action => "show", :id => @file


  		





  
  117
  
    
  end


  		





  
  118
  
    

  		





  
  119
  
    
  private


  		





  
  120
  
    

  		





  
  121
  
    
  def log_activity(file, action)


  		





  
  122
  
    
    Rails.logger.info "#{Time.now.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')} #{User.current.login}@#{request.remote_ip}/#{request.env['HTTP_X_FORWARDED_FOR']}: #{action} dmsf://#{file.project.identifier}/#{file.id}/#{file.last_revision.id}"


  		





  
  123
  
    
  end


  		





  
  124
  
    

  		





  
  125
  
    
  def find_file


  		





  
  126
  
    
    @file = DmsfFile.find(params[:id])


  		





  
  127
  
    
    @project = @file.project


  		





  
  128
  
    
  end


  		





  
  129
  
    
  


  		





  
  130
  
    
end

  def new


  		





  
  30
  
    
    @target_project = DmsfFolder.allowed_target_projects_on_copy.detect {|p| p.id.to_s == params[:target_project_id]} if params[:target_project_id]

    @target_project ||= @project if User.current.allowed_to?(:folder_manipulation, @project)

    if DmsfFile.allowed_target_projects_on_copy.blank?

      flash.now[:warning] = l(:warning_no_project_to_copy_folder_to)

      @target_project ||= DmsfFolder.allowed_target_projects_on_copy[0]

    @target_folder = DmsfFolder.find(params[:target_folder_id]) unless params[:target_folder_id].blank?

    @target_folder ||= @folder.folder if @target_project == @project

  def copy_to


  		





  
  45
  
    
    @target_project = DmsfFile.allowed_target_projects_on_copy.detect {|p| p.id.to_s == params[:target_project_id]} if params[:target_project_id]


  		





  
  46
  
    
    unless @target_project


  		





  
  47
  
    
      render_403


  		





  
  48
  
    
      return


  		





  
  49
  
    
    end


  		





  
  50
  
    
    @target_folder = DmsfFolder.find(params[:target_folder_id]) unless params[:target_folder_id].blank?


  		





  
  51
  
    
    if !@target_folder.nil? && @target_folder.project != @target_project


  		





  
  52
  
    
      raise DmsfAccessError, l(:error_entry_project_does_not_match_current_project) 


  		





  
  53
  
    
    end


  		





  
  54
  
    

  		





  
  55
  
    
    if (!@target_folder.nil? && @target_folder == @folder.folder) || 


  		





  
  56
  
    
        (@target_folder.nil? && @folder.folder.nil? && @target_project == @folder.project)


  		





  
  57
  
    
      flash[:error] = l(:error_target_folder_same)


  		





  
  58
  
    
      redirect_to :action => "new", :id => @folder, :target_project_id => @target_project, :target_folder_id => @target_folder


  		





  
  59
  
    
      return


  		





  
  60
  
    
    end


  		





  
  61
  
    

  		





  
  62
  
    
    new_folder = @folder.copy_to(@target_project, @target_folder)


  		





  
  63
  
    
    


  		





  
  64
  
    
    unless new_folder.errors.empty?


  		





  
  65
  
    
      flash[:error] = "#{l(:error_folder_cannot_be_copied)}: #{new_folder.errors.full_messages.join(", ")}"


  		





  
  66
  
    
      redirect_to :action => "new", :id => @folder, :target_project_id => @target_project, :target_folder_id => @target_folder


  		





  
  67
  
    
      return


  		





  
  68
  
    
    end


  		





  
  69
  
    

  		





  
  70
  
    
    new_folder.reload


  		





  
  71
  
    
    


  		





  
  72
  
    
    flash[:notice] = l(:notice_folder_copied)


  		





  
  73
  
    
    log_activity(new_folder, "was copied (is copy)")


  		





  
  74
  
    
    


  		





  
  75
  
    
    #TODO: implement proper notification for all new files


  		





  
  76
  
    
    #begin 


  		





  
  77
  
    
    #  DmsfMailer.deliver_files_updated(User.current, [new_file])


  		





  
  78
  
    
    #rescue ActionView::MissingTemplate => e


  		





  
  79
  
    
    #  Rails.logger.error "Could not send email notifications: " + e


  		





  
  80
  
    
    #end


  		





  
  81
  
    
    


  		





  
  82
  
    
    redirect_to :controller => "dmsf", :action => "show", :id => @target_project, :folder_id => new_folder


  		





  
  83
  
    
  end

  87
  
    
  def log_activity(folder, action)


  		





  
  88
  
    
    Rails.logger.info "#{Time.now.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')} #{User.current.login}@#{request.remote_ip}/#{request.env['HTTP_X_FORWARDED_FOR']}: #{action} dmsf://#{folder.project.identifier}/#{folder.id}"


  		





  
  89
  
    
  end


  		





  
  90
  
    

  		





  
  91
  
    
  def find_folder


  		





  
  92
  
    
    @folder = DmsfFolder.find(params[:id])


  		





  
  93
  
    
    @project = @folder.project


  		





  
  94
  
    
  end


  		





  
  95
  
    
  


  		





  
  96
  
    
end

class DmsfStateController < ApplicationController

  unloadable

  26

  verify :method => :post, :only => [:user_pref_save], :render => { :nothing => true, :status => :method_not_allowed }

  29
  
    
  def user_pref_save


  		





  
  30
  
    
    member = @project.members.find(:first, :conditions => {:user_id => User.current.id})


  		





  
  31
  
    
    if member


  		





  
  32
  
    
      member.dmsf_mail_notification = params[:email_notify];


  		





  
  33
  
    
      member.save!


  		





  
  34
  
    
      flash[:notice] = l(:notice_your_preferences_were_saved)  


  		





  
  35
  
    
    else


  		





  
  36
  
    
      flash[:warning] = l(:user_is_not_project_member)


  		





  
  37
  
    
    end


  		





  
  38
  
    
    redirect_to :controller => "projects", :action => 'settings', :tab => 'dmsf', :id => @project


  		





  
  39
  
    
  end

  end

  def check_project(entry)


  		





  
  48
  
    
    if !entry.nil? && entry.project != @project


  		





  
  49
  
    
      raise DmsfAccessError, l(:error_entry_project_does_not_match_current_project) 


  		





  
  50
  
    
    end


  		





  
  51
  
    
  end

      b/vendor/plugins/redmine_dmsf/app/controllers/dmsf_upload_controller.rb

class DmsfUploadController < ApplicationController


  		





  
  20
  
    
  unloadable


  		





  
  21
  
    
  


  		





  
  22
  
    
  menu_item :dmsf


  		





  
  23
  
    
  


  		





  
  24
  
    
  before_filter :find_project


  		





  
  25
  
    
  before_filter :authorize


  		





  
  26
  
    
  before_filter :find_folder, :except => [:upload_file]


  		





  
  27
  
    
  


  		





  
  28
  
    
  verify :method => :post, :only => [:upload_files, :upload_file, :commit_files], 


  		





  
  29
  
    
    :render => { :nothing => true, :status => :method_not_allowed }


  		





  
  30
  
    
  


  		





  
  31
  
    
  def upload_files


  		





  
  32
  
    
    uploaded_files = params[:uploaded_files]


  		





  
  33
  
    
    @uploads = []


  		





  
  34
  
    
    if uploaded_files && uploaded_files.is_a?(Hash)


  		





  
  35
  
    
      # standard file input uploads


  		





  
  36
  
    
      uploaded_files.each_value do |uploaded_file|


  		





  
  37
  
    
        @uploads.push(DmsfUpload.create_from_uploaded_file(@project, @folder, uploaded_file))


  		





  
  38
  
    
      end


  		





  
  39
  
    
    else


  		





  
  40
  
    
      # plupload multi upload completed


  		





  
  41
  
    
      uploaded = params[:uploaded]


  		





  
  42
  
    
      if uploaded && uploaded.is_a?(Hash)


  		





  
  43
  
    
        uploaded.each_value do |uploaded_file|


  		





  
  44
  
    
          @uploads.push(DmsfUpload.new(@project, @folder, uploaded_file))


  		





  
  45
  
    
        end


  		





  
  46
  
    
      end


  		





  
  47
  
    
    end


  		





  
  48
  
    
  end


  		





  
  49
  
    

  		





  
  50
  
    
  # async single file upload handling 


  		





  
  51
  
    
  def upload_file


  		





  
  52
  
    
    @tempfile = params[:file]


  		





  
  53
  
    
    unless @tempfile.original_filename


  		





  
  54
  
    
      render_404


  		





  
  55
  
    
      return


  		





  
  56
  
    
    end


  		





  
  57
  
    
    @disk_filename = DmsfHelper.temp_filename(@tempfile.original_filename)


  		





  
  58
  
    
    File.open("#{DmsfHelper.temp_dir}/#{@disk_filename}", "wb") do |f| 


  		





  
  59
  
    
      while (buffer = @tempfile.read(8192))


  		





  
  60
  
    
        f.write(buffer)


  		





  
  61
  
    
      end


  		





  
  62
  
    
    end


  		





  
  63
  
    
    


  		





  
  64
  
    
    render :layout => false


  		





  
  65
  
    
  end


  		





  
  66
  
    

  		





  
  67
  
    
  #TODO: flash notice when files saved and unlocked


  		





  
  68
  
    
  #TODO: separate control for approval


  		





  
  69
  
    
  def commit_files


  		





  
  70
  
    
    commited_files = params[:commited_files]


  		





  
  71
  
    
    if commited_files && commited_files.is_a?(Hash)


  		





  
  72
  
    
      files = []


  		





  
  73
  
    
      failed_uploads = []


  		





  
  74
  
    
      commited_files.each_value do |commited_file|


  		





  
  75
  
    
        name = commited_file["name"];


  		





  
  76
  
    
        


  		





  
  77
  
    
        new_revision = DmsfFileRevision.new


  		





  
  78
  
    
        file = DmsfFile.find_file_by_name(@project, @folder, name)


  		





  
  79
  
    
        if file.nil?


  		





  
  80
  
    
          file = DmsfFile.new


  		





  
  81
  
    
          file.project = @project


  		





  
  82
  
    
          file.name = name


  		





  
  83
  
    
          file.folder = @folder


  		





  
  84
  
    
          file.notification = !Setting.plugin_redmine_dmsf["dmsf_default_notifications"].blank?


  		





  
  85
  
    
          


  		





  
  86
  
    
          new_revision.minor_version = 0


  		





  
  87
  
    
          new_revision.major_version = 0


  		





  
  88
  
    
        else


  		





  
  89
  
    
          if file.locked_for_user?


  		





  
  90
  
    
            failed_uploads.push(commited_file)


  		





  
  91
  
    
            next


  		





  
  92
  
    
          end


  		





  
  93
  
    
          last_revision = file.last_revision


  		





  
  94
  
    
          new_revision.source_revision = last_revision


  		





  
  95
  
    
          new_revision.major_version = last_revision.major_version


  		





  
  96
  
    
          new_revision.minor_version = last_revision.minor_version


  		





  
  97
  
    
          new_revision.workflow = last_revision.workflow


  		





  
  98
  
    
        end


  		





  
  99
  
    

  		





  
  100
  
    
        commited_disk_filepath = "#{DmsfHelper.temp_dir}/#{commited_file["disk_filename"].gsub(/[\/\\]/,'')}"


  		





  
  101
  
    
        


  		





  
  102
  
    
        new_revision.project = @project


  		





  
  103
  
    
        new_revision.folder = @folder


  		





  
  104
  
    
        new_revision.file = file


  		





  
  105
  
    
        new_revision.user = User.current


  		





  
  106
  
    
        new_revision.name = name


  		





  
  107
  
    
        new_revision.title = commited_file["title"]


  		





  
  108
  
    
        new_revision.description = commited_file["description"]


  		





  
  109
  
    
        new_revision.comment = commited_file["comment"]


  		





  
  110
  
    
        new_revision.increase_version(commited_file["version"].to_i, true)


  		





  
  111
  
    
        new_revision.set_workflow(commited_file["workflow"])


  		





  
  112
  
    
        new_revision.mime_type = Redmine::MimeType.of(new_revision.name)


  		





  
  113
  
    
        new_revision.size = File.size(commited_disk_filepath)


  		





  
  114
  
    

  		





  
  115
  
    
        file_upload = File.new(commited_disk_filepath, "rb")


  		





  
  116
  
    
        if file_upload.nil?


  		





  
  117
  
    
          failed_uploads.push(commited_file)


  		





  
  118
  
    
          flash[:error] = l(:error_file_commit_require_uploaded_file)


  		





  
  119
  
    
          next


  		





  
  120
  
    
        end


  		





  
  121
  
    
        


  		





  
  122
  
    
        if file.locked?


  		





  
  123
  
    
          DmsfFileLock.file_lock_state(file, false)


  		





  
  124
  
    
          flash[:notice] = l(:notice_file_unlocked)


  		





  
  125
  
    
        end


  		





  
  126
  
    
        


  		





  
  127
  
    
        # Need to save file first to generate id for it in case of creation. 


  		





  
  128
  
    
        # File id is needed to properly generate revision disk filename


  		





  
  129
  
    
        if new_revision.valid? && file.save


  		





  
  130
  
    
          new_revision.disk_filename = new_revision.new_storage_filename


  		





  
  131
  
    
        else


  		





  
  132
  
    
          failed_uploads.push(commited_file)


  		





  
  133
  
    
          next


  		





  
  134
  
    
        end


  		





  
  135
  
    
        


  		





  
  136
  
    
        if new_revision.save


  		





  
  137
  
    
          file.reload


  		





  
  138
  
    
          


  		





  
  139
  
    
          new_revision.copy_file_content(file_upload)


  		





  
  140
  
    
          file_upload.close


  		





  
  141
  
    
          File.delete(commited_disk_filepath)


  		





  
  142
  
    
          


  		





  
  143
  
    
          files.push(file)


  		





  
  144
  
    
        else


  		





  
  145
  
    
          failed_uploads.push(commited_file)


  		





  
  146
  
    
        end


  		





  
  147
  
    
      end


  		





  
  148
  
    
      unless files.empty?


  		





  
  149
  
    
        files.each {|file| log_activity(file, "uploaded")}


  		





  
  150
  
    
        begin 


  		





  
  151
  
    
          DmsfMailer.deliver_files_updated(User.current, files)


  		





  
  152
  
    
        rescue ActionView::MissingTemplate => e


  		





  
  153
  
    
          Rails.logger.error "Could not send email notifications: " + e


  		





  
  154
  
    
        end


  		





  
  155
  
    
      end


  		





  
  156
  
    
      unless failed_uploads.empty?


  		





  
  157
  
    
        flash[:warning] = l(:warning_some_files_were_not_commited, :files => failed_uploads.map{|u| u["name"]}.join(", "))


  		





  
  158
  
    
      end


  		





  
  159
  
    
    end


  		





  
  160
  
    
    redirect_to :controller => "dmsf", :action => "show", :id => @project, :folder_id => @folder


  		





  
  161
  
    
  end


  		





  
  162
  
    

  		





  
  163
  
    
  private


  		





  
  164
  
    
  


  		





  
  165
  
    
  def log_activity(file, action)


  		





  
  166
  
    
    Rails.logger.info "#{Time.now.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')} #{User.current.login}@#{request.remote_ip}/#{request.env['HTTP_X_FORWARDED_FOR']}: #{action} dmsf://#{file.project.identifier}/#{file.id}/#{file.last_revision.id}"


  		





  
  167
  
    
  end


  		





  
  168
  
    
  


  		





  
  169
  
    
  def find_project


  		





  
  170
  
    
    @project = Project.find(params[:id])


  		





  
  171
  
    
  end


  		





  
  172
  
    
  


  		





  
  173
  
    
  def find_folder


  		





  
  174
  
    
    @folder = DmsfFolder.find(params[:folder_id]) if params.keys.include?("folder_id")


  		





  
  175
  
    
    check_project(@folder)


  		





  
  176
  
    
  rescue DmsfAccessError


  		





  
  177
  
    
    render_403


  		





  
  178
  
    
  end


  		





  
  179
  
    

  		





  
  180
  
    
  def check_project(entry)


  		





  
  181
  
    
    if !entry.nil? && entry.project != @project


  		





  
  182
  
    
      raise DmsfAccessError, l(:error_entry_project_does_not_match_current_project) 


  		





  
  183
  
    
    end


  		





  
  184
  
    
  end


  		





  
  185
  
    
  


  		





  
  186
  
    
end

require "tmpdir"


  		





  
  20
  
    
require "digest/md5"


  		





  
  21
  
    

  		





  
  22
  
    
module DmsfHelper


  		





  
  23
  
    

  		





  
  24
  
    
  def self.temp_dir


  		





  
  25
  
    
    Dir.tmpdir


  		





  
  26
  
    
  end


  		





  
  27
  
    

  		





  
  28
  
    
  def self.temp_filename(filename)


  		





  
  29
  
    
    filename = sanitize_filename(filename)


  		





  
  30
  
    
    timestamp = DateTime.now.strftime("%y%m%d%H%M%S")


  		





  
  31
  
    
    while File.exist?(File.join(temp_dir, "#{timestamp}_#{filename}"))


  		





  
  32
  
    
      timestamp.succ!


  		





  
  33
  
    
    end


  		





  
  34
  
    
    "#{timestamp}_#{filename}"


  		





  
  35
  
    
  end


  		





  
  36
  
    
  


  		





  
  37
  
    
  def self.sanitize_filename(filename)


  		





  
  38
  
    
    # get only the filename, not the whole path


  		





  
  39
  
    
    just_filename = File.basename(filename.gsub('\\\\', '/'))


  		





  
  40
  
    

  		





  
  41
  
    
    # replace all non alphanumeric, hyphens or periods with underscore


  		





  
  42
  
    
    just_filename = just_filename.gsub(/[^\w\.\-]/,'_')


  		





  
  43
  
    

  		





  
  44
  
    
    unless just_filename =~ %r{^[a-zA-Z0-9_\.\-]*$}


  		





  
  45
  
    
      # keep the extension if any


  		





  
  46
  
    
      extension = $1 if just_filename =~ %r{(\.[a-zA-Z0-9]+)$}


  		





  
  47
  
    
      just_filename = Digest::MD5.hexdigest(just_filename) << extension


  		





  
  48
  
    
    end


  		





  
  49
  
    
    


  		





  
  50
  
    
    just_filename


  		





  
  51
  
    
  end


  		





  
  52
  
    
  


  		





  
  53
  
    
  def self.filetype_css(filename)


  		





  
  54
  
    
    extension = File.extname(filename)


  		





  
  55
  
    
    extension = extension[1, extension.length-1]


  		





  
  56
  
    
    if File.exists?("#{File.dirname(__FILE__)}/../../assets/images/filetypes/#{extension}.png")


  		





  
  57
  
    
      return "filetype-#{extension}";


  		





  
  58
  
    
    else


  		





  
  59
  
    
      return Redmine::MimeType.css_class_of(filename)


  		





  
  60
  
    
    end


  		





  
  61
  
    
  end


  		





  
  62
  
    
  


  		





  
  63
  
    
end


  		












  

    
      b/vendor/plugins/redmine_dmsf/app/models/dmsf_file.rb

  27
  
    
class DmsfFile < ActiveRecord::Base


  		





  
  28
  
    
  unloadable


  		





  
  29
  
    
  belongs_to :project


  		





  
  30
  
    
  belongs_to :folder, :class_name => "DmsfFolder", :foreign_key => "dmsf_folder_id"


  		





  
  31
  
    
  has_many :revisions, :class_name => "DmsfFileRevision", :foreign_key => "dmsf_file_id", 


  		





  
  32
  
    
    :order => "major_version DESC, minor_version DESC, updated_at DESC", 


  		





  
  33
  
    
    :conditions => { :deleted => false }


  		





  
  34
  
    
  has_many :locks, :class_name => "DmsfFileLock", :foreign_key => "dmsf_file_id", 


  		





  
  35
  
    
    :order => "updated_at DESC"


  		





  
  36
  
    
  belongs_to :deleted_by_user, :class_name => "User", :foreign_key => "deleted_by_user_id"


  		





  
  37
  
    
  


  		





  
  38
  
    
  validates_presence_of :name


  		





  
  39
  
    
  validates_format_of :name, :with => DmsfFolder.invalid_characters,


  		





  
  40
  
    
    :message => l(:error_contains_invalid_character)


  		





  
  41
  
    
  


  		





  
  42
  
    
  validate :validates_name_uniqueness 


  		





  
  43
  
    
  


  		





  
  44
  
    
  def validates_name_uniqueness


  		





  
  45
  
    
    existing_file = DmsfFile.find_file_by_name(self.project, self.folder, self.name)


  		





  
  46
  
    
    errors.add(:name, l("activerecord.errors.messages.taken")) unless


  		





  
  47
  
    
      existing_file.nil? || existing_file.id == self.id


  		





  
  48
  
    
  end


  		





  
  49
  
    
  


  		





  
  50
  
    
  acts_as_event :title => Proc.new {|o| "#{o.title} - #{o.name}"},


  		





  
  51
  
    
                :description => Proc.new {|o| o.description },


  		





  
  52
  
    
                :url => Proc.new {|o| {:controller => "dmsf_files", :action => "show", :id => o, :download => ""}},


  		





  
  53
  
    
                :datetime => Proc.new {|o| o.updated_at },


  		





  
  54
  
    
                :author => Proc.new {|o| o.last_revision.user }

  def self.storage_path


  		





  
  58
  
    
    storage_dir = Setting.plugin_redmine_dmsf["dmsf_storage_directory"].strip


  		





  
  59
  
    
    if !File.exists?(storage_dir)


  		





  
  60
  
    
      Dir.mkdir(storage_dir)


  		





  
  61
  
    
    end


  		





  
  62
  
    
    storage_dir


  		





  
  63
  
    
  end
