  65
  
    
  def self.project_root_files(project)


  		





  
  66
  
    
    find(:all, :conditions => 


  		





  
  67
  
    
      ["dmsf_folder_id is NULL and project_id = :project_id and deleted = :deleted",


  		





  
  68
  
    
        {:project_id => project.id, :deleted => false}], :order => "name ASC")


  		





  
  69
  
    
  end


  		





  
  70
  
    
  


  		





  
  71
  
    
  def self.find_file_by_name(project, folder, name)


  		





  
  72
  
    
    if folder.nil?


  		





  
  73
  
    
      find(:first, :conditions => 


  		





  
  74
  
    
        ["dmsf_folder_id is NULL and project_id = :project_id and name = :name and deleted = :deleted", 


  		





  
  75
  
    
          {:project_id => project.id, :name => name, :deleted => false}])


  		





  
  76
  
    
    else


  		





  
  77
  
    
      find(:first, :conditions => 


  		





  
  78
  
    
        ["dmsf_folder_id = :folder_id and project_id = :project_id and name = :name and deleted = :deleted", 


  		





  
  79
  
    
          {:project_id => project.id, :folder_id => folder.id, :name => name, :deleted => false}])


  		





  
  80
  
    
    end


  		





  
  81
  
    
  end


  		





  
  82
  
    

  		





  
  83
  
    
  def last_revision


  		





  
  84
  
    
    self.revisions.first


  		





  
  85
  
    
  end


  		





  
  86
  
    

  		





  
  87
  
    
  def delete


  		





  
  88
  
    
    if locked_for_user?


  		





  
  89
  
    
      errors.add_to_base(l(:error_file_is_locked))


  		





  
  90
  
    
      return false 


  		





  
  91
  
    
    end


  		





  
  92
  
    
    if Setting.plugin_redmine_dmsf["dmsf_really_delete_files"]


  		





  
  93
  
    
      self.revisions.each {|r| r.delete(true)}


  		





  
  94
  
    
      self.destroy


  		





  
  95
  
    
    else


  		





  
  96
  
    
      self.deleted = true


  		





  
  97
  
    
      self.deleted_by_user = User.current


  		





  
  98
  
    
      save


  		





  
  99
  
    
    end


  		





  
  100
  
    
  end


  		





  
  101
  
    
  


  		





  
  102
  
    
  def locked?


  		





  
  103
  
    
    self.locks.empty? ? false : self.locks[0].locked


  		





  
  104
  
    
  end


  		





  
  105
  
    
  


  		





  
  106
  
    
  def locked_for_user?


  		





  
  107
  
    
    self.locked? && self.locks[0].user != User.current


  		





  
  108
  
    
  end


  		





  
  109
  
    
  


  		





  
  110
  
    
  def lock


  		





  
  111
  
    
    l = DmsfFileLock.file_lock_state(self, true)


  		





  
  112
  
    
    self.reload


  		





  
  113
  
    
    return l


  		





  
  114
  
    
  end


  		





  
  115
  
    
  


  		





  
  116
  
    
  def unlock


  		





  
  117
  
    
    l = DmsfFileLock.file_lock_state(self, false)


  		





  
  118
  
    
    self.reload


  		





  
  119
  
    
    return l


  		





  
  120
  
    
  end


  		





  
  121
  
    
  


  		





  
  122
  
    
  def title


  		





  
  123
  
    
    self.last_revision.title


  		





  
  124
  
    
  end


  		





  
  125
  
    
  


  		





  
  126
  
    
  def description


  		





  
  127
  
    
    self.last_revision.description


  		





  
  128
  
    
  end


  		





  
  129
  
    
  


  		





  
  130
  
    
  def version


  		





  
  131
  
    
    self.last_revision.version


  		





  
  132
  
    
  end


  		





  
  133
  
    
  


  		





  
  134
  
    
  def workflow


  		





  
  135
  
    
    self.last_revision.workflow


  		





  
  136
  
    
  end


  		





  
  137
  
    
  


  		





  
  138
  
    
  def size


  		





  
  139
  
    
    self.last_revision.size


  		





  
  140
  
    
  end


  		





  
  141
  
    
  


  		





  
  142
  
    
  def dmsf_path


  		





  
  143
  
    
    path = self.folder.nil? ? [] : self.folder.dmsf_path


  		





  
  144
  
    
    path.push(self)


  		





  
  145
  
    
    path


  		





  
  146
  
    
  end


  		





  
  147
  
    
  


  		





  
  148
  
    
  def dmsf_path_str


  		





  
  149
  
    
    path = self.dmsf_path


  		





  
  150
  
    
    string_path = path.map { |element| element.title }


  		





  
  151
  
    
    string_path.join("/")


  		





  
  152
  
    
  end


  		





  
  153
  
    
  


  		





  
  154
  
    
  def notify?


  		





  
  155
  
    
    return true if self.notification


  		





  
  156
  
    
    return true if folder && folder.notify?


  		





  
  157
  
    
    return false


  		





  
  158
  
    
  end


  		





  
  159
  
    
  


  		





  
  160
  
    
  def notify_deactivate


  		





  
  161
  
    
    self.notification = false


  		





  
  162
  
    
    self.save!


  		





  
  163
  
    
  end


  		





  
  164
  
    
  


  		





  
  165
  
    
  def notify_activate


  		





  
  166
  
    
    self.notification = true


  		





  
  167
  
    
    self.save!


  		





  
  168
  
    
  end


  		





  
  169
  
    
  


  		





  
  170
  
    
  def display_name


  		





  
  171
  
    
    #if self.name.length > 33


  		





  
  172
  
    
    #  extension = File.extname(self.name)


  		





  
  173
  
    
    #  return self.name[0, self.name.length - extension.length][0, 25] + "..." + extension


  		





  
  174
  
    
    #else 


  		





  
  175
  
    
      return self.name


  		





  
  176
  
    
    #end


  		





  
  177
  
    
  end


  		





  
  178
  
    
  


  		





  
  179
  
    
  # Returns an array of projects that current user can copy file to


  		





  
  180
  
    
  def self.allowed_target_projects_on_copy


  		





  
  181
  
    
    projects = []


  		





  
  182
  
    
    if User.current.admin?


  		





  
  183
  
    
      projects = Project.visible.all


  		





  
  184
  
    
    elsif User.current.logged?


  		





  
  185
  
    
      User.current.memberships.each {|m| projects << m.project if m.roles.detect {|r| r.allowed_to?(:file_manipulation)}}


  		





  
  186
  
    
    end


  		





  
  187
  
    
    projects


  		





  
  188
  
    
  end


  		





  
  189
  
    
  


  		





  
  190
  
    
  def move_to(project, folder)


  		





  
  191
  
    
    if self.locked_for_user?


  		





  
  192
  
    
      errors.add_to_base(l(:error_file_is_locked))


  		





  
  193
  
    
      return false 


  		





  
  194
  
    
    end


  		





  
  195
  
    
    


  		





  
  196
  
    
    new_revision = self.last_revision.clone


  		





  
  197
  
    
    


  		





  
  198
  
    
    new_revision.folder = folder ? folder : nil


  		





  
  199
  
    
    new_revision.project = folder ? folder.project : project


  		





  
  200
  
    
    new_revision.comment = l(:comment_moved_from, :source => "#{self.project.identifier}:#{self.dmsf_path_str}") 


  		





  
  201
  
    

  		





  
  202
  
    
    self.folder = new_revision.folder


  		





  
  203
  
    
    self.project = new_revision.project


  		





  
  204
  
    

  		





  
  205
  
    
    return self.save && new_revision.save


  		





  
  206
  
    
  end


  		





  
  207
  
    
  


  		





  
  208
  
    
  def copy_to(project, folder)


  		





  
  209
  
    
    file = DmsfFile.new


  		





  
  210
  
    
    file.folder = folder ? folder : nil


  		





  
  211
  
    
    file.project = folder ? folder.project : project


  		





  
  212
  
    
    file.name = self.name


  		





  
  213
  
    
    file.notification = !Setting.plugin_redmine_dmsf["dmsf_default_notifications"].blank?


  		





  
  214
  
    

  		





  
  215
  
    
    new_revision = self.last_revision.clone


  		





  
  216
  
    
    


  		





  
  217
  
    
    new_revision.file = file


  		





  
  218
  
    
    new_revision.folder = folder ? folder : nil


  		





  
  219
  
    
    new_revision.project = folder ? folder.project : project


  		





  
  220
  
    
    new_revision.comment = l(:comment_copied_from, :source => "#{self.project.identifier}:#{self.dmsf_path_str}")


  		





  
  221
  
    
    


  		





  
  222
  
    
    new_revision.save if file.save  


  		





  
  223
  
    
    


  		





  
  224
  
    
    return file


  		





  
  225
  
    
  end


  		





  
  226
  
    
  


  		





  
  227
  
    
  # To fullfill searchable module expectations


  		





  
  228
  
    
  def self.search(tokens, projects=nil, options={})


  		





  
  229
  
    
    tokens = [] << tokens unless tokens.is_a?(Array)


  		





  
  230
  
    
    projects = [] << projects unless projects.nil? || projects.is_a?(Array)


  		





  
  231
  
    
    


  		





  
  232
  
    
    find_options = {:include => [:project,:revisions]}


  		





  
  233
  
    
    find_options[:order] = "dmsf_files.updated_at " + (options[:before] ? 'DESC' : 'ASC')


  		





  
  234
  
    
    


  		





  
  235
  
    
    limit_options = {}


  		





  
  236
  
    
    limit_options[:limit] = options[:limit] if options[:limit]


  		





  
  237
  
    
    if options[:offset]


  		





  
  238
  
    
      limit_options[:conditions] = "(dmsf_files.updated_at " + (options[:before] ? '<' : '>') + "'#{connection.quoted_date(options[:offset])}')"


  		





  
  239
  
    
    end


  		





  
  240
  
    
    


  		





  
  241
  
    
    columns = ["dmsf_files.name","dmsf_file_revisions.title", "dmsf_file_revisions.description"]


  		





  
  242
  
    
    columns = ["dmsf_file_revisions.title"] if options[:titles_only]


  		





  
  243
  
    
            


  		





  
  244
  
    
    token_clauses = columns.collect {|column| "(LOWER(#{column}) LIKE ?)"}


  		





  
  245
  
    
    


  		





  
  246
  
    
    sql = (['(' + token_clauses.join(' OR ') + ')'] * tokens.size).join(options[:all_words] ? ' AND ' : ' OR ')


  		





  
  247
  
    
    find_options[:conditions] = [sql, * (tokens.collect {|w| "%#{w.downcase}%"} * token_clauses.size).sort]


  		





  
  248
  
    
    


  		





  
  249
  
    
    project_conditions = []


  		





  
  250
  
    
    project_conditions << (Project.allowed_to_condition(User.current, :view_dmsf_files))


  		





  
  251
  
    
    project_conditions << "#{DmsfFile.table_name}.project_id IN (#{projects.collect(&:id).join(',')})" unless projects.nil?


  		





  
  252
  
    
    


  		





  
  253
  
    
    results = []


  		





  
  254
  
    
    results_count = 0


  		





  
  255
  
    
    


  		





  
  256
  
    
    with_scope(:find => {:conditions => [project_conditions.join(' AND ') + " AND #{DmsfFile.table_name}.deleted = :false", {:false => false}]}) do


  		





  
  257
  
    
      with_scope(:find => find_options) do


  		





  
  258
  
    
        results_count = count(:all)


  		





  
  259
  
    
        results = find(:all, limit_options)


  		





  
  260
  
    
      end


  		





  
  261
  
    
    end


  		





  
  262
  
    
    


  		





  
  263
  
    
    if !options[:titles_only] && $xapian_bindings_available


  		





  
  264
  
    
      database = nil


  		





  
  265
  
    
      begin


  		





  
  266
  
    
        database = Xapian::Database.new(Setting.plugin_redmine_dmsf["dmsf_index_database"].strip)


  		





  
  267
  
    
      rescue


  		





  
  268
  
    
        Rails.logger.warn "REDMAIN_XAPIAN ERROR: Xapian database is not properly set or initiated or is corrupted."


  		





  
  269
  
    
      end


  		





  
  270
  
    

  		





  
  271
  
    
      unless database.nil?


  		





  
  272
  
    
        enquire = Xapian::Enquire.new(database)


  		





  
  273
  
    
        


  		





  
  274
  
    
        queryString = tokens.join(' ')


  		





  
  275
  
    
        qp = Xapian::QueryParser.new()


  		





  
  276
  
    
        stemmer = Xapian::Stem.new(Setting.plugin_redmine_dmsf['dmsf_stemming_lang'].strip)


  		





  
  277
  
    
        qp.stemmer = stemmer


  		





  
  278
  
    
        qp.database = database


  		





  
  279
  
    
        


  		





  
  280
  
    
        case Setting.plugin_redmine_dmsf['dmsf_stemming_strategy'].strip


  		





  
  281
  
    
          when "STEM_NONE" then qp.stemming_strategy = Xapian::QueryParser::STEM_NONE


  		





  
  282
  
    
          when "STEM_SOME" then qp.stemming_strategy = Xapian::QueryParser::STEM_SOME


  		





  
  283
  
    
          when "STEM_ALL" then qp.stemming_strategy = Xapian::QueryParser::STEM_ALL


  		





  
  284
  
    
        end


  		





  
  285
  
    
      


  		





  
  286
  
    
        if options[:all_words]


  		





  
  287
  
    
          qp.default_op = Xapian::Query::OP_AND


  		





  
  288
  
    
        else  


  		





  
  289
  
    
          qp.default_op = Xapian::Query::OP_OR


  		





  
  290
  
    
        end


  		





  
  291
  
    
        


  		





  
  292
  
    
        query = qp.parse_query(queryString)


  		





  
  293
  
    
  


  		





  
  294
  
    
        enquire.query = query


  		





  
  295
  
    
        matchset = enquire.mset(0, 1000)


  		





  
  296
  
    
    


  		





  
  297
  
    
        unless matchset.nil?


  		





  
  298
  
    
          matchset.matches.each {|m|


  		





  
  299
  
    
            docdata = m.document.data{url}


  		





  
  300
  
    
            dochash = Hash[*docdata.scan(/(url|sample|modtime|type|size)=\/?([^\n\]]+)/).flatten]


  		





  
  301
  
    
            filename = dochash["url"]


  		





  
  302
  
    
            if !filename.nil?


  		





  
  303
  
    
              dmsf_attrs = filename.split("_")


  		





  
  304
  
    
              next if dmsf_attrs[1].blank?


  		





  
  305
  
    
              next unless results.select{|f| f.id.to_s == dmsf_attrs[1]}.empty?


  		





  
  306
  
    
              


  		





  
  307
  
    
              find_conditions =  DmsfFile.merge_conditions(limit_options[:conditions], :id => dmsf_attrs[1], :deleted => false )


  		





  
  308
  
    
              dmsf_file = DmsfFile.find(:first, :conditions => find_conditions )


  		





  
  309
  
    
    


  		





  
  310
  
    
              if !dmsf_file.nil?


  		





  
  311
  
    
                if options[:offset]


  		





  
  312
  
    
                  if options[:before]


  		





  
  313
  
    
                    next if dmsf_file.updated_at < options[:offset]


  		





  
  314
  
    
                  else


  		





  
  315
  
    
                    next if dmsf_file.updated_at > options[:offset]


  		





  
  316
  
    
                  end


  		





  
  317
  
    
                end


  		





  
  318
  
    
              


  		





  
  319
  
    
                allowed = User.current.allowed_to?(:view_dmsf_files, dmsf_file.project)


  		





  
  320
  
    
                project_included = false


  		





  
  321
  
    
                project_included = true if projects.nil?


  		





  
  322
  
    
                if !project_included


  		





  
  323
  
    
                  projects.each {|x| 


  		





  
  324
  
    
                    project_included = true if x[:id] == dmsf_file.project.id


  		





  
  325
  
    
                  }


  		





  
  326
  
    
                end


  		





  
  327
  
    
  


  		





  
  328
  
    
                if (allowed && project_included)


  		





  
  329
  
    
                  results.push(dmsf_file)


  		





  
  330
  
    
                  results_count += 1


  		





  
  331
  
    
                end


  		





  
  332
  
    
              end


  		





  
  333
  
    
            end


  		





  
  334
  
    
          }


  		





  
  335
  
    
        end


  		





  
  336
  
    
      end    


  		





  
  337
  
    
    end


  		





  
  338
  
    
    


  		





  
  339
  
    
    [results, results_count]


  		





  
  340
  
    
  end


  		





  
  341
  
    
  


  		





  
  342
  
    
end

  def self.file_lock_state(file, locked)


  		





  
  25
  
    
    lock = DmsfFileLock.new


  		





  
  26

  27
  
    
    lock.user = User.current

    lock.locked = locked


  		





  
  29
  
    
    lock.save!

  end

class DmsfFileRevision < ActiveRecord::Base


  		





  
  20
  
    
  unloadable


  		





  
  21
  
    
  belongs_to :file, :class_name => "DmsfFile", :foreign_key => "dmsf_file_id"


  		





  
  22
  
    
  belongs_to :source_revision, :class_name => "DmsfFileRevision", :foreign_key => "source_dmsf_file_revision_id"


  		





  
  23
  
    
  belongs_to :user


  		





  
  24
  
    
  belongs_to :folder, :class_name => "DmsfFolder", :foreign_key => "dmsf_folder_id"


  		





  
  25
  
    
  belongs_to :deleted_by_user, :class_name => "User", :foreign_key => "deleted_by_user_id"


  		





  
  26
  
    
  belongs_to :project


  		





  
  27
  
    
  


  		





  
  28
  
    
  acts_as_event :title => Proc.new {|o| "#{l(:label_dmsf_updated)}: #{o.file.dmsf_path_str}"},


  		





  
  29
  
    
                :url => Proc.new {|o| {:controller => 'dmsf_files', :action => 'show', :id => o.file}},


  		





  
  30
  
    
                :datetime => Proc.new {|o| o.updated_at },


  		





  
  31
  
    
                :description => Proc.new {|o| o.comment },


  		





  
  32
  
    
                :author => Proc.new {|o| o.user }


  		





  
  33
  
    
                


  		





  
  34
  
    
  acts_as_activity_provider :type => "dmsf_files",


  		





  
  35
  
    
                            :timestamp => "#{DmsfFileRevision.table_name}.updated_at",


  		





  
  36
  
    
                            :author_key => "#{DmsfFileRevision.table_name}.user_id",


  		





  
  37
  
    
                            :permission => :view_dmsf_files,


  		





  
  38
  
    
                            :find_options => {:select => "#{DmsfFileRevision.table_name}.*", 


  		





  
  39
  
    
                                              :joins => 


  		





  
  40
  
    
                                                "INNER JOIN #{DmsfFile.table_name} ON #{DmsfFileRevision.table_name}.dmsf_file_id = #{DmsfFile.table_name}.id " +


  		





  
  41
  
    
                                                "INNER JOIN #{Project.table_name} ON #{DmsfFile.table_name}.project_id = #{Project.table_name}.id",


  		





  
  42
  
    
                                              :conditions => ["#{DmsfFile.table_name}.deleted = :false", {:false => false}]


  		





  
  43
  
    
                                             }


  		





  
  44
  
    
  


  		





  
  45
  
    
  validates_presence_of :title


  		





  
  46
  
    
  validates_presence_of :name


  		





  
  47
  
    
  validates_format_of :name, :with => DmsfFolder.invalid_characters,


  		





  
  48
  
    
    :message => l(:error_contains_invalid_character)


  		





  
  49
  
    
  


  		





  
  50
  
    
  def self.remove_extension(filename)


  		





  
  51
  
    
    filename[0, (filename.length - File.extname(filename).length)]


  		





  
  52
  
    
  end


  		





  
  53
  
    
  


  		





  
  54
  
    
  #TODO: check if better to move to dmsf_upload class


  		





  
  55
  
    
  def self.filename_to_title(filename)


  		





  
  56
  
    
    remove_extension(filename).gsub(/_+/, " ");


  		





  
  57
  
    
  end


  		





  
  58
  
    
  


  		





  
  59
  
    
  def delete(delete_all = false)


  		





  
  60
  
    
    if self.file.locked_for_user?


  		





  
  61
  
    
      errors.add_to_base(l(:error_file_is_locked))


  		





  
  62
  
    
      return false 


  		





  
  63
  
    
    end


  		





  
  64
  
    
    if !delete_all && self.file.revisions.length <= 1


  		





  
  65
  
    
      errors.add_to_base(l(:error_at_least_one_revision_must_be_present))


  		





  
  66
  
    
      return false


  		





  
  67
  
    
    end


  		





  
  68
  
    
    dependent = DmsfFileRevision.find(:all, :conditions => 


  		





  
  69
  
    
      ["source_dmsf_file_revision_id = :id and deleted = :deleted",


  		





  
  70
  
    
        {:id => self.id, :deleted => false}])


  		





  
  71
  
    
    dependent.each do |d| 


  		





  
  72
  
    
      d.source_revision = self.source_revision


  		





  
  73
  
    
      d.save!


  		





  
  74
  
    
    end


  		





  
  75
  
    
    if Setting.plugin_redmine_dmsf["dmsf_really_delete_files"]


  		





  
  76
  
    
      dependent = DmsfFileRevision.find(:all, :conditions => 


  		





  
  77
  
    
        ["disk_filename = :filename", {:filename => self.disk_filename}])


  		





  
  78
  
    
      File.delete(self.disk_file) if dependent.length <= 1 && File.exist?(self.disk_file) 


  		





  
  79
  
    
      DmsfFileRevisionAccess.find(:all, :conditions => ["dmsf_file_revision_id = ?", self.id]).each {|a| a.destroy}


  		





  
  80
  
    
      self.destroy


  		





  
  81
  
    
    else


  		





  
  82
  
    
      self.deleted = true


  		





  
  83
  
    
      self.deleted_by_user = User.current


  		





  
  84
  
    
      save


  		





  
  85
  
    
    end


  		





  
  86
  
    
  end


  		





  
  87
  
    
  


  		





  
  88
  
    
  def self.access_grouped(revision_id)


  		





  
  89
  
    
    sql = "select user_id, count(*) as count, min(created_at) as min, max(created_at) as max from #{DmsfFileRevisionAccess.table_name} where dmsf_file_revision_id = ? group by user_id"


  		





  
  90
  
    
    self.connection.select_all(self.sanitize_sql_array([sql, revision_id]))


  		





  
  91
  
    
  end


  		





  
  92
  
    
  


  		





  
  93
  
    
  def access_grouped


  		





  
  94
  
    
    DmsfFileRevision.access_grouped(self.id)


  		





  
  95
  
    
  end

  def version


  		





  
  98
  
    
    "#{self.major_version}.#{self.minor_version}"


  		





  
  99
  
    
  end

  def disk_file


  		





  
  102
  
    
    "#{DmsfFile.storage_path}/#{self.disk_filename}"


  		





  
  103
  
    
  end


  		





  
  104
  
    
  


  		





  
  105
  
    
  def detect_content_type


  		





  
  106
  
    
    content_type = self.mime_type


  		





  
  107
  
    
    content_type = Redmine::MimeType.of(self.disk_filename) if content_type.blank?


  		





  
  108
  
    
    content_type = "application/octet-stream" if content_type.blank?


  		





  
  109
  
    
    content_type.to_s


  		





  
  110
  
    
  end


  		





  
  111

  #TODO: use standard clone method


  		





  
  113
  
    
  def clone


  		





  
  114
  
    
    new_revision = DmsfFileRevision.new


  		





  
  115
  
    
    new_revision.file = self.file


  		





  
  116
  
    
    new_revision.project = self.project


  		





  
  117
  
    
    new_revision.disk_filename = self.disk_filename


  		





  
  118
  
    
    new_revision.size = self.size


  		





  
  119
  
    
    new_revision.mime_type = self.mime_type


  		





  
  120
  
    
    new_revision.title = self.title


  		





  
  121
  
    
    new_revision.description = self.description


  		





  
  122
  
    
    new_revision.workflow = self.workflow


  		





  
  123
  
    
    new_revision.major_version = self.major_version


  		





  
  124
  
    
    new_revision.minor_version = self.minor_version


  		





  
  125
  
    
    


  		





  
  126
  
    
    new_revision.source_revision = self


  		





  
  127
  
    
    new_revision.user = User.current


  		





  
  128
  
    
    


  		





  
  129
  
    
    new_revision.name = self.name


  		





  
  130
  
    
    new_revision.folder = self.folder


  		





  
  131
  
    
    


  		





  
  132
  
    
    return new_revision


  		





  
  133
  
    
  end


  		





  
  134
  
    
  


  		





  
  135
  
    
  #TODO: validate if it isn't doubled or move it to view


  		





  
  136
  
    
  def workflow_str


  		





  
  137
  
    
    case workflow


  		





  
  138
  
    
      when 1 then l(:title_waiting_for_approval)


  		





  
  139
  
    
      when 2 then l(:title_approved)


  		





  
  140
  
    
      else nil


  		





  
  141
  
    
    end


  		





  
  142
  
    
  end


  		





  
  143
  
    
  


  		





  
  144
  
    
  def set_workflow(workflow)


  		





  
  145
  
    
    if User.current.allowed_to?(:file_approval, self.file.project)


  		





  
  146
  
    
      self.workflow = workflow


  		





  
  147
  
    
    else


  		





  
  148
  
    
      if self.source_revision.nil?


  		





  
  149
  
    
        self.workflow = workflow == 2 ? 1 : workflow


  		





  
  150
  
    
      else


  		





  
  151
  
    
        if workflow == 2 || self.source_revision.workflow == 1 || self.source_revision.workflow == 2


  		





  
  152
  
    
          self.workflow = 1


  		





  
  153
  
    
        else


  		





  
  154
  
    
          self.workflow = workflow


  		





  
  155
  
    
        end


  		





  
  156
  
    
      end


  		





  
  157
  
    
    end


  		





  
  158
  
    
  end


  		





  
  159
  
    
  


  		





  
  160
  
    
  def increase_version(version_to_increase, new_content)


  		





  
  161
  
    
    if new_content


  		





  
  162
  
    
      self.minor_version = case version_to_increase 


  		





  
  163
  
    
        when 2 then 0


  		





  
  164
  
    
        else self.minor_version + 1


  		





  
  165
  
    
      end


  		





  
  166
  
    
    else


  		





  
  167
  
    
      self.minor_version = case version_to_increase 


  		





  
  168
  
    
        when 1 then self.minor_version + 1


  		





  
  169
  
    
        when 2 then 0


  		





  
  170
  
    
        else self.minor_version


  		





  
  171
  
    
      end


  		





  
  172
  
    
    end


  		





  
  173
  
    

  		





  
  174
  
    
    self.major_version = case version_to_increase 


  		





  
  175
  
    
      when 2 then self.major_version + 1


  		





  
  176
  
    
      else self.major_version


  		





  
  177
  
    
    end


  		





  
  178
  
    
  end


  		





  
  179
  
    
  


  		





  
  180
  
    
  def display_title


  		





  
  181
  
    
    #if self.title.length > 35


  		





  
  182
  
    
    #  return self.title[0, 30] + "..."


  		





  
  183
  
    
    #else 


  		





  
  184
  
    
      return self.title


  		





  
  185
  
    
    #end


  		





  
  186
  
    
  end


  		





  
  187
  
    
  


  		





  
  188
  
    
  def new_storage_filename


  		





  
  189
  
    
    raise DmsfAccessError, "File id is not set" unless self.file.id


  		





  
  190
  
    
    filename = DmsfHelper.sanitize_filename(self.name)


  		





  
  191
  
    
    timestamp = DateTime.now.strftime("%y%m%d%H%M%S")


  		





  
  192
  
    
    while File.exist?(File.join(DmsfFile.storage_path, "#{timestamp}_#{self.file.id}_#{filename}"))


  		





  
  193
  
    
      timestamp.succ!


  		





  
  194
  
    
    end


  		





  
  195
  
    
    "#{timestamp}_#{self.file.id}_#{filename}"


  		





  
  196
  
    
  end


  		





  
  197
  
    
  


  		





  
  198
  
    
  def copy_file_content(open_file)


  		





  
  199
  
    
    File.open(self.disk_file, "wb") do |f| 


  		





  
  200
  
    
      while (buffer = open_file.read(8192))


  		





  
  201
  
    
        f.write(buffer)


  		





  
  202
  
    
      end


  		





  
  203
  
    
    end


  		





  
  204
  
    
  end


  		





  
  205
  
    
     


  		





  
  206
  
    
end

class DmsfFolder < ActiveRecord::Base


  		





  
  20
  
    
  unloadable


  		





  
  21
  
    
  


  		





  
  22
  
    
  cattr_reader :invalid_characters


  		





  
  23
  
    
  @@invalid_characters = /\A[^\/\\\?":<>]*\z/


  		





  
  24
  
    
  


  		





  
  25
  
    
  belongs_to :project


  		





  
  26
  
    
  belongs_to :folder, :class_name => "DmsfFolder", :foreign_key => "dmsf_folder_id"


  		





  
  27
  
    
  has_many :subfolders, :class_name => "DmsfFolder", :foreign_key => "dmsf_folder_id", :order => "title ASC"


  		





  
  28
  
    
  has_many :files, :class_name => "DmsfFile", :foreign_key => "dmsf_folder_id",


  		





  
  29
  
    
           :conditions => { :deleted => false }


  		





  
  30
  
    
  belongs_to :user


  		





  
  31
  
    
  


  		





  
  32
  
    
  validates_presence_of :title


  		





  
  33
  
    
  validates_uniqueness_of :title, :scope => [:dmsf_folder_id, :project_id]


  		





  
  34
  
    
  


  		





  
  35
  
    
  validates_format_of :title, :with => @@invalid_characters,


  		





  
  36
  
    
    :message => l(:error_contains_invalid_character)


  		





  
  37
  
    
  


  		





  
  38
  
    
  validate :check_cycle


  		





  
  39
  
    
  


  		





  
  40
  
    
  acts_as_event :title => Proc.new {|o| o.title},


  		





  
  41
  
    
                :description => Proc.new {|o| o.description },


  		





  
  42
  
    
                :url => Proc.new {|o| {:controller => "dmsf", :action => "show", :id => o.project, :folder_id => o}},


  		





  
  43
  
    
                :datetime => Proc.new {|o| o.updated_at },


  		





  
  44
  
    
                :author => Proc.new {|o| o.user }


  		





  
  45
  
    
  


  		





  
  46
  
    
  def check_cycle


  		





  
  47
  
    
    folders = []


  		





  
  48
  
    
    self.subfolders.each {|f| folders.push(f)}


  		





  
  49
  
    
    folders.each do |folder|


  		





  
  50
  
    
      if folder == self.folder


  		





  
  51
  
    
        errors.add(:folder, l(:error_create_cycle_in_folder_dependency))


  		





  
  52
  
    
        return false 


  		





  
  53
  
    
      end


  		





  
  54
  
    
      folder.subfolders.each {|f| folders.push(f)}


  		





  
  55
  
    
    end


  		





  
  56
  
    
    return true


  		





  
  57
  
    
  end


  		





  
  58
  
    
  


  		





  
  59
  
    
  def self.project_root_folders(project)


  		





  
  60
  
    
    find(:all, :conditions => 


  		





  
  61
  
    
        ["dmsf_folder_id is NULL and project_id = :project_id", {:project_id => project.id}], :order => "title ASC")


  		





  
  62
  
    
  end


  		





  
  63
  
    
  


  		





  
  64
  
    
  def self.find_by_title(project, folder, title)


  		





  
  65
  
    
    if folder.nil?


  		





  
  66
  
    
      find(:first, :conditions => 


  		





  
  67
  
    
        ["dmsf_folder_id is NULL and project_id = :project_id and title = :title", 


  		





  
  68
  
    
          {:project_id => project.id, :title => title}])


  		





  
  69
  
    
    else


  		





  
  70
  
    
      find(:first, :conditions => 


  		





  
  71
  
    
        ["dmsf_folder_id = :folder_id and title = :title", 


  		





  
  72
  
    
          {:project_id => project.id, :folder_id => folder.id, :title => title}])


  		





  
  73
  
    
    end


  		





  
  74
  
    
  end


  		





  
  75
  
    
  


  		





  
  76
  
    
  def delete


  		





  
  77
  
    
    return false if !self.subfolders.empty? || !self.files.empty?


  		





  
  78
  
    
    destroy


  		





  
  79
  
    
  end


  		





  
  80
  
    
  


  		





  
  81
  
    
  def dmsf_path


  		





  
  82
  
    
    folder = self


  		





  
  83
  
    
    path = []


  		





  
  84
  
    
    while !folder.nil?


  		





  
  85
  
    
      path.unshift(folder)


  		





  
  86
  
    
      folder = folder.folder


  		





  
  87
  
    
    end 


  		





  
  88
  
    
    path


  		





  
  89
  
    
  end


  		





  
  90
  
    
  


  		





  
  91
  
    
  def dmsf_path_str


  		





  
  92
  
    
    path = self.dmsf_path


  		





  
  93
  
    
    string_path = path.map { |element| element.title }


  		





  
  94
  
    
    string_path.join("/")


  		





  
  95
  
    
  end


  		





  
  96
  
    
  


  		





  
  97
  
    
  def notify?


  		





  
  98
  
    
    return true if self.notification


  		





  
  99
  
    
    return true if folder && folder.notify?


  		





  
  100
  
    
    return false


  		





  
  101
  
    
  end


  		





  
  102
  
    
  


  		





  
  103
  
    
  def notify_deactivate


  		





  
  104
  
    
    self.notification = false


  		





  
  105
  
    
    self.save!


  		





  
  106
  
    
  end


  		





  
  107
  
    
  


  		





  
  108
  
    
  def notify_activate


  		





  
  109
  
    
    self.notification = true


  		





  
  110
  
    
    self.save!


  		





  
  111
  
    
  end


  		





  
  112
  
    
  


  		





  
  113
  
    
  def self.directory_tree(project, current_folder = nil)


  		





  
  114
  
    
    tree = [[l(:link_documents), nil]]


  		





  
  115
  
    
    DmsfFolder.project_root_folders(project).each do |folder|


  		





  
  116
  
    
      unless folder == current_folder


  		





  
  117
  
    
        tree.push(["...#{folder.title}", folder.id])


  		





  
  118
  
    
        directory_subtree(tree, folder, 2, current_folder)


  		





  
  119
  
    
      end


  		





  
  120
  
    
    end


  		





  
  121
  
    
    return tree


  		





  
  122
  
    
  end


  		





  
  123
  
    

  		





  
  124
  
    
  def deep_file_count


  		





  
  125
  
    
    file_count = self.files.length


  		





  
  126
  
    
    self.subfolders.each {|subfolder| file_count += subfolder.deep_file_count}


  		





  
  127
  
    
    file_count


  		





  
  128
  
    
  end


  		





  
  129
  
    

  		





  
  130
  
    
  def deep_size


  		





  
  131
  
    
    size = 0


  		





  
  132
  
    
    self.files.each {|file| size += file.size}


  		





  
  133
  
    
    self.subfolders.each {|subfolder| size += subfolder.deep_size}


  		





  
  134
  
    
    size


  		





  
  135
  
    
  end

  137
  
    
  # Returns an array of projects that current user can copy folder to


  		





  
  138
  
    
  def self.allowed_target_projects_on_copy


  		





  
  139
  
    
    projects = []


  		





  
  140
  
    
    if User.current.admin?


  		





  
  141
  
    
      projects = Project.visible.all


  		





  
  142
  
    
    elsif User.current.logged?


  		





  
  143
  
    
      User.current.memberships.each {|m| projects << m.project if m.roles.detect {|r| r.allowed_to?(:folder_manipulation) && r.allowed_to?(:file_manipulation)}}


  		





  
  144
  
    
    end


  		





  
  145
  
    
    projects


  		





  
  146
  
    
  end


  		





  
  147
  
    

  		





  
  148
  
    
  def copy_to(project, folder)


  		





  
  149
  
    
    new_folder = DmsfFolder.new


  		





  
  150
  
    
    new_folder.folder = folder ? folder : nil


  		





  
  151
  
    
    new_folder.project = folder ? folder.project : project


  		





  
  152
  
    
    new_folder.title = self.title


  		





  
  153
  
    
    new_folder.description = self.description


  		





  
  154
  
    
    new_folder.user = User.current


  		





  
  155
  
    

  		





  
  156
  
    
    return new_folder unless new_folder.save


  		





  
  157
  
    
    


  		





  
  158
  
    
    self.files.each do |f|


  		





  
  159
  
    
      f.copy_to(project, new_folder)


  		





  
  160
  
    
    end


  		





  
  161
  
    
    


  		





  
  162
  
    
    self.subfolders.each do |s|


  		





  
  163
  
    
      s.copy_to(project, new_folder)


  		





  
  164
  
    
    end


  		





  
  165
  
    
    


  		





  
  166
  
    
    return new_folder


  		





  
  167
  
    
  end

  169
  
    
  # To fullfill searchable module expectations


  		





  
  170
  
    
  def self.search(tokens, projects=nil, options={})


  		





  
  171
  
    
    tokens = [] << tokens unless tokens.is_a?(Array)


  		





  
  172
  
    
    projects = [] << projects unless projects.nil? || projects.is_a?(Array)


  		





  
  173
  
    
    


  		





  
  174
  
    
    find_options = {:include => [:project]}


  		





  
  175
  
    
    find_options[:order] = "dmsf_folders.updated_at " + (options[:before] ? 'DESC' : 'ASC')


  		





  
  176
  
    
    


  		





  
  177
  
    
    limit_options = {}


  		





  
  178
  
    
    limit_options[:limit] = options[:limit] if options[:limit]


  		





  
  179
  
    
    if options[:offset]


  		





  
  180
  
    
      limit_options[:conditions] = "(dmsf_folders.updated_at " + (options[:before] ? '<' : '>') + "'#{connection.quoted_date(options[:offset])}')"


  		





  
  181
  
    
    end


  		





  
  182
  
    
    


  		





  
  183
  
    
    columns = options[:titles_only] ? ["dmsf_folders.title"] : ["dmsf_folders.title", "dmsf_folders.description"]


  		





  
  184
  
    
            


  		





  
  185
  
    
    token_clauses = columns.collect {|column| "(LOWER(#{column}) LIKE ?)"}


  		





  
  186
  
    
    


  		





  
  187
  
    
    sql = (['(' + token_clauses.join(' OR ') + ')'] * tokens.size).join(options[:all_words] ? ' AND ' : ' OR ')


  		





  
  188
  
    
    find_options[:conditions] = [sql, * (tokens.collect {|w| "%#{w.downcase}%"} * token_clauses.size).sort]


  		





  
  189
  
    
    


  		





  
  190
  
    
    project_conditions = []


  		





  
  191
  
    
    project_conditions << (Project.allowed_to_condition(User.current, :view_dmsf_files))


  		





  
  192
  
    
    project_conditions << "project_id IN (#{projects.collect(&:id).join(',')})" unless projects.nil?


  		





  
  193
  
    
    


  		





  
  194
  
    
    results = []


  		





  
  195
  
    
    results_count = 0


  		





  
  196
  
    
    


  		





  
  197
  
    
    with_scope(:find => {:conditions => [project_conditions.join(' AND ')]}) do


  		





  
  198
  
    
      with_scope(:find => find_options) do


  		





  
  199
  
    
        results_count = count(:all)


  		





  
  200
  
    
        results = find(:all, limit_options)


  		





  
  201
  
    
      end


  		





  
  202
  
    
    end


  		





  
  203
  
    
    


  		





  
  204
  
    
    [results, results_count]


  		





  
  205
  
    
  end


  		





  
  206
  
    

  		





  
  207
  
    
  private


  		





  
  208
  
    
  


  		





  
  209
  
    
  def self.directory_subtree(tree, folder, level, current_folder)


  		





  
  210
  
    
    folder.subfolders.each do |subfolder|


  		





  
  211
  
    
      unless subfolder == current_folder


  		





  
  212
  
    
        tree.push(["#{"..." * level}#{subfolder.title}", subfolder.id])


  		





  
  213
  
    
        directory_subtree(tree, subfolder, level + 1, current_folder)


  		





  
  214
  
    
      end


  		





  
  215
  
    
    end


  		





  
  216
  
    
  end


  		





  
  217
  
    
  


  		





  
  218
  
    
end

require "mailer"

class DmsfMailer < Mailer

  23
  
    
  def files_updated(user, files)


  		





  
  24
  
    
    project = files[0].project


  		





  
  25
  
    
    files = files.select { |file| file.notify? }


  		





  
  26
  
    
    


  		





  
  27
  
    
    redmine_headers "Project" => project.identifier


  		





  
  28
  
    
    recipients get_notify_user_emails(user, files)


  		





  
  29
  
    
    subject project.name + ": Dmsf files updated"


  		





  
  30
  
    
    body :user => user, :files => files, :project => project


  		





  
  31
  
    
    # TODO: correct way should be  render_multipart("files_updated", body), but other plugin broke it


  		





  
  32
  
    
    render_multipart(File.expand_path(File.dirname(__FILE__) + "/../views/dmsf_mailer/" + "files_updated"), body)


  		





  
  33
  
    
  end


  		





  
  34
  
    
  


  		





  
  35
  
    
  def files_deleted(user, files)


  		





  
  36
  
    
    project = files[0].project


  		





  
  37
  
    
    files = files.select { |file| file.notify? }


  		





  
  38
  
    
    


  		





  
  39
  
    
    redmine_headers "Project" => project.identifier


  		





  
  40
  
    
    recipients get_notify_user_emails(user, files)


  		





  
  41
  
    
    subject project.name + ": Dmsf files deleted"


  		





  
  42
  
    
    body :user => user, :files => files, :project => project


  		





  
  43
  
    
    # TODO: correct way should be  render_multipart("files_updated", body), but other plugin broke it


  		





  
  44
  
    
    render_multipart(File.expand_path(File.dirname(__FILE__) + "/../views/dmsf_mailer/" + "files_deleted"), body)


  		





  
  45
  
    
  end


  		





  
  46
  
    
  


  		





  
  47
  
    
  def send_documents(user, email_to, email_cc, email_subject, zipped_content, email_plain_body)


  		





  
  48
  
    
    recipients      email_to


  		





  
  49
  
    
    if !email_cc.strip.blank?


  		





  
  50
  
    
      cc              email_cc


  		





  
  51
  
    
    end


  		





  
  52
  
    
    subject         email_subject


  		





  
  53
  
    
    from            user.mail


  		





  
  54
  
    
    content_type    "multipart/mixed"


  		





  
  55
  
    

  		





  
  56
  
    
    part "text/plain" do |p|


  		





  
  57
  
    
      p.body = email_plain_body


  		





  
  58
  
    
    end


  		





  
  59
  
    
  


  		





  
  60
  
    
    zipped_content_data = open(zipped_content, "rb") {|io| io.read }


  		





  
  61
  
    

  		





  
  62
  
    
    attachment :content_type => "application/zip",


  		





  
  63
  
    
             :filename => "Documents.zip",


  		





  
  64
  
    
             :body => zipped_content_data


  		





  
  65
  
    
  end


  		





  
  66
  
    
  


  		





  
  67
  
    
  private


  		





  
  68
  
    
  


  		





  
  69
  
    
  def get_notify_user_emails(user, files)


  		





  
  70
  
    
    if files.empty?


  		





  
  71
  
    
      return []


  		





  
  72
  
    
    end


  		





  
  73
  
    
    


  		





  
  74
  
    
    project = files[0].project


  		





  
  75
  
    
    


  		





  
  76
  
    
    notify_members = project.members


  		





  
  77
  
    
    notify_members = notify_members.select do |notify_member|


  		





  
  78
  
    
      notify_user = notify_member.user


  		





  
  79
  
    
      if notify_user.pref[:no_self_notified] && notify_user == user


  		





  
  80
  
    
        false


  		





  
  81
  
    
      else


  		





  
  82
  
    
        if notify_member.dmsf_mail_notification.nil?


  		





  
  83
  
    
          case notify_user.mail_notification


  		





  
  84
  
    
          when 'all'


  		





  
  85
  
    
            true


  		





  
  86
  
    
          when 'selected'


  		





  
  87
  
    
            notify_member.mail_notification?


  		





  
  88
  
    
          when 'only_my_events'


  		





  
  89
  
    
            notify_user.allowed_to?(:file_approval, project) ? true : false


  		





  
  90
  
    
          when 'only_owner'


  		





  
  91
  
    
            notify_user.allowed_to?(:file_approval, project) ? true : false


  		





  
  92
  
    
          else


  		





  
  93
  
    
            false


  		





  
  94
  
    
          end


  		





  
  95
  
    
        else  
          notify_member.dmsf_mail_notification


  		





  
  96
  
    
        end


  		





  
  97
  
    
      end


  		





  
  98
  
    
    end      


  		





  
  99
  
    

  		





  
  100
  
    
    notify_members.collect {|m| m.user.mail }


  		





  
  101
  
    
  end


  		





  
  102
  
    
  


  		





  
  103
  
    
end

  35
  
    
  def disk_file


  		





  
  36
  
    
    "#{DmsfHelper.temp_dir}/#{self.disk_filename}"


  		





  
  37
  
    
  end


  		





  
  38
  
    
  


  		





  
  39
  
    
  def self.create_from_uploaded_file(project, folder, uploaded_file)


  		





  
  40
  
    
    uploaded = {


  		





  
  41
  
    
      "disk_filename" => DmsfHelper.temp_filename(uploaded_file.original_filename),


  		





  
  42
  
    
      "content_type" => uploaded_file.content_type.to_s,


  		





  
  43
  
    
      "original_filename" => uploaded_file.original_filename,


  		





  
  44
  
    
    }


  		





  
  45
  
    
    


  		





  
  46
  
    
    File.open("#{DmsfHelper.temp_dir}/#{uploaded["disk_filename"]}", "wb") do |f| 


  		





  
  47
  
    
      while (buffer = uploaded_file.read(8192))


  		





  
  48
  
    
        f.write(buffer)


  		





  
  49
  
    
      end


  		





  
  50
  
    
    end


  		





  
  51
  
    
    DmsfUpload.new(project, folder, uploaded)


  		





  
  52
  
    
  end


  		





  
  53
  
    
  


  		





  
  54
  
    
  def initialize(project, folder, uploaded)


  		





  
  55
  
    
    @name = uploaded["original_filename"]


  		





  
  56
  
    
    


  		





  
  57
  
    
    dmsf_file = DmsfFile.find_file_by_name(project, folder, @name)


  		





  
  58
  
    
    


  		





  
  59
  
    
    @disk_filename = uploaded["disk_filename"]


  		





  
  60
  
    
    @mime_type = uploaded["content_type"]


  		





  
  61
  
    
    @size = File.size(disk_file)


  		





  
  62
  
    
    


  		





  
  63
  
    
    if dmsf_file.nil? || dmsf_file.last_revision.nil?


  		





  
  64
  
    
      @title = DmsfFileRevision.filename_to_title(@name)


  		





  
  65
  
    
      @description = nil


  		





  
  66
  
    
      @major_version = 0


  		





  
  67
  
    
      @minor_version = 0


  		





  
  68
  
    
      @workflow = nil


  		





  
  69
  
    
    else


  		





  
  70
  
    
      last_revision = dmsf_file.last_revision 


  		





  
  71
  
    
      @title = last_revision.title


  		





  
  72
  
    
      @description = last_revision.description


  		





  
  73
  
    
      @major_version = last_revision.major_version


  		





  
  74
  
    
      @minor_version = last_revision.minor_version


  		





  
  75
  
    
      @workflow = last_revision.workflow


  		





  
  76
  
    
    end


  		





  
  77
  
    
    


  		





  
  78
  
    
    @locked = !dmsf_file.nil? && dmsf_file.locked_for_user?


  		





  
  79
  
    
  end


  		





  
  80
  
    
  


  		





  
  81
  
    
end

		uploader.bind('Init', function(up, res) {

  221
  
    
		


  		





  
  222
  
    
		// check if file count doesn't exceed the limit


  		





  
  223
  
    
		if (self.options.max_file_count) {


  		





  
  224
  
    
			uploader.bind('FilesAdded', function(up, selectedFiles) {


  		





  
  225
  
    
				var removed = [], selectedCount = selectedFiles.length;


  		





  
  226
  
    
				var extraCount = up.files.length + selectedCount - self.options.max_file_count;


  		





  
  227
  
    
				


  		





  
  228
  
    
				if (extraCount > 0) {


  		





  
  229
  
    
					removed = selectedFiles.splice(selectedCount - extraCount, extraCount);


  		





  
  230
  
    
					


  		





  
  231
  
    
					up.trigger('Error', {


  		





  
  232
  
    
						code : self.FILE_COUNT_ERROR,


  		





  
  233
  
    
						message : _('File count error.'),


  		





  
  234
  
    
						file : removed


  		





  
  235
  
    
					});


  		





  
  236
  
    
				}


  		





  
  237
  
    
			});


  		





  
  238
  
    
		}

		// uploader internal events must run first

		uploader.init();


  		





  
  242
  
    
		


  		





  
  243
  
    
		uploader.bind('FilesAdded', function(up, files) {

  285
  
    
		});


  		





  
  286
  
    
		


  		





  
  287
  
    
		uploader.bind('Error', function(up, err) {			


  		





  
  288
  
    
			var file = err.file, message, details;


  		





  
  289
  
    

  		





  
  290
  
    
			if (file) {


  		





  
  291
  
    
				message = '<strong>' + err.message + '</strong>';


  		





  
  292
  
    
				details = err.details;


  		





  
  293
  
    
				


  		





  
  294
  
    
				if (details) {


  		





  
  295
  
    
					message += " <br /><i>" + err.details + "</i>";


  		





  
  296
  
    
				} else {


  		





  
  297
  
    
					


  		





  
  298
  
    
					switch (err.code) {


  		





  
  299
  
    
						case plupload.FILE_EXTENSION_ERROR:


  		





  
  300
  
    
							details = _("File: %s").replace('%s', file.name);


  		





  
  301
  
    
							break;


  		





  
  302
  
    
						


  		





  
  303
  
    
						case plupload.FILE_SIZE_ERROR:


  		





  
  304
  
    
							details = _("File: %f, size: %s, max file size: %m").replace(/%([fsm])/g, function($0, $1) {


  		





  
  305
  
    
								switch ($1) {


  		





  
  306
  
    
									case 'f': return file.name;


  		





  
  307
  
    
									case 's': return file.size;	


  		





  
  308
  
    
									case 'm': return plupload.parseSize(self.options.max_file_size);


  		





  
  309
  
    
								}


  		





  
  310
  
    
							});


  		





  
  311
  
    
							break;


  		





  
  312
  
    
							


  		





  
  313
  
    
						case self.FILE_COUNT_ERROR:


  		





  
  314
  
    
							details = _("Upload element accepts only %d file(s) at a time. Extra files were stripped.")


  		





  
  315
  
    
								.replace('%d', self.options.max_file_count);


  		





  
  316
  
    
							break;


  		





  
  317
  
    
						


  		





  
  318
  
    
						case plupload.IMAGE_FORMAT_ERROR :


  		





  
  319
  
    
							details = plupload.translate('Image format either wrong or not supported.');


  		





  
  320
  
    
							break;	


  		





  
  321
  
    
						


  		





  
  322
  
    
						case plupload.IMAGE_MEMORY_ERROR :


  		





  
  323
  
    
							details = plupload.translate('Runtime ran out of available memory.');


  		





  
  324
  
    
							break;


  		





  
  325
  
    
						


  		





  
  326
  
    
						case plupload.IMAGE_DIMENSIONS_ERROR :


  		





  
  327
  
    
							details = plupload.translate('Resoultion out of boundaries! <b>%s</b> runtime supports images only up to %wx%hpx.').replace(/%([swh])/g, function($0, $1) {


  		





  
  328
  
    
								switch ($1) {


  		





  
  329
  
    
									case 's': return up.runtime;


  		





  
  330
  
    
									case 'w': return up.features.maxWidth;	


  		





  
  331
  
    
									case 'h': return up.features.maxHeight;


  		





  
  332
  
    
								}


  		





  
  333
  
    
							});


  		





  
  334
  
    
							break;	


  		





  
  335
  
    
													


  		





  
  336
  
    
						case plupload.HTTP_ERROR:


  		





  
  337
  
    
							details = _("Upload URL might be wrong or doesn't exist");


  		





  
  338
  
    
							break;


  		





  
  339
  
    
					}


  		





  
  340
  
    
					message += " <br /><i>" + details + "</i>";


  		





  
  341
  
    
				}


  		





  
  342
  
    
				


  		





  
  343
  
    
				self.notify('error', message);


  		





  
  344
  
    
				self._trigger('error', null, { up: up, file: file, error: message } );


  		





  
  345
  
    
			}


  		





  
  346
  
    
		});


  		





  
  347
  
    
	},


  		





  
  348
  
    
	


  		





  
  349
  
    
	_setOption: function(key, value) {


  		





  
  350
  
    
		var self = this;


  		





  
  351
  
    

  		





  
  352
  
    
		if (key == 'buttons' && typeof(value) == 'object') {	


  		





  
  353
  
    
			value = $.extend(self.options.buttons, value);


  		





  
  354
  
    
			


  		





  
  355
  
    
			if (!value.browse) {


  		





  
  356
  
    
				self.browse_button.button('disable').hide();


  		





  
  357
  
    
				$('#' + self.id + self.runtime + '_container').hide();


  		





  
  358
  
    
			} else {


  		





  
  359
  
    
				self.browse_button.button('enable').show();


  		





  
  360
  
    
				$('#' + self.id + self.runtime + '_container').show();


  		





  
  361
  
    
			}


  		





  
  362
  
    
			


  		





  
  363
  
    
			if (!value.start) {


  		





  
  364
  
    
				self.start_button.button('disable').hide();


  		





  
  365
  
    
			} else {


  		





  
  366
  
    
				self.start_button.button('enable').show();


  		





  
  367
  
    
			}


  		





  
  368
  
    
			


  		





  
  369
  
    
			if (!value.stop) {


  		





  
  370
  
    
				self.stop_button.button('disable').hide();


  		





  
  371
  
    
			} else {


  		





  
  372
  
    
				self.start_button.button('enable').show();	


  		





  
  373
  
    
			}


  		





  
  374
  
    
		}


  		





  
  375
  
    
		


  		





  
  376
  
    
		self.uploader.settings[key] = value;	


  		





  
  377
  
    
	},

  390
  
    
	getFile: function(id) {


  		





  
  391
  
    
		var file;


  		





  
  392
  
    
		


  		





  
  393
  
    
		if (typeof id === 'number') {


  		





  
  394
  
    
			file = this.uploader.files[id];	


  		





  
  395
  
    
		} else {


  		





  
  396
  
    
			file = this.uploader.getFile(id);	


  		





  
  397
  
    
		}


  		





  
  398
  
    
		return file;


  		





  
  399
  
    
	},


  		





  
  400
  
    
	


  		





  
  401
  
    
	removeFile: function(id) {


  		





  
  402
  
    
		var file = this.getFile(id);


  		





  
  403
  
    
		if (file) {


  		





  
  404
  
    
			this.uploader.removeFile(file);


  		





  
  405
  
    
		}


  		





  
  406
  
    
	},

	clearQueue: function() {

	},


  		





  
  411

  421
  
    
	_handleState: function() {


  		





  
  422
  
    
		var self = this, uploader = this.uploader;


  		





  
  423
  
    
						


  		





  
  424
  
    
		if (uploader.state === plupload.STARTED) {


  		





  
  425
  
    
							


  		





  
  426
  
    
			$(self.start_button).button('disable');


  		





  
  427
  
    
								


  		





  
  428
  
    
			$([])


  		





  
  429
  
    
				.add(self.stop_button)


  		





  
  430
  
    
				.add('.plupload_started')


  		





  
  431
  
    
					.removeClass('plupload_hidden');


  		





  
  432
  
    
							


  		





  
  433
  
    
			$('.plupload_upload_status', self.element).text(


  		





  
  434
  
    
				_('Uploaded %d/%d files').replace('%d/%d', uploader.total.uploaded+'/'+uploader.files.length)


  		





  
  435
  
    
			);


  		





  
  436
  
    
			


  		





  
  437
  
    
			$('.plupload_header_content', self.element).addClass('plupload_header_content_bw');


  		





  
  438
  
    
		


  		





  
  439
  
    
		} else {


  		





  
  440
  
    
			


  		





  
  441
  
    
			$([])


  		





  
  442
  
    
				.add(self.stop_button)


  		





  
  443
  
    
				.add('.plupload_started')


  		





  
  444
  
    
					.addClass('plupload_hidden');


  		





  
  445
  
    
			


  		





  
  446
  
    
			if (self.options.multiple_queues) {


  		





  
  447
  
    
				$(self.start_button).button('enable');


  		





  
  448
  
    
						


  		





  
  449
  
    
				$('.plupload_header_content', self.element).removeClass('plupload_header_content_bw');


  		





  
  450
  
    
			}


  		





  
  451
  
    

  		





  
  452
  
    
			self._updateFileList();


  		





  
  453
  
    
		}


  		





  
  454
  
    
	},


  		





  
  455
  
    
	


  		





  
  456
  
    
	


  		





  
  457
  
    
	_handleFileStatus: function(file) {


  		





  
  458
  
    
		var actionClass, iconClass;


  		





  
  459
  
    

  		





  
  460
  
    
		switch (file.status) {


  		





  
  461
  
    
			case plupload.DONE: 


  		





  
  462
  
    
				actionClass = 'plupload_done';


  		





  
  463
  
    
				iconClass = 'ui-icon ui-icon-circle-check';


  		





  
  464
  
    
				break;


  		





  
  465
  
    
			


  		





  
  466
  
    
			case plupload.FAILED:


  		





  
  467
  
    
				actionClass = 'ui-state-error plupload_failed';


  		





  
  468
  
    
				iconClass = 'ui-icon ui-icon-alert';


  		





  
  469
  
    
				break;


  		





  
  470
  
    

  		





  
  471
  
    
			case plupload.QUEUED:


  		





  
  472
  
    
				actionClass = 'plupload_delete';


  		





  
  473
  
    
				iconClass = 'ui-icon ui-icon-circle-minus';


  		





  
  474
  
    
				break;


  		





  
  475
  
    

  		





  
  476
  
    
			case plupload.UPLOADING:


  		





  
  477
  
    
				actionClass = 'ui-state-highlight plupload_uploading';


  		





  
  478
  
    
				iconClass = 'ui-icon ui-icon-circle-arrow-w';


  		





  
  479
  
    
				


  		





  
  480
  
    
				// scroll uploading file into the view if its bottom boundary is out of it


  		





  
  481
  
    
				var scroller = $('.plupload_scroll', this.container),


  		





  
  482
  
    
					scrollTop = scroller.scrollTop(),


  		





  
  483
  
    
					scrollerHeight = scroller.height(),


  		





  
  484
  
    
					rowOffset = $('#' + file.id).position().top + $('#' + file.id).height();


  		





  
  485
  
    
					


  		





  
  486
  
    
				if (scrollerHeight < rowOffset) {


  		





  
  487
  
    
					scroller.scrollTop(scrollTop + rowOffset - scrollerHeight);


  		





  
  488
  
    
				}				


  		





  
  489
  
    
				break;


  		





  
  490
  
    
		}


  		





  
  491
  
    
		actionClass += ' ui-state-default plupload_file';


  		





  
  492
  
    

  		





  
  493
  
    
		$('#' + file.id)


  		





  
  494
  
    
			.attr('class', actionClass)


  		





  
  495
  
    
			.find('.ui-icon')


  		





  
  496
  
    
				.attr('class', iconClass);


  		





  
  497
  
    
	},


  		





  
  498
  
    
	


  		





  
  499
  
    
	


  		





  
  500
  
    
	_updateTotalProgress: function() {


  		





  
  501
  
    
		var uploader = this.uploader;


  		





  
  502
  
    
		


  		





  
  503
  
    
		this.progressbar.progressbar('value', uploader.total.percent);


  		





  
  504
  
    
		


  		





  
  505
  
    
		$('.plupload_total_status', this.element).html(uploader.total.percent + '%');


  		





  
  506
  
    
		


  		





  
  507
  
    
		$('.plupload_upload_status', this.element).text(


  		





  
  508
  
    
			_('Uploaded %d/%d files').replace('%d/%d', uploader.total.uploaded+'/'+uploader.files.length)

	_updateFileList: function() {

	_enableRenaming: function() {

		var self = this;

  600
  
    
		$('.plupload_file_name span', this.filelist).live('click', function(e) {

			parts = /^(.+)(\.[^.]+)$/.exec(name);

			if (parts) {

				name = parts[1];

				ext = parts[2];

			targetSpan.next().val(name).focus().blur(function() {

				targetSpan.show().next().remove();


  		





  
  616
  
    
			}).keydown(function(e) {

				var targetInput = $(this);


  		





  
  618
  
    

  		





  
  619
  
    
				if ($.inArray(e.keyCode, [13, 27]) !== -1) {

					if (e.keyCode === 13) {

						file.name = targetInput.val() + ext;

						targetSpan.text(file.name);

					}


  		





  
  627
  
    
					targetInput.blur();


  		





  
  628
  
    
				}

			});

		});

	_enableSortingList: function() {

  670
  
    
			}

		});

(function(window, document, plupload, undef) {


  		





  
  15
  
    
	var uploadInstances = {}, initialized = {};


  		





  
  16
  
    

  		





  
  17
  
    
	function getFlashVersion() {


  		





  
  18
  
    
		var version;


  		





  
  19
  
    

  		





  
  20
  
    
		try {


  		





  
  21
  
    
			version = navigator.plugins['Shockwave Flash'];


  		





  
  22
  
    
			version = version.description;


  		





  
  23
  
    
		} catch (e1) {


  		





  
  24
  
    
			try {


  		





  
  25
  
    
				version = new ActiveXObject('ShockwaveFlash.ShockwaveFlash').GetVariable('$version');


  		





  
  26
  
    
			} catch (e2) {


  		





  
  27
  
    
				version = '0.0';


  		





  
  28
  
    
			}


  		





  
  29
  
    
		}


  		





  
  30
  
    

  		





  
  31
  
    
		version = version.match(/\d+/g);


  		





  
  32
  
    

  		





  
  33
  
    
		return parseFloat(version[0] + '.' + version[1]);


  		





  
  34
  
    
	}


  		





  
  35
  
    

  		





  
  36
  
    
	plupload.flash = {


  		





  
  37
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  38
  
    
		 * Will be executed by the Flash runtime when it sends out events.


  		





  
  39
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  40
  
    
		 * @param {String} id If for the upload instance.


  		





  
  41
  
    
		 * @param {String} name Event name to trigger.


  		





  
  42
  
    
		 * @param {Object} obj Parameters to be passed with event.


  		





  
  43
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  44
  
    
		trigger : function(id, name, obj) {


  		





  
  45
  
    
								


  		





  
  46
  
    
			// Detach the call so that error handling in the browser is presented correctly


  		





  
  47
  
    
			setTimeout(function() {


  		





  
  48
  
    
				var uploader = uploadInstances[id], i, args;


  		





  
  49
  
    

  		





  
  50
  
    
				if (uploader) {


  		





  
  51
  
    
					uploader.trigger('Flash:' + name, obj);


  		





  
  52
  
    
				}


  		





  
  53
  
    
			}, 0);


  		





  
  54
  
    
		}


  		





  
  55
  
    
	};


  		





  
  56
  
    

  		





  
  57
  
    
	/**


  		





  
  58
  
    
	 * FlashRuntime implementation. This runtime supports these features: jpgresize, pngresize, chunks.


  		





  
  59
  
    
	 *


  		





  
  60
  
    
	 * @static


  		





  
  61
  
    
	 * @class plupload.runtimes.Flash


  		





  
  62
  
    
	 * @extends plupload.Runtime


  		





  
  63
  
    
	 */


  		





  
  64
  
    
	plupload.runtimes.Flash = plupload.addRuntime("flash", {


  		





  
  65
  
    
		


  		





  
  66
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  67
  
    
		 * Returns a list of supported features for the runtime.


  		





  
  68
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  69
  
    
		 * @return {Object} Name/value object with supported features.


  		





  
  70
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  71
  
    
		getFeatures : function() {


  		





  
  72
  
    
			return {


  		





  
  73
  
    
				jpgresize: true,


  		





  
  74
  
    
				pngresize: true,


  		





  
  75
  
    
				maxWidth: 8091,


  		





  
  76
  
    
				maxHeight: 8091,


  		





  
  77
  
    
				chunks: true,


  		





  
  78
  
    
				progress: true,


  		





  
  79
  
    
				multipart: true,


  		





  
  80
  
    
				multi_selection: true


  		





  
  81
  
    
			};


  		





  
  82
  
    
		},


  		





  
  83
  
    

  		





  
  84
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  85
  
    
		 * Initializes the upload runtime. This method should add necessary items to the DOM and register events needed for operation. 


  		





  
  86
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  87
  
    
		 * @method init


  		





  
  88
  
    
		 * @param {plupload.Uploader} uploader Uploader instance that needs to be initialized.


  		





  
  89
  
    
		 * @param {function} callback Callback to execute when the runtime initializes or fails to initialize. If it succeeds an object with a parameter name success will be set to true.


  		





  
  90
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  91
  
    
		init : function(uploader, callback) {


  		





  
  92
  
    
			var browseButton, flashContainer, waitCount = 0, container = document.body;


  		





  
  93
  
    

  		





  
  94
  
    
			if (getFlashVersion() < 10) {


  		





  
  95
  
    
				callback({success : false});


  		





  
  96
  
    
				return;


  		





  
  97
  
    
			}


  		





  
  98
  
    

  		





  
  99
  
    
			initialized[uploader.id] = false;


  		





  
  100
  
    
			uploadInstances[uploader.id] = uploader;


  		





  
  101
  
    

  		





  
  102
  
    
			// Find browse button and set to to be relative


  		





  
  103
  
    
			browseButton = document.getElementById(uploader.settings.browse_button);


  		





  
  104
  
    

  		





  
  105
  
    
			// Create flash container and insert it at an absolute position within the browse button


  		





  
  106
  
    
			flashContainer = document.createElement('div');

			function getFlashObj() {


  		





  
  157
  
    
				return document.getElementById(uploader.id + '_flash');


  		





  
  158
  
    
			}

			function waitLoad() {


  		





  
  161
  
    
								


  		





  
  162
  
    
				// Wait for 5 sec


  		





  
  163
  
    
				if (waitCount++ > 5000) {


  		





  
  164
  
    
					callback({success : false});


  		





  
  165
  
    
					return;


  		





  
  166
  
    
				}


  		





  
  167
  
    

  		





  
  168
  
    
				if (!initialized[uploader.id]) {


  		





  
  169
  
    
					setTimeout(waitLoad, 1);


  		





  
  170
  
    
				}


  		





  
  171
  
    
			}


  		





  
  172
  
    

  		





  
  173
  
    
			waitLoad();

			uploader.bind("Flash:Init", function() {	


  		





  
  180
  
    
				var lookup = {}, i;


  		





  
  181
  
    

  		





  
  182
  
    
				getFlashObj().setFileFilters(uploader.settings.filters, uploader.settings.multi_selection);


  		





  
  183
  
    

  		





  
  184
  
    
				// Prevent eventual reinitialization of the instance


  		





  
  185
  
    
				if (initialized[uploader.id]) {


  		





  
  186
  
    
					return;


  		





  
  187
  
    
				}


  		





  
  188
  
    
				initialized[uploader.id] = true;

				uploader.bind("UploadFile", function(up, file) {


  		





  
  191
  
    
					var settings = up.settings, resize = uploader.settings.resize || {};


  		





  
  192
  
    

  		





  
  193
  
    
					getFlashObj().uploadFile(lookup[file.id], settings.url, {


  		





  
  194
  
    
						name : file.target_name || file.name,


  		





  
  195
  
    
						mime : plupload.mimeTypes[file.name.replace(/^.+\.([^.]+)/, '$1').toLowerCase()] || 'application/octet-stream',


  		





  
  196
  
    
						chunk_size : settings.chunk_size,


  		





  
  197
  
    
						width : resize.width,


  		





  
  198
  
    
						height : resize.height,


  		





  
  199
  
    
						quality : resize.quality,


  		





  
  200
  
    
						multipart : settings.multipart,


  		





  
  201
  
    
						multipart_params : settings.multipart_params || {},


  		





  
  202
  
    
						file_data_name : settings.file_data_name,


  		





  
  203
  
    
						format : /\.(jpg|jpeg)$/i.test(file.name) ? 'jpg' : 'png',


  		





  
  204
  
    
						headers : settings.headers,


  		





  
  205
  
    
						urlstream_upload : settings.urlstream_upload


  		





  
  206
  
    
					});


  		





  
  207
  
    
				});

				uploader.bind("Flash:UploadProcess", function(up, flash_file) {


  		





  
  211
  
    
					var file = up.getFile(lookup[flash_file.id]);


  		





  
  212
  
    

  		





  
  213
  
    
					if (file.status != plupload.FAILED) {


  		





  
  214
  
    
						file.loaded = flash_file.loaded;


  		





  
  215
  
    
						file.size = flash_file.size;


  		





  
  216
  
    

  		





  
  217
  
    
						up.trigger('UploadProgress', file);


  		





  
  218
  
    
					}


  		





  
  219
  
    
				});


  		





  
  220
  
    

  		





  
  221
  
    
				uploader.bind("Flash:UploadChunkComplete", function(up, info) {


  		





  
  222
  
    
					var chunkArgs, file = up.getFile(lookup[info.id]);


  		





  
  223
  
    

  		





  
  224
  
    
					chunkArgs = {


  		





  
  225
  
    
						chunk : info.chunk,


  		





  
  226
  
    
						chunks : info.chunks,


  		





  
  227
  
    
						response : info.text


  		





  
  228
  
    
					};


  		





  
  229
  
    

  		





  
  230
  
    
					up.trigger('ChunkUploaded', file, chunkArgs);


  		





  
  231
  
    

  		





  
  232
  
    
					// Stop upload if file is maked as failed


  		





  
  233
  
    
					if (file.status != plupload.FAILED) {


  		





  
  234
  
    
						getFlashObj().uploadNextChunk();


  		





  
  235
  
    
					}


  		





  
  236
  
    

  		





  
  237
  
    
					// Last chunk then dispatch FileUploaded event


  		





  
  238
  
    
					if (info.chunk == info.chunks - 1) {


  		





  
  239
  
    
						file.status = plupload.DONE;


  		





  
  240
  
    

  		





  
  241
  
    
						up.trigger('FileUploaded', file, {


  		





  
  242
  
    
							response : info.text


  		





  
  243
  
    
						});


  		





  
  244
  
    
					}


  		





  
  245
  
    
				});


  		





  
  246
  
    

  		





  
  247
  
    
				uploader.bind("Flash:SelectFiles", function(up, selected_files) {


  		





  
  248
  
    
					var file, i, files = [], id;


  		





  
  249
  
    

  		





  
  250
  
    
					// Add the selected files to the file queue


  		





  
  251
  
    
					for (i = 0; i < selected_files.length; i++) {


  		





  
  252
  
    
						file = selected_files[i];


  		





  
  253
  
    

  		





  
  254
  
    
						// Store away flash ref internally


  		





  
  255
  
    
						id = plupload.guid();


  		





  
  256
  
    
						lookup[id] = file.id;


  		





  
  257
  
    
						lookup[file.id] = id;


  		





  
  258
  
    

  		





  
  259
  
    
						files.push(new plupload.File(id, file.name, file.size));


  		





  
  260
  
    
					}


  		





  
  261
  
    

  		





  
  262
  
    
					// Trigger FilesAdded event if we added any


  		





  
  263
  
    
					if (files.length) {


  		





  
  264
  
    
						uploader.trigger("FilesAdded", files);


  		





  
  265
  
    
					}


  		





  
  266
  
    
				});


  		





  
  267

(function(window, document, plupload, undef) {

	function getById(id) {

		return document.getElementById(id);

	/**


  		





  
  21
  
    
	 * HTML4 implementation. This runtime has no special features it uses an form that posts files into an hidden iframe.
