  1173
  
    

  		





  
  1174
  
    
		function extractTags(IFD_offset, tags2extract) {


  		





  
  1175
  
    
			var length = data.SHORT(IFD_offset), i, ii,


  		





  
  1176
  
    
				tag, type, count, tagOffset, offset, value, values = [], hash = {};


  		





  
  1177
  
    

  		





  
  1178
  
    
			for (i = 0; i < length; i++) {


  		





  
  1179
  
    
				// Set binary reader pointer to beginning of the next tag


  		





  
  1180
  
    
				offset = tagOffset = IFD_offset + 12 * i + 2;


  		





  
  1181
  
    

  		





  
  1182
  
    
				tag = tags2extract[data.SHORT(offset)];


  		





  
  1183
  
    

  		





  
  1184
  
    
				if (tag === undef) {


  		





  
  1185
  
    
					continue; // Not the tag we requested


  		





  
  1186
  
    
				}


  		





  
  1187
  
    

  		





  
  1188
  
    
				type = data.SHORT(offset+=2);


  		





  
  1189
  
    
				count = data.LONG(offset+=2);


  		





  
  1190
  
    

  		





  
  1191
  
    
				offset += 4;


  		





  
  1192
  
    
				values = [];


  		





  
  1193
  
    

  		





  
  1194
  
    
				switch (type) {


  		





  
  1195
  
    
					case 1: // BYTE


  		





  
  1196
  
    
					case 7: // UNDEFINED


  		





  
  1197
  
    
						if (count > 4) {


  		





  
  1198
  
    
							offset = data.LONG(offset) + offsets.tiffHeader;


  		





  
  1199
  
    
						}


  		





  
  1200
  
    

  		





  
  1201
  
    
						for (ii = 0; ii < count; ii++) {


  		





  
  1202
  
    
							values[ii] = data.BYTE(offset + ii);


  		





  
  1203
  
    
						}


  		





  
  1204
  
    

  		





  
  1205
  
    
						break;


  		





  
  1206
  
    

  		





  
  1207
  
    
					case 2: // STRING


  		





  
  1208
  
    
						if (count > 4) {


  		





  
  1209
  
    
							offset = data.LONG(offset) + offsets.tiffHeader;


  		





  
  1210
  
    
						}


  		





  
  1211
  
    

  		





  
  1212
  
    
						hash[tag] = data.STRING(offset, count - 1);


  		





  
  1213
  
    

  		





  
  1214
  
    
						continue;


  		





  
  1215
  
    

  		





  
  1216
  
    
					case 3: // SHORT


  		





  
  1217
  
    
						if (count > 2) {


  		





  
  1218
  
    
							offset = data.LONG(offset) + offsets.tiffHeader;


  		





  
  1219
  
    
						}


  		





  
  1220
  
    

  		





  
  1221
  
    
						for (ii = 0; ii < count; ii++) {


  		





  
  1222
  
    
							values[ii] = data.SHORT(offset + ii*2);


  		





  
  1223
  
    
						}


  		





  
  1224
  
    

  		





  
  1225
  
    
						break;


  		





  
  1226
  
    

  		





  
  1227
  
    
					case 4: // LONG


  		





  
  1228
  
    
						if (count > 1) {


  		





  
  1229
  
    
							offset = data.LONG(offset) + offsets.tiffHeader;


  		





  
  1230
  
    
						}


  		





  
  1231
  
    

  		





  
  1232
  
    
						for (ii = 0; ii < count; ii++) {


  		





  
  1233
  
    
							values[ii] = data.LONG(offset + ii*4);


  		





  
  1234
  
    
						}


  		





  
  1235
  
    

  		





  
  1236
  
    
						break;


  		





  
  1237
  
    

  		





  
  1238
  
    
					case 5: // RATIONAL


  		





  
  1239
  
    
						offset = data.LONG(offset) + offsets.tiffHeader;


  		





  
  1240
  
    

  		





  
  1241
  
    
						for (ii = 0; ii < count; ii++) {


  		





  
  1242
  
    
							values[ii] = data.LONG(offset + ii*4) / data.LONG(offset + ii*4 + 4);


  		





  
  1243
  
    
						}


  		





  
  1244
  
    

  		





  
  1245
  
    
						break;


  		





  
  1246
  
    

  		





  
  1247
  
    
					case 9: // SLONG


  		





  
  1248
  
    
						offset = data.LONG(offset) + offsets.tiffHeader;


  		





  
  1249
  
    

  		





  
  1250
  
    
						for (ii = 0; ii < count; ii++) {


  		





  
  1251
  
    
							values[ii] = data.SLONG(offset + ii*4);


  		





  
  1252
  
    
						}


  		





  
  1253
  
    

  		





  
  1254
  
    
						break;


  		





  
  1255
  
    

  		





  
  1256
  
    
					case 10: // SRATIONAL


  		





  
  1257
  
    
						offset = data.LONG(offset) + offsets.tiffHeader;


  		





  
  1258
  
    

  		





  
  1259
  
    
						for (ii = 0; ii < count; ii++) {


  		





  
  1260
  
    
							values[ii] = data.SLONG(offset + ii*4) / data.SLONG(offset + ii*4 + 4);


  		





  
  1261
  
    
						}


  		





  
  1262
  
    

  		





  
  1263
  
    
						break;


  		





  
  1264
  
    

  		





  
  1265
  
    
					default:


  		





  
  1266
  
    
						continue;


  		





  
  1267
  
    
				}


  		





  
  1268
  
    

  		





  
  1269
  
    
				value = (count == 1 ? values[0] : values);


  		





  
  1270
  
    

  		





  
  1271
  
    
				if (tagDescs.hasOwnProperty(tag) && typeof value != 'object') {


  		





  
  1272
  
    
					hash[tag] = tagDescs[tag][value];


  		





  
  1273
  
    
				} else {


  		





  
  1274
  
    
					hash[tag] = value;


  		





  
  1275
  
    
				}


  		





  
  1276
  
    
			}


  		





  
  1277
  
    

  		





  
  1278
  
    
			return hash;


  		





  
  1279
  
    
		}


  		





  
  1280
  
    

  		





  
  1281
  
    
		function getIFDOffsets() {


  		





  
  1282
  
    
			var Tiff = undef, idx = offsets.tiffHeader;


  		





  
  1283
  
    

  		





  
  1284
  
    
			// Set read order of multi-byte data


  		





  
  1285
  
    
			data.II(data.SHORT(idx) == 0x4949);


  		





  
  1286
  
    

  		





  
  1287
  
    
			// Check if always present bytes are indeed present


  		





  
  1288
  
    
			if (data.SHORT(idx+=2) !== 0x002A) {


  		





  
  1289
  
    
				return false;


  		





  
  1290
  
    
			}


  		





  
  1291
  
    
		


  		





  
  1292
  
    
			offsets['IFD0'] = offsets.tiffHeader + data.LONG(idx += 2);


  		





  
  1293
  
    
			Tiff = extractTags(offsets['IFD0'], tags.tiff);


  		





  
  1294
  
    

  		





  
  1295
  
    
			offsets['exifIFD'] = ('ExifIFDPointer' in Tiff ? offsets.tiffHeader + Tiff.ExifIFDPointer : undef);


  		





  
  1296
  
    
			offsets['gpsIFD'] = ('GPSInfoIFDPointer' in Tiff ? offsets.tiffHeader + Tiff.GPSInfoIFDPointer : undef);


  		





  
  1297
  
    

  		





  
  1298
  
    
			return true;


  		





  
  1299
  
    
		}


  		





  
  1300
  
    
		


  		





  
  1301
  
    
		// At the moment only setting of simple (LONG) values, that do not require offset recalculation, is supported


  		





  
  1302
  
    
		function setTag(ifd, tag, value) {


  		





  
  1303
  
    
			var offset, length, tagOffset, valueOffset = 0;


  		





  
  1304
  
    
			


  		





  
  1305
  
    
			// If tag name passed translate into hex key


  		





  
  1306
  
    
			if (typeof(tag) === 'string') {


  		





  
  1307
  
    
				var tmpTags = tags[ifd.toLowerCase()];


  		





  
  1308
  
    
				for (hex in tmpTags) {


  		





  
  1309
  
    
					if (tmpTags[hex] === tag) {


  		





  
  1310
  
    
						tag = hex;


  		





  
  1311
  
    
						break;	


  		





  
  1312
  
    
					}


  		





  
  1313
  
    
				}


  		





  
  1314
  
    
			}


  		





  
  1315
  
    
			offset = offsets[ifd.toLowerCase() + 'IFD'];


  		





  
  1316
  
    
			length = data.SHORT(offset);


  		





  
  1317
  
    
						


  		





  
  1318
  
    
			for (i = 0; i < length; i++) {


  		





  
  1319
  
    
				tagOffset = offset + 12 * i + 2;


  		





  
  1320
  
    

  		





  
  1321
  
    
				if (data.SHORT(tagOffset) == tag) {


  		





  
  1322
  
    
					valueOffset = tagOffset + 8;


  		





  
  1323
  
    
					break;


  		





  
  1324
  
    
				}


  		





  
  1325
  
    
			}


  		





  
  1326
  
    
			


  		





  
  1327
  
    
			if (!valueOffset) return false;


  		





  
  1328
  
    

  		





  
  1329
  
    
			


  		





  
  1330
  
    
			data.LONG(valueOffset, value);


  		





  
  1331
  
    
			return true;


  		





  
  1332
  
    
		}


  		





  
  1333
  
    
		


  		





  
  1334
  
    

  		





  
  1335
  
    
		// Public functions


  		





  
  1336
  
    
		return {


  		





  
  1337
  
    
			init: function(segment) {


  		





  
  1338
  
    
				// Reset internal data


  		





  
  1339
  
    
				offsets = {


  		





  
  1340
  
    
					tiffHeader: 10


  		





  
  1341
  
    
				};


  		





  
  1342
  
    
				


  		





  
  1343
  
    
				if (segment === undef || !segment.length) {


  		





  
  1344
  
    
					return false;


  		





  
  1345
  
    
				}


  		





  
  1346
  
    

  		





  
  1347
  
    
				data.init(segment);


  		





  
  1348
  
    

  		





  
  1349
  
    
				// Check if that's APP1 and that it has EXIF


  		





  
  1350
  
    
				if (data.SHORT(0) === 0xFFE1 && data.STRING(4, 5).toUpperCase() === "EXIF\0") {


  		





  
  1351
  
    
					return getIFDOffsets();


  		





  
  1352
  
    
				}


  		





  
  1353
  
    
				return false;


  		





  
  1354
  
    
			},


  		





  
  1355
  
    
			


  		





  
  1356
  
    
			EXIF: function() {


  		





  
  1357
  
    
				var Exif;


  		





  
  1358
  
    
				


  		





  
  1359
  
    
				// Populate EXIF hash


  		





  
  1360
  
    
				Exif = extractTags(offsets.exifIFD, tags.exif);


  		





  
  1361
  
    

  		





  
  1362
  
    
				// Fix formatting of some tags


  		





  
  1363
  
    
				if (Exif.ExifVersion) {


  		





  
  1364
  
    
					Exif.ExifVersion = String.fromCharCode(


  		





  
  1365
  
    
						Exif.ExifVersion[0],


  		





  
  1366
  
    
						Exif.ExifVersion[1],


  		





  
  1367
  
    
						Exif.ExifVersion[2],


  		





  
  1368
  
    
						Exif.ExifVersion[3]


  		





  
  1369
  
    
					);


  		





  
  1370
  
    
				}


  		





  
  1371
  
    

  		





  
  1372
  
    
				return Exif;


  		





  
  1373
  
    
			},


  		





  
  1374
  
    

  		





  
  1375
  
    
			GPS: function() {


  		





  
  1376
  
    
				var GPS;


  		





  
  1377
  
    
				


  		





  
  1378
  
    
				GPS = extractTags(offsets.gpsIFD, tags.gps);


  		





  
  1379
  
    
				


  		





  
  1380
  
    
				// iOS devices (and probably some others) do not put in GPSVersionID tag (why?..)


  		





  
  1381
  
    
				if (GPS.GPSVersionID) { 


  		





  
  1382
  
    
					GPS.GPSVersionID = GPS.GPSVersionID.join('.');


  		





  
  1383
  
    
				}


  		





  
  1384
  
    

  		





  
  1385
  
    
				return GPS;


  		





  
  1386
  
    
			},


  		





  
  1387
  
    
			


  		





  
  1388
  
    
			setExif: function(tag, value) {


  		





  
  1389
  
    
				// Right now only setting of width/height is possible


  		





  
  1390
  
    
				if (tag !== 'PixelXDimension' && tag !== 'PixelYDimension') return false;


  		





  
  1391
  
    
				


  		





  
  1392
  
    
				return setTag('exif', tag, value);


  		





  
  1393
  
    
			},


  		





  
  1394
  
    

  		





  
  1395
  
    

  		





  
  1396
  
    
			getBinary: function() {


  		





  
  1397
  
    
				return data.SEGMENT();


  		





  
  1398
  
    
			}


  		





  
  1399
  
    
		};


  		





  
  1400
  
    
	};

})(window, document, plupload);

  243
  
    
		ua: (function() {


  		





  
  244
  
    
			var nav = navigator, userAgent = nav.userAgent, vendor = nav.vendor, webkit, opera, safari;


  		





  
  245
  
    
			


  		





  
  246
  
    
			webkit = /WebKit/.test(userAgent);


  		





  
  247

  249
  
    
			


  		





  
  250
  
    
			return {


  		





  
  251
  
    
				windows: navigator.platform.indexOf('Win') !== -1,


  		





  
  252
  
    
				ie: !webkit && !opera && (/MSIE/gi).test(userAgent) && (/Explorer/gi).test(nav.appName),


  		





  
  253
  
    
				webkit: webkit,


  		





  
  254
  
    
				gecko: !webkit && /Gecko/.test(userAgent),


  		





  
  255
  
    
				safari: safari,


  		





  
  256
  
    
				opera: !!opera


  		





  
  257
  
    
			};


  		





  
  258
  
    
		}()),

		/**

  267

  268
  
    
		extend : function(target) {


  		





  
  269
  
    
			plupload.each(arguments, function(arg, i) {


  		





  
  270
  
    
				if (i > 0) {


  		





  
  271
  
    
					plupload.each(arg, function(value, key) {


  		





  
  272
  
    
						target[key] = value;

		/**


  		





  
  281
  
    
		 * Cleans the specified name from national characters (diacritics). The result will be a name with only a-z, 0-9 and _.


  		





  
  282
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  283
  
    
		 * @method cleanName


  		





  
  284
  
    
		 * @param {String} s String to clean up.


  		





  
  285
  
    
		 * @return {String} Cleaned string.


  		





  
  286
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  287
  
    
		cleanName : function(name) {


  		





  
  288
  
    
			var i, lookup;


  		





  
  289
  
    

  		





  
  290
  
    
			// Replace diacritics


  		





  
  291
  
    
			lookup = [


  		





  
  292
  
    
				/[\300-\306]/g, 'A', /[\340-\346]/g, 'a', 


  		





  
  293
  
    
				/\307/g, 'C', /\347/g, 'c',


  		





  
  294
  
    
				/[\310-\313]/g, 'E', /[\350-\353]/g, 'e',


  		





  
  295
  
    
				/[\314-\317]/g, 'I', /[\354-\357]/g, 'i',


  		





  
  296
  
    
				/\321/g, 'N', /\361/g, 'n',


  		





  
  297
  
    
				/[\322-\330]/g, 'O', /[\362-\370]/g, 'o',


  		





  
  298
  
    
				/[\331-\334]/g, 'U', /[\371-\374]/g, 'u'


  		





  
  299
  
    
			];


  		





  
  300
  
    

  		





  
  301
  
    
			for (i = 0; i < lookup.length; i += 2) {


  		





  
  302
  
    
				name = name.replace(lookup[i], lookup[i + 1]);


  		





  
  303
  
    
			}


  		





  
  304
  
    

  		





  
  305
  
    
			// Replace whitespace


  		





  
  306
  
    
			name = name.replace(/\s+/g, '_');


  		





  
  307
  
    

  		





  
  308
  
    
			// Remove anything else


  		





  
  309
  
    
			name = name.replace(/[^a-z0-9_\-\.]+/gi, '');


  		





  
  310
  
    

  		





  
  311
  
    
			return name;


  		





  
  312
  
    
		},


  		





  
  313
  
    

  		





  
  314
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  315
  
    
		 * Adds a specific upload runtime like for example flash or gears.


  		





  
  316
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  317
  
    
		 * @method addRuntime


  		





  
  318

		addRuntime : function(name, runtime) {

			runtime.name = name;


  		





  
  323
  
    
			runtimes[name] = runtime;


  		





  
  324
  
    
			runtimes.push(runtime);


  		





  
  325
  
    

  		





  
  326

  327
  
    
		},


  		





  
  328
  
    

  		





  
  329
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  330
  
    
		 * Generates an unique ID. This is 99.99% unique since it takes the current time and 5 random numbers.


  		





  
  331
  
    
		 * The only way a user would be able to get the same ID is if the two persons at the same exact milisecond manages


  		





  
  332
  
    
		 * to get 5 the same random numbers between 0-65535 it also uses a counter so each call will be guaranteed to be page unique.


  		





  
  333
  
    
		 * It's more probable for the earth to be hit with an ansteriod. You can also if you want to be 100% sure set the plupload.guidPrefix property


  		





  
  334
  
    
		 * to an user unique key.


  		





  
  335
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  336
  
    
		 * @method guid


  		





  
  337
  
    
		 * @return {String} Virtually unique id.


  		





  
  338
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  339
  
    
		guid : function() {


  		





  
  340
  
    
			var guid = new Date().getTime().toString(32), i;


  		





  
  341
  
    

  		





  
  342
  
    
			for (i = 0; i < 5; i++) {


  		





  
  343
  
    
				guid += Math.floor(Math.random() * 65535).toString(32);


  		





  
  344
  
    
			}


  		





  
  345
  
    

  		





  
  346
  
    
			return (plupload.guidPrefix || 'p') + guid + (count++).toString(32);


  		





  
  347
  
    
		},


  		





  
  348
  
    

  		





  
  349
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  350
  
    
		 * Builds a full url out of a base URL and an object with items to append as query string items.


  		





  
  351
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  352
  
    
		 * @param {String} url Base URL to append query string items to.


  		





  
  353
  
    
		 * @param {Object} items Name/value object to serialize as a querystring.


  		





  
  354
  
    
		 * @return {String} String with url + serialized query string items.


  		





  
  355
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  356
  
    
		buildUrl : function(url, items) {


  		





  
  357
  
    
			var query = '';


  		





  
  358
  
    

  		





  
  359
  
    
			plupload.each(items, function(value, name) {


  		





  
  360
  
    
				query += (query ? '&' : '') + encodeURIComponent(name) + '=' + encodeURIComponent(value);


  		





  
  361
  
    
			});


  		





  
  362
  
    

  		





  
  363
  
    
			if (query) {


  		





  
  364
  
    
				url += (url.indexOf('?') > 0 ? '&' : '?') + query;


  		





  
  365
  
    
			}


  		





  
  366
  
    

  		





  
  367
  
    
			return url;


  		





  
  368
  
    
		},


  		





  
  369
  
    

  		





  
  370
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  371
  
    
		 * Executes the callback function for each item in array/object. If you return false in the


  		





  
  372
  
    
		 * callback it will break the loop.


  		





  
  373
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  374
  
    
		 * @param {Object} obj Object to iterate.


  		





  
  375
  
    
		 * @param {function} callback Callback function to execute for each item.


  		





  
  376
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  377
  
    
		each : function(obj, callback) {


  		





  
  378
  
    
			var length, key, i;


  		





  
  379
  
    

  		





  
  380
  
    
			if (obj) {


  		





  
  381
  
    
				length = obj.length;


  		





  
  382
  
    

  		





  
  383
  
    
				if (length === undef) {


  		





  
  384
  
    
					// Loop object items


  		





  
  385
  
    
					for (key in obj) {


  		





  
  386
  
    
						if (obj.hasOwnProperty(key)) {


  		





  
  387
  
    
							if (callback(obj[key], key) === false) {


  		





  
  388
  
    
								return;


  		





  
  389
  
    
							}


  		





  
  390
  
    
						}


  		





  
  391
  
    
					}


  		





  
  392
  
    
				} else {


  		





  
  393
  
    
					// Loop array items


  		





  
  394
  
    
					for (i = 0; i < length; i++) {


  		





  
  395
  
    
						if (callback(obj[i], i) === false) {


  		





  
  396
  
    
							return;


  		





  
  397
  
    
						}


  		





  
  398
  
    
					}


  		





  
  399
  
    
				}


  		





  
  400
  
    
			}


  		





  
  401
  
    
		},


  		





  
  402
  
    

  		





  
  403
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  404
  
    
		 * Formats the specified number as a size string for example 1024 becomes 1 KB.


  		





  
  405
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  406
  
    
		 * @method formatSize


  		





  
  407
  
    
		 * @param {Number} size Size to format as string.


  		





  
  408
  
    
		 * @return {String} Formatted size string.


  		





  
  409
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  410
  
    
		formatSize : function(size) {


  		





  
  411
  
    
			if (size === undef || /\D/.test(size)) {


  		





  
  412
  
    
				return plupload.translate('N/A');


  		





  
  413
  
    
			}


  		





  
  414
  
    
			


  		





  
  415
  
    
			// GB


  		





  
  416
  
    
			if (size > 1073741824) {


  		





  
  417
  
    
				return Math.round(size / 1073741824, 1) + " GB";


  		





  
  418
  
    
			}


  		





  
  419
  
    

  		





  
  420
  
    
			// MB


  		





  
  421
  
    
			if (size > 1048576) {


  		





  
  422
  
    
				return Math.round(size / 1048576, 1) + " MB";


  		





  
  423
  
    
			}


  		





  
  424
  
    

  		





  
  425
  
    
			// KB


  		





  
  426
  
    
			if (size > 1024) {


  		





  
  427
  
    
				return Math.round(size / 1024, 1) + " KB";


  		





  
  428
  
    
			}


  		





  
  429
  
    

  		





  
  430
  
    
			return size + " b";


  		





  
  431
  
    
		},


  		





  
  432
  
    

  		





  
  433
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  434
  
    
		 * Returns the absolute x, y position of an Element. The position will be returned in a object with x, y fields.


  		





  
  435
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  436
  
    
		 * @method getPos


  		





  
  437
  
    
		 * @param {Element} node HTML element or element id to get x, y position from.


  		





  
  438
  
    
		 * @param {Element} root Optional root element to stop calculations at.


  		





  
  439
  
    
		 * @return {object} Absolute position of the specified element object with x, y fields.


  		





  
  440
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  441
  
    
		 getPos : function(node, root) {


  		





  
  442
  
    
			var x = 0, y = 0, parent, doc = document, nodeRect, rootRect;


  		





  
  443
  
    

  		





  
  444
  
    
			node = node;


  		





  
  445
  
    
			root = root || doc.body;


  		





  
  446
  
    

  		





  
  447
  
    
			// Returns the x, y cordinate for an element on IE 6 and IE 7


  		





  
  448
  
    
			function getIEPos(node) {


  		





  
  449
  
    
				var bodyElm, rect, x = 0, y = 0;


  		





  
  450
  
    

  		





  
  451
  
    
				if (node) {


  		





  
  452
  
    
					rect = node.getBoundingClientRect();


  		





  
  453
  
    
					bodyElm = doc.compatMode === "CSS1Compat" ? doc.documentElement : doc.body;


  		





  
  454
  
    
					x = rect.left + bodyElm.scrollLeft;


  		





  
  455
  
    
					y = rect.top + bodyElm.scrollTop;


  		





  
  456
  
    
				}


  		





  
  457
  
    

  		





  
  458
  
    
				return {


  		





  
  459
  
    
					x : x,


  		





  
  460
  
    
					y : y


  		





  
  461
  
    
				};


  		





  
  462
  
    
			}


  		





  
  463
  
    

  		





  
  464
  
    
			// Use getBoundingClientRect on IE 6 and IE 7 but not on IE 8 in standards mode


  		





  
  465
  
    
			if (node && node.getBoundingClientRect && (navigator.userAgent.indexOf('MSIE') > 0 && doc.documentMode !== 8)) {


  		





  
  466
  
    
				nodeRect = getIEPos(node);


  		





  
  467
  
    
				rootRect = getIEPos(root);


  		





  
  468
  
    

  		





  
  469
  
    
				return {


  		





  
  470
  
    
					x : nodeRect.x - rootRect.x,


  		





  
  471
  
    
					y : nodeRect.y - rootRect.y


  		





  
  472
  
    
				};


  		





  
  473
  
    
			}


  		





  
  474
  
    

  		





  
  475
  
    
			parent = node;


  		





  
  476
  
    
			while (parent && parent != root && parent.nodeType) {


  		





  
  477
  
    
				x += parent.offsetLeft || 0;


  		





  
  478
  
    
				y += parent.offsetTop || 0;


  		





  
  479
  
    
				parent = parent.offsetParent;


  		





  
  480
  
    
			}


  		





  
  481
  
    

  		





  
  482
  
    
			parent = node.parentNode;


  		





  
  483
  
    
			while (parent && parent != root && parent.nodeType) {


  		





  
  484
  
    
				x -= parent.scrollLeft || 0;


  		





  
  485
  
    
				y -= parent.scrollTop || 0;


  		





  
  486
  
    
				parent = parent.parentNode;


  		





  
  487
  
    
			}


  		





  
  488
  
    

  		





  
  489
  
    
			return {


  		





  
  490
  
    
				x : x,


  		





  
  491
  
    
				y : y


  		





  
  492
  
    
			};


  		





  
  493
  
    
		},


  		





  
  494
  
    

  		





  
  495
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  496
  
    
		 * Returns the size of the specified node in pixels.


  		





  
  497
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  498
  
    
		 * @param {Node} node Node to get the size of.


  		





  
  499
  
    
		 * @return {Object} Object with a w and h property.


  		





  
  500
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  501
  
    
		getSize : function(node) {


  		





  
  502
  
    
			return {


  		





  
  503
  
    
				w : node.offsetWidth || node.clientWidth,


  		





  
  504
  
    
				h : node.offsetHeight || node.clientHeight


  		





  
  505
  
    
			};


  		





  
  506
  
    
		},


  		





  
  507
  
    

  		





  
  508
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  509
  
    
		 * Parses the specified size string into a byte value. For example 10kb becomes 10240.


  		





  
  510
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  511
  
    
		 * @method parseSize


  		





  
  512
  
    
		 * @param {String/Number} size String to parse or number to just pass through.


  		





  
  513
  
    
		 * @return {Number} Size in bytes.


  		





  
  514
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  515
  
    
		parseSize : function(size) {


  		





  
  516
  
    
			var mul;


  		





  
  517
  
    

  		





  
  518
  
    
			if (typeof(size) == 'string') {


  		





  
  519
  
    
				size = /^([0-9]+)([mgk]?)$/.exec(size.toLowerCase().replace(/[^0-9mkg]/g, ''));


  		





  
  520
  
    
				mul = size[2];


  		





  
  521
  
    
				size = +size[1];


  		





  
  522
  
    

  		





  
  523
  
    
				if (mul == 'g') {


  		





  
  524
  
    
					size *= 1073741824;


  		





  
  525
  
    
				}


  		





  
  526
  
    

  		





  
  527
  
    
				if (mul == 'm') {


  		





  
  528
  
    
					size *= 1048576;


  		





  
  529
  
    
				}


  		





  
  530
  
    

  		





  
  531
  
    
				if (mul == 'k') {


  		





  
  532
  
    
					size *= 1024;


  		





  
  533
  
    
				}


  		





  
  534
  
    
			}


  		





  
  535
  
    

  		





  
  536
  
    
			return size;


  		





  
  537
  
    
		},


  		





  
  538
  
    

  		





  
  539
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  540
  
    
		 * Encodes the specified string.


  		





  
  541
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  542
  
    
		 * @method xmlEncode


  		





  
  543
  
    
		 * @param {String} s String to encode.


  		





  
  544
  
    
		 * @return {String} Encoded string.


  		





  
  545
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  546
  
    
		xmlEncode : function(str) {


  		





  
  547
  
    
			return str ? ('' + str).replace(xmlEncodeRegExp, function(chr) {


  		





  
  548
  
    
				return xmlEncodeChars[chr] ? '&' + xmlEncodeChars[chr] + ';' : chr;


  		





  
  549
  
    
			}) : str;


  		





  
  550
  
    
		},


  		





  
  551
  
    

  		





  
  552
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  553
  
    
		 * Forces anything into an array.


  		





  
  554
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  555
  
    
		 * @method toArray


  		





  
  556
  
    
		 * @param {Object} obj Object with length field.


  		





  
  557
  
    
		 * @return {Array} Array object containing all items.


  		





  
  558
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  559
  
    
		toArray : function(obj) {


  		





  
  560
  
    
			var i, arr = [];


  		





  
  561
  
    

  		





  
  562
  
    
			for (i = 0; i < obj.length; i++) {


  		





  
  563
  
    
				arr[i] = obj[i];


  		





  
  564
  
    
			}


  		





  
  565
  
    

  		





  
  566
  
    
			return arr;


  		





  
  567
  
    
		},


  		





  
  568
  
    

  		





  
  569
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  570
  
    
		 * Extends the language pack object with new items.


  		





  
  571
  
    
		 *

		 */

		addI18n : function(pack) {

  577
  
    
		},


  		





  
  578
  
    

  		





  
  579
  
    
		/**

  581
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  582
  
    
		 * @param {String} str String to look for.

		 * @return {String} Translated string or the input string if it wasn't found.


  		





  
  584
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  585
  
    
		translate : function(str) {


  		





  
  586
  
    
			return i18n[str] || str;


  		





  
  587
  
    
		},


  		





  
  588
  
    
		


  		





  
  589
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  590
  
    
		 * Checks if object is empty.


  		





  
  591
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  592
  
    
		 * @param {Object} obj Object to check.


  		





  
  593
  
    
		 * @return {Boolean}


  		





  
  594
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  595
  
    
		isEmptyObj : function(obj) {


  		





  
  596
  
    
			if (obj === undef) return true;


  		





  
  597
  
    
			


  		





  
  598
  
    
			for (var prop in obj) {


  		





  
  599
  
    
				return false;	


  		





  
  600
  
    
			}


  		





  
  601
  
    
			return true;


  		





  
  602
  
    
		},


  		





  
  603
  
    
		


  		





  
  604
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  605
  
    
		 * Checks if specified DOM element has specified class.


  		





  
  606
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  607
  
    
		 * @param {Object} obj DOM element like object to add handler to.


  		





  
  608
  
    
		 * @param {String} name Class name


  		





  
  609
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  610
  
    
		hasClass : function(obj, name) {


  		





  
  611
  
    
			var regExp;


  		





  
  612
  
    
		


  		





  
  613
  
    
			if (obj.className == '') {


  		





  
  614
  
    
				return false;


  		





  
  615
  
    
			}


  		





  
  616
  
    

  		





  
  617
  
    
			regExp = new RegExp("(^|\\s+)"+name+"(\\s+|$)");


  		





  
  618
  
    

  		





  
  619
  
    
			return regExp.test(obj.className);


  		





  
  620
  
    
		},


  		





  
  621
  
    
		


  		





  
  622
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  623
  
    
		 * Adds specified className to specified DOM element.


  		





  
  624
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  625
  
    
		 * @param {Object} obj DOM element like object to add handler to.


  		





  
  626
  
    
		 * @param {String} name Class name


  		





  
  627
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  628
  
    
		addClass : function(obj, name) {


  		





  
  629
  
    
			if (!plupload.hasClass(obj, name)) {


  		





  
  630
  
    
				obj.className = obj.className == '' ? name : obj.className.replace(/\s+$/, '')+' '+name;


  		





  
  631
  
    
			}


  		





  
  632
  
    
		},


  		





  
  633
  
    
		


  		





  
  634
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  635
  
    
		 * Removes specified className from specified DOM element.


  		





  
  636
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  637
  
    
		 * @param {Object} obj DOM element like object to add handler to.


  		





  
  638
  
    
		 * @param {String} name Class name


  		





  
  639
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  640
  
    
		removeClass : function(obj, name) {


  		





  
  641
  
    
			var regExp = new RegExp("(^|\\s+)"+name+"(\\s+|$)");


  		





  
  642
  
    
			


  		





  
  643
  
    
			obj.className = obj.className.replace(regExp, function($0, $1, $2) {


  		





  
  644
  
    
				return $1 === ' ' && $2 === ' ' ? ' ' : '';


  		





  
  645
  
    
			});


  		





  
  646
  
    
		},


  		





  
  647
  
    
    


  		





  
  648
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  649
  
    
		 * Returns a given computed style of a DOM element.


  		





  
  650
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  651
  
    
		 * @param {Object} obj DOM element like object.


  		





  
  652
  
    
		 * @param {String} name Style you want to get from the DOM element


  		





  
  653
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  654
  
    
		getStyle : function(obj, name) {


  		





  
  655
  
    
			if (obj.currentStyle) {


  		





  
  656
  
    
				return obj.currentStyle[name];


  		





  
  657
  
    
			} else if (window.getComputedStyle) {


  		





  
  658
  
    
				return window.getComputedStyle(obj, null)[name];


  		





  
  659
  
    
			}


  		





  
  660
  
    
		},


  		





  
  661
  
    

  		





  
  662
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  663
  
    
		 * Adds an event handler to the specified object and store reference to the handler


  		





  
  664
  
    
		 * in objects internal Plupload registry (@see removeEvent).


  		





  
  665
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  666
  
    
		 * @param {Object} obj DOM element like object to add handler to.


  		





  
  667
  
    
		 * @param {String} name Name to add event listener to.


  		





  
  668
  
    
		 * @param {Function} callback Function to call when event occurs.


  		





  
  669
  
    
		 * @param {String} (optional) key that might be used to add specifity to the event record.


  		





  
  670
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  671
  
    
		addEvent : function(obj, name, callback) {


  		





  
  672
  
    
			var func, events, types, key;


  		





  
  673
  
    
			


  		





  
  674
  
    
			// if passed in, event will be locked with this key - one would need to provide it to removeEvent


  		





  
  675
  
    
			key = arguments[3];


  		





  
  676
  
    
						


  		





  
  677
  
    
			name = name.toLowerCase();


  		





  
  678
  
    
						


  		





  
  679
  
    
			// Initialize unique identifier if needed


  		





  
  680
  
    
			if (uid === undef) {


  		





  
  681
  
    
				uid = 'Plupload_' + plupload.guid();


  		





  
  682
  
    
			}


  		





  
  683
  
    

  		





  
  684
  
    
			// Add event listener


  		





  
  685
  
    
			if (obj.addEventListener) {


  		





  
  686
  
    
				func = callback;


  		





  
  687
  
    
				


  		





  
  688
  
    
				obj.addEventListener(name, func, false);


  		





  
  689
  
    
			} else if (obj.attachEvent) {


  		





  
  690
  
    
				


  		





  
  691
  
    
				func = function() {


  		





  
  692
  
    
					var evt = window.event;


  		





  
  693
  
    

  		





  
  694
  
    
					if (!evt.target) {


  		





  
  695
  
    
						evt.target = evt.srcElement;


  		





  
  696
  
    
					}


  		





  
  697
  
    

  		





  
  698
  
    
					evt.preventDefault = preventDefault;


  		





  
  699
  
    
					evt.stopPropagation = stopPropagation;


  		





  
  700
  
    

  		





  
  701
  
    
					callback(evt);


  		





  
  702
  
    
				};


  		





  
  703
  
    
				obj.attachEvent('on' + name, func);


  		





  
  704
  
    
			} 


  		





  
  705
  
    
			


  		





  
  706
  
    
			// Log event handler to objects internal Plupload registry


  		





  
  707
  
    
			if (obj[uid] === undef) {


  		





  
  708
  
    
				obj[uid] = plupload.guid();


  		





  
  709
  
    
			}


  		





  
  710
  
    
			


  		





  
  711
  
    
			if (!eventhash.hasOwnProperty(obj[uid])) {


  		





  
  712
  
    
				eventhash[obj[uid]] = {};


  		





  
  713
  
    
			}


  		





  
  714
  
    
			


  		





  
  715
  
    
			events = eventhash[obj[uid]];


  		





  
  716
  
    
			


  		





  
  717
  
    
			if (!events.hasOwnProperty(name)) {


  		





  
  718
  
    
				events[name] = [];


  		





  
  719
  
    
			}


  		





  
  720
  
    
					


  		





  
  721
  
    
			events[name].push({


  		





  
  722
  
    
				func: func,


  		





  
  723
  
    
				orig: callback, // store original callback for IE


  		





  
  724
  
    
				key: key


  		





  
  725
  
    
			});


  		





  
  726
  
    
		},


  		





  
  727
  
    
		


  		





  
  728
  
    
		


  		





  
  729
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  730
  
    
		 * Remove event handler from the specified object. If third argument (callback)


  		





  
  731
  
    
		 * is not specified remove all events with the specified name.


  		





  
  732
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  733
  
    
		 * @param {Object} obj DOM element to remove event listener(s) from.


  		





  
  734
  
    
		 * @param {String} name Name of event listener to remove.


  		





  
  735
  
    
		 * @param {Function|String} (optional) might be a callback or unique key to match.


  		





  
  736
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  737
  
    
		removeEvent: function(obj, name) {


  		





  
  738
  
    
			var type, callback, key;


  		





  
  739
  
    
			


  		





  
  740
  
    
			// match the handler either by callback or by key	


  		





  
  741
  
    
			if (typeof(arguments[2]) == "function") {


  		





  
  742
  
    
				callback = arguments[2];


  		





  
  743
  
    
			} else {


  		





  
  744
  
    
				key = arguments[2];


  		





  
  745
  
    
			}


  		





  
  746
  
    
						


  		





  
  747
  
    
			name = name.toLowerCase();


  		





  
  748
  
    
			


  		





  
  749
  
    
			if (obj[uid] && eventhash[obj[uid]] && eventhash[obj[uid]][name]) {


  		





  
  750
  
    
				type = eventhash[obj[uid]][name];


  		





  
  751
  
    
			} else {


  		





  
  752
  
    
				return;


  		





  
  753
  
    
			}


  		





  
  754
  
    
			


  		





  
  755
  
    
				


  		





  
  756
  
    
			for (var i=type.length-1; i>=0; i--) {


  		





  
  757
  
    
				// undefined or not, key should match			


  		





  
  758
  
    
				if (type[i].key === key || type[i].orig === callback) {


  		





  
  759
  
    
										


  		





  
  760
  
    
					if (obj.detachEvent) {


  		





  
  761
  
    
						obj.detachEvent('on'+name, type[i].func);


  		





  
  762
  
    
					} else if (obj.removeEventListener) {


  		





  
  763
  
    
						obj.removeEventListener(name, type[i].func, false);		


  		





  
  764
  
    
					}


  		





  
  765
  
    
					


  		





  
  766
  
    
					type[i].orig = null;


  		





  
  767
  
    
					type[i].func = null;


  		





  
  768
  
    
					


  		





  
  769
  
    
					type.splice(i, 1);


  		





  
  770
  
    
					


  		





  
  771
  
    
					// If callback was passed we are done here, otherwise proceed


  		





  
  772
  
    
					if (callback !== undef) {


  		





  
  773
  
    
						break;


  		





  
  774
  
    
					}


  		





  
  775
  
    
				}			


  		





  
  776
  
    
			}	


  		





  
  777
  
    
			


  		





  
  778
  
    
			// If event array got empty, remove it


  		





  
  779
  
    
			if (!type.length) {


  		





  
  780
  
    
				delete eventhash[obj[uid]][name];


  		





  
  781
  
    
			}


  		





  
  782
  
    
			


  		





  
  783
  
    
			// If Plupload registry has become empty, remove it


  		





  
  784
  
    
			if (plupload.isEmptyObj(eventhash[obj[uid]])) {


  		





  
  785
  
    
				delete eventhash[obj[uid]];


  		





  
  786
  
    
				


  		





  
  787
  
    
				// IE doesn't let you remove DOM object property with - delete


  		





  
  788
  
    
				try {


  		





  
  789
  
    
					delete obj[uid];


  		





  
  790
  
    
				} catch(e) {


  		





  
  791
  
    
					obj[uid] = undef;


  		





  
  792
  
    
				}


  		





  
  793
  
    
			}


  		





  
  794
  
    
		},


  		





  
  795
  
    
		


  		





  
  796
  
    
		


  		





  
  797
  
    
		/**


  		





  
  798
  
    
		 * Remove all kind of events from the specified object


  		





  
  799
  
    
		 *


  		





  
  800
  
    
		 * @param {Object} obj DOM element to remove event listeners from.


  		





  
  801
  
    
		 * @param {String} (optional) unique key to match, when removing events.


  		





  
  802
  
    
		 */


  		





  
  803
  
    
		removeAllEvents: function(obj) {


  		





  
  804
  
    
			var key = arguments[1];


  		





  
  805
  
    
			


  		





  
  806
  
    
			if (obj[uid] === undef || !obj[uid]) {


  		





  
  807
  
    
				return;


  		





  
  808
  
    
			}


  		





  
  809
  
    
			


  		





  
  810
  
    
			plupload.each(eventhash[obj[uid]], function(events, name) {


  		





  
  811
  
    
				plupload.removeEvent(obj, name, key);


  		





  
  812
  
    
			});		


  		





  
  813
  
    
		}


  		





  
  814
  
    
	};


  		





  
  815
  
    
	


  		





  
  816
  
    

  		





  
  817
  
    
	/**


  		





  
  818
  
    
	 * Uploader class, an instance of this class will be created for each upload field.


  		





  
  819
  
    
	 *


  		





  
  820
  
    
	 * @example


  		





  
  821
  
    
	 * var uploader = new plupload.Uploader({


  		





  
  822
  
    
	 *     runtimes : 'gears,html5,flash',


  		





  
  823
  
    
	 *     browse_button : 'button_id'


  		





  
  824
  
    
	 * });


  		





  
  825
  
    
	 *


  		





  
  826
  
    
	 * uploader.bind('Init', function(up) {


  		





  
  827
  
    
	 *     alert('Supports drag/drop: ' + (!!up.features.dragdrop));


  		





  
  828
  
    
	 * });


  		





  
  829
  
    
	 *


  		





  
  830
  
    
	 * uploader.bind('FilesAdded', function(up, files) {


  		





  
  831
  
    
	 *     alert('Selected files: ' + files.length);


  		





  
  832
  
    
	 * });


  		





  
  833
  
    
	 *


  		





  
  834
  
    
	 * uploader.bind('QueueChanged', function(up) {


  		





  
  835
  
    
	 *     alert('Queued files: ' + uploader.files.length);


  		





  
  836
  
    
	 * });


  		





  
  837
  
    
	 *


  		





  
  838
  
    
	 * uploader.init();


  		





  
  839
  
    
	 *


  		





  
  840
  
    
	 * @class plupload.Uploader


  		





  
  841
  
    
	 */


  		





  
  842
  
    

  		





  
  843
  
    
	/**


  		





  
  844
  
    
	 * Constructs a new uploader instance.


  		





  
  845
  
    
	 *


  		





  
  846
  
    
	 * @constructor


  		





  
  847
  
    
	 * @method Uploader


  		





  
  848
  
    
	 * @param {Object} settings Initialization settings, to be used by the uploader instance and runtimes.


  		





  
  849
  
    
	 */


  		





  
  850
  
    
	plupload.Uploader = function(settings) {


  		





  
  851
  
    
		var events = {}, total, files = [], startTime;


  		





  
  852
  
    

  		





  
  853
  
    
		// Inital total state


  		





  
  854
  
    
		total = new plupload.QueueProgress();


  		





  
  855
  
    

  		





  
  856
  
    
		// Default settings


  		





  
  857
  
    
		settings = plupload.extend({


  		





  
  858
  
    
			chunk_size : 0,


  		





  
  859
  
    
			multipart : true,


  		





  
  860
  
    
			multi_selection : true,


  		





  
  861
  
    
			file_data_name : 'file',


  		





  
  862
  
    
			filters : []


  		





  
  863
  
    
		}, settings);


  		





  
  864
  
    

  		





  
  865
  
    
		// Private methods


  		





  
  866
  
    
		function uploadNext() {


  		





  
  867
  
    
			var file, count = 0, i;


  		





  
  868
  
    

  		





  
  869
  
    
			if (this.state == plupload.STARTED) {


  		





  
  870
  
    
				// Find first QUEUED file


  		





  
  871
  
    
				for (i = 0; i < files.length; i++) {


  		





  
  872
  
    
					if (!file && files[i].status == plupload.QUEUED) {


  		





  
  873
  
    
						file = files[i];


  		





  
  874
  
    
						file.status = plupload.UPLOADING;


  		





  
  875
  
    
						if (this.trigger("BeforeUpload", file)) {


  		





  
  876
  
    
							this.trigger("UploadFile", file);


  		





  
  877
  
    
						}


  		





  
  878
  
    
					} else {


  		





  
  879
  
    
						count++;


  		





  
  880
  
    
					}


  		





  
  881
  
    
				}


  		





  
  882
  
    

  		





  
  883
  
    
				// All files are DONE or FAILED


  		





  
  884
  
    
				if (count == files.length) {


  		





  
  885
  
    
					this.stop();


  		





  
  886
  
    
					this.trigger("UploadComplete", files);


  		





  
  887
  
    
				}


  		





  
  888
  
    
			}


  		





  
  889
  
    
		}


  		





  
  890
  
    

  		





  
  891
  
    
		function calc() {


  		





  
  892
  
    
			var i, file;


  		





  
  893
  
    

  		





  
  894
  
    
			// Reset stats


  		





  
  895
  
    
			total.reset();


  		





  
  896
  
    

  		





  
  897
  
    
			// Check status, size, loaded etc on all files


  		





  
  898
  
    
			for (i = 0; i < files.length; i++) {


  		





  
  899
  
    
				file = files[i];


  		





  
  900
  
    

  		





  
  901
  
    
				if (file.size !== undef) {


  		





  
  902
  
    
					total.size += file.size;


  		





  
  903
  
    
					total.loaded += file.loaded;


  		





  
  904
  
    
				} else {


  		





  
  905
  
    
					total.size = undef;


  		





  
  906
  
    
				}


  		





  
  907
  
    

  		





  
  908
  
    
				if (file.status == plupload.DONE) {


  		





  
  909
  
    
					total.uploaded++;


  		





  
  910
  
    
				} else if (file.status == plupload.FAILED) {


  		





  
  911
  
    
					total.failed++;


  		





  
  912
  
    
				} else {


  		





  
  913
  
    
					total.queued++;


  		





  
  914
  
    
				}


  		





  
  915
  
    
			}


  		





  
  916
  
    

  		





  
  917
  
    
			// If we couldn't calculate a total file size then use the number of files to calc percent


  		





  
  918
  
    
			if (total.size === undef) {


  		





  
  919
  
    
				total.percent = files.length > 0 ? Math.ceil(total.uploaded / files.length * 100) : 0;


  		





  
  920
  
    
			} else {


  		





  
  921
  
    
				total.bytesPerSec = Math.ceil(total.loaded / ((+new Date() - startTime || 1) / 1000.0));


  		





  
  922
  
    
				total.percent = total.size > 0 ? Math.ceil(total.loaded / total.size * 100) : 0;


  		





  
  923
  
    
			}


  		





  
  924
  
    
		}


  		





  
  925
  
    

  		





  
  926
  
    
		// Add public methods


  		





  
  927
  
    
		plupload.extend(this, {


  		





  
  928
  
    
			/**


  		





  
  929
  
    
			 * Current state of the total uploading progress. This one can either be plupload.STARTED or plupload.STOPPED.


  		





  
  930
  
    
			 * These states are controlled by the stop/start methods. The default value is STOPPED.


  		





  
  931
  
    
			 *


  		





  
  932
  
    
			 * @property state


  		





  
  933
  
    
			 * @type Number


  		





  
  934
  
    
			 */


  		





  
  935
  
    
			state : plupload.STOPPED,


  		





  
  936
  
    
			


  		





  
  937
  
    
			/**


  		





  
  938
  
    
			 * Current runtime name.


  		





  
  939
  
    
			 *


  		





  
  940
  
    
			 * @property runtime


  		





  
  941
  
    
			 * @type String


  		





  
  942
  
    
			 */


  		





  
  943
  
    
			runtime: '',


  		





  
  944
  
    

  		





  
  945
  
    
			/**


  		





  
  946
  
    
			 * Map of features that are available for the uploader runtime. Features will be filled


  		





  
  947
  
    
			 * before the init event is called, these features can then be used to alter the UI for the end user.


  		





  
  948
  
    
			 * Some of the current features that might be in this map is: dragdrop, chunks, jpgresize, pngresize.


  		





  
  949
  
    
			 *


  		





  
  950
  
    
			 * @property features


  		





  
  951
  
    
			 * @type Object


  		





  
  952
  
    
			 */


  		





  
  953
  
    
			features : {},


  		





  
  954
  
    

  		





  
  955
  
    
			/**


  		





  
  956
  
    
			 * Current upload queue, an array of File instances.


  		





  
  957
  
    
			 *


  		





  
  958
  
    
			 * @property files


  		





  
  959
  
    
			 * @type Array


  		





  
  960
  
    
			 * @see plupload.File


  		





  
  961
  
    
			 */


  		





  
  962
  
    
			files : files,


  		





  
  963
  
    

  		





  
  964
  
    
			/**


  		





  
  965
  
    
			 * Object with name/value settings.


  		





  
  966
  
    
			 *


  		





  
  967
  
    
			 * @property settings


  		





  
  968
  
    
			 * @type Object


  		





  
  969
  
    
			 */


  		





  
  970
  
    
			settings : settings,


  		





  
  971
  
    

  		





  
  972
  
    
			/**


  		





  
  973
  
    
			 * Total progess information. How many files has been uploaded, total percent etc.


  		





  
  974
  
    
			 *


  		





  
  975
  
    
			 * @property total


  		





  
  976
  
    
			 * @type plupload.QueueProgress


  		





  
  977
  
    
			 */


  		





  
  978
  
    
			total : total,


  		





  
  979
  
    

  		





  
  980
  
    
			/**


  		





  
  981
  
    
			 * Unique id for the Uploader instance.


  		





  
  982
  
    
			 *


  		





  
  983
  
    
			 * @property id


  		





  
  984
  
    
			 * @type String


  		





  
  985
  
    
			 */


  		





  
  986
  
    
			id : plupload.guid(),


  		





  
  987
  
    

  		





  
  988
  
    
			/**


  		





  
  989
  
    
			 * Initializes the Uploader instance and adds internal event listeners.


  		





  
  990
  
    
			 *


  		





  
  991
  
    
			 * @method init


  		





  
  992
  
    
			 */


  		





  
  993
  
    
			init : function() {


  		





  
  994
  
    
				var self = this, i, runtimeList, a, runTimeIndex = 0, items;


  		





  
  995
  
    

  		





  
  996
  
    
				if (typeof(settings.preinit) == "function") {


  		





  
  997
  
    
					settings.preinit(self);


  		





  
  998
  
    
				} else {


  		





  
  999
  
    
					plupload.each(settings.preinit, function(func, name) {


  		





  
  1000
  
    
						self.bind(name, func);


  		





  
  1001
  
    
					});


  		





  
  1002
  
    
				}


  		





  
  1003
  
    

  		





  
  1004
  
    
				settings.page_url = settings.page_url || document.location.pathname.replace(/\/[^\/]+$/g, '/');


  		





  
  1005
  
    

  		





  
  1006
  
    
				// If url is relative force it absolute to the current page


  		





  
  1007
  
    
				if (!/^(\w+:\/\/|\/)/.test(settings.url)) {


  		





  
  1008
  
    
					settings.url = settings.page_url + settings.url;


  		





  
  1009
  
    
				}


  		





  
  1010
  
    

  		





  
  1011
  
    
				// Convert settings


  		





  
  1012
  
    
				settings.chunk_size = plupload.parseSize(settings.chunk_size);


  		





  
  1013
  
    
				settings.max_file_size = plupload.parseSize(settings.max_file_size);


  		





  
  1014
  
    

  		





  
  1015
  
    
				// Add files to queue


  		





  
  1016
  
    
				self.bind('FilesAdded', function(up, selected_files) {


  		





  
  1017
  
    
					var i, file, count = 0, extensionsRegExp, filters = settings.filters;


  		





  
  1018
  
    

  		





  
  1019
  
    
					// Convert extensions to regexp


  		





  
  1020
  
    
					if (filters && filters.length) {


  		





  
  1021
  
    
						extensionsRegExp = [];


  		





  
  1022
  
    
						


  		





  
  1023
  
    
						plupload.each(filters, function(filter) {


  		





  
  1024
  
    
							plupload.each(filter.extensions.split(/,/), function(ext) {


  		





  
  1025
  
    
								if (/^\s*\*\s*$/.test(ext)) {


  		





  
  1026
  
    
									extensionsRegExp.push('\\.*');


  		





  
  1027
  
    
								} else {


  		





  
  1028
  
    
									extensionsRegExp.push('\\.' + ext.replace(new RegExp('[' + ('/^$.*+?|()[]{}\\'.replace(/./g, '\\$&')) + ']', 'g'), '\\$&'));


  		





  
  1029
  
    
								}


  		





  
  1030
  
    
							});


  		





  
  1031
  
    
						});


  		





  
  1032
  
    
						


  		





  
  1033
  
    
						extensionsRegExp = new RegExp(extensionsRegExp.join('|') + '$', 'i');


  		





  
  1034
  
    
					}


  		





  
  1035
  
    

  		





  
  1036
  
    
					for (i = 0; i < selected_files.length; i++) {


  		





  
  1037
  
    
						file = selected_files[i];


  		





  
  1038
  
    
						file.loaded = 0;


  		





  
  1039
  
    
						file.percent = 0;


  		





  
  1040
  
    
						file.status = plupload.QUEUED;


  		





  
  1041
  
    

  		





  
  1042
  
    
						// Invalid file extension


  		





  
  1043
  
    
						if (extensionsRegExp && !extensionsRegExp.test(file.name)) {


  		





  
  1044
  
    
							up.trigger('Error', {


  		





  
  1045
  
    
								code : plupload.FILE_EXTENSION_ERROR,


  		





  
  1046
  
    
								message : plupload.translate('File extension error.'),


  		





  
  1047
  
    
								file : file


  		





  
  1048
  
    
							});


  		





  
  1049
  
    

  		





  
  1050
  
    
							continue;


  		





  
  1051
  
    
						}


  		





  
  1052
  
    

  		





  
  1053
  
    
						// Invalid file size


  		





  
  1054
  
    
						if (file.size !== undef && file.size > settings.max_file_size) {


  		





  
  1055
  
    
							up.trigger('Error', {


  		





  
  1056
  
    
								code : plupload.FILE_SIZE_ERROR,


  		





  
  1057
  
    
								message : plupload.translate('File size error.'),


  		





  
  1058
  
    
								file : file


  		





  
  1059
  
    
							});


  		





  
  1060
  
    

  		





  
  1061
  
    
							continue;


  		





  
  1062
  
    
						}


  		





  
  1063
  
    

  		





  
  1064
  
    
						// Add valid file to list


  		





  
  1065
  
    
						files.push(file);


  		





  
  1066
  
    
						count++;


  		





  
  1067
  
    
					}


  		





  
  1068
  
    

  		





  
  1069
  
    
					// Only trigger QueueChanged event if any files where added


  		





  
  1070
  
    
					if (count) {


  		





  
  1071
  
    
						delay(function() {


  		





  
  1072
  
    
							self.trigger("QueueChanged");


  		





  
  1073
  
    
							self.refresh();


  		





  
  1074
  
    
						}, 1);


  		





  
  1075
  
    
					} else {


  		





  
  1076
  
    
						return false; // Stop the FilesAdded event from immediate propagation


  		





  
  1077
  
    
					}


  		





  
  1078
  
    
				});


  		





  
  1079
  
    

  		





  
  1080
  
    
				// Generate unique target filenames


  		





  
  1081
  
    
				if (settings.unique_names) {


  		





  
  1082
  
    
					self.bind("UploadFile", function(up, file) {


  		





  
  1083
  
    
						var matches = file.name.match(/\.([^.]+)$/), ext = "tmp";


  		





  
  1084
  
    

  		





  
  1085
  
    
						if (matches) {


  		





  
  1086
  
    
							ext = matches[1];


  		





  
  1087
  
    
						}


  		





  
  1088
  
    

  		





  
  1089
  
    
						file.target_name = file.id + '.' + ext;


  		





  
  1090
  
    
					});


  		





  
  1091
  
    
				}


  		





  
  1092
  
    

  		





  
  1093
  
    
				self.bind('UploadProgress', function(up, file) {


  		





  
  1094
  
    
					file.percent = file.size > 0 ? Math.ceil(file.loaded / file.size * 100) : 100;


  		





  
  1095
  
    
					calc();


  		





  
  1096
  
    
				});


  		





  
  1097
  
    

  		





  
  1098
  
    
				self.bind('StateChanged', function(up) {


  		





  
  1099
  
    
					if (up.state == plupload.STARTED) {


  		





  
  1100
  
    
						// Get start time to calculate bps


  		





  
  1101
  
    
						startTime = (+new Date());


  		





  
  1102
  
    
						


  		





  
  1103
  
    
					} else if (up.state == plupload.STOPPED) {


  		





  
  1104
  
    
						// Reset currently uploading files


  		





  
  1105
  
    
						for (i = up.files.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {


  		





  
  1106
  
    
							if (up.files[i].status == plupload.UPLOADING) {


  		





  
  1107
  
    
								up.files[i].status = plupload.QUEUED;


  		





  
  1108
  
    
								calc();


  		





  
  1109
  
    
							}


  		





  
  1110
  
    
						}


  		





  
  1111
  
    
					}


  		





  
  1112
  
    
				});


  		





  
  1113
  
    

  		





  
  1114
  
    
				self.bind('QueueChanged', calc);


  		





  
  1115
  
    

  		





  
  1116
  
    
				self.bind("Error", function(up, err) {


  		





  
  1117
  
    
					// Set failed status if an error occured on a file


  		





  
  1118
  
    
					if (err.file) {


  		





  
  1119
  
    
						err.file.status = plupload.FAILED;


  		





  
  1120
  
    
						calc();


  		





  
  1121
  
    

  		





  
  1122
  
    
						// Upload next file but detach it from the error event


  		





  
  1123
  
    
						// since other custom listeners might want to stop the queue


  		





  
  1124
  
    
						if (up.state == plupload.STARTED) {


  		





  
  1125
  
    
							delay(function() {


  		





  
  1126
  
    
								uploadNext.call(self);


  		





  
  1127
  
    
							}, 1);


  		





  
  1128
  
    
						}


  		





  
  1129
  
    
					}


  		





  
  1130
  
    
				});


  		





  
  1131
  
    

  		





  
  1132
  
    
				self.bind("FileUploaded", function(up, file) {


  		





  
  1133
  
    
					file.status = plupload.DONE;


  		





  
  1134
  
    
					file.loaded = file.size;


  		





  
  1135
  
    
					up.trigger('UploadProgress', file);


  		





  
  1136
  
    

  		





  
  1137
  
    
					// Upload next file but detach it from the error event


  		





  
  1138
  
    
					// since other custom listeners might want to stop the queue


  		





  
  1139
  
    
					delay(function() {


  		





  
  1140
  
    
						uploadNext.call(self);


  		





  
  1141
  
    
					}, 1);


  		





  
  1142
  
    
				});


  		





  
  1143
  
    

  		





  
  1144
  
    
				// Setup runtimeList


  		





  
  1145
  
    
				if (settings.runtimes) {


  		





  
  1146
  
    
					runtimeList = [];


  		





  
  1147
  
    
					items = settings.runtimes.split(/\s?,\s?/);


  		





  
  1148
  
    

  		





  
  1149
  
    
					for (i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {


  		





  
  1150
  
    
						if (runtimes[items[i]]) {


  		





  
  1151
  
    
							runtimeList.push(runtimes[items[i]]);


  		





  
  1152
  
    
						}


  		





  
  1153
  
    
					}


  		





  
  1154
  
    
				} else {


  		





  
  1155
  
    
					runtimeList = runtimes;


  		





  
  1156
  
    
				}


  		





  
  1157
  
    

  		





  
  1158
  
    
				// Call init on each runtime in sequence


  		





  
  1159
  
    
				function callNextInit() {


  		





  
  1160
  
    
					var runtime = runtimeList[runTimeIndex++], features, requiredFeatures, i;


  		





  
  1161
  
    

  		





  
  1162
  
    
					if (runtime) {


  		





  
  1163
  
    
						features = runtime.getFeatures();


  		





  
  1164
  
    

  		





  
  1165
  
    
						// Check if runtime supports required features


  		





  
  1166
  
    
						requiredFeatures = self.settings.required_features;


  		





  
  1167
  
    
						if (requiredFeatures) {


  		





  
  1168
  
    
							requiredFeatures = requiredFeatures.split(',');


  		





  
  1169
  
    

  		





  
  1170
  
    
							for (i = 0; i < requiredFeatures.length; i++) {


  		





  
  1171
  
    
								// Specified feature doesn't exist


  		





  
  1172
  
    
								if (!features[requiredFeatures[i]]) {


  		





  
  1173
  
    
									callNextInit();


  		





  
  1174
  
    
									return;


  		





  
  1175
  
    
								}


  		





  
  1176
  
    
							}


  		





  
  1177
  
    
						}


  		





  
  1178
  
    

  		





  
  1179
  
    
						// Try initializing the runtime


  		





  
  1180
  
    
						runtime.init(self, function(res) {


  		





  
  1181
  
    
							if (res && res.success) {


  		





  
  1182
  
    
								// Successful initialization


  		





  
  1183
  
    
								self.features = features;


  		





  
  1184
  
    
								self.runtime = runtime.name;


  		





  
  1185
  
    
								self.trigger('Init', {runtime : runtime.name});


  		





  
  1186
  
    
								self.trigger('PostInit');


  		





  
  1187
  
    
								self.refresh();


  		





  
  1188
  
    
							} else {


  		





  
  1189
  
    
								callNextInit();


  		





  
  1190
  
    
							}


  		





  
  1191
  
    
						});


  		





  
  1192
  
    
					} else {


  		





  
  1193
  
    
						// Trigger an init error if we run out of runtimes


  		





  
  1194
  
    
						self.trigger('Error', {


  		





  
  1195
  
    
							code : plupload.INIT_ERROR,


  		





  
  1196
  
    
							message : plupload.translate('Init error.')


  		





  
  1197
  
    
						});


  		





  
  1198
  
    
					}


  		





  
  1199
  
    
				}


  		





  
  1200
  
    

  		





  
  1201
  
    
				callNextInit();


  		





  
  1202
  
    

  		





  
  1203
  
    
				if (typeof(settings.init) == "function") {


  		





  
  1204
  
    
					settings.init(self);


  		





  
  1205
  
    
				} else {


  		





  
  1206
  
    
					plupload.each(settings.init, function(func, name) {


  		





  
  1207
  
    
						self.bind(name, func);
